130 SketchObject::SketchObject() : geoLastId(0)
131 {
132  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(
133  Geometry, (nullptr), "Sketch", (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_None), "Sketch geometry");
134  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(Constraints,
135  (nullptr),
136  "Sketch",
137  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_None),
138  "Sketch constraints");
139  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(ExternalGeometry,
140  (nullptr, nullptr),
141  "Sketch",
142  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_None | App::Prop_ReadOnly),
143  "Sketch external geometry");
144  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(ExternalTypes,
145  ({}),
146  "Sketch",
147  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_None | App::Prop_Hidden),
148  "Sketch external geometry type: 0 = projection, 1 = intersection, 2 = both.");
149  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(FullyConstrained,
150  (false),
151  "Sketch",
152  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_Output | App::Prop_ReadOnly | App::Prop_Hidden),
153  "Sketch is fully constrained");
154  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(Exports,
155  (nullptr),
156  "Sketch",
157  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_Hidden),"Sketch export geometry");
158  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(ExternalGeo,
159  (nullptr),
160  "Sketch",
161  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_Hidden),"Sketch external geometry");
162  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(ArcFitTolerance,
163  (0.0),
164  "Sketch",
165  (App::PropertyType)(App::Prop_None),
166  "Tolerance for fitting arcs of projected external geometry");
167  ADD_PROPERTY(InternalShape,
168  (Part::TopoShape()));
169  ADD_PROPERTY_TYPE(MakeInternals,
170  (false),
171  "Internal Geometry",
172  App::Prop_None,
173  "Make internal geometry, e.g. split intersecting edges, face of closed wires.");
174 
175  Geometry.setOrderRelevant(true);
176 
177  allowOtherBody = true;
178  allowUnaligned = true;
179 
180  initExternalGeo();
181 
182  rebuildVertexIndex();
183 
184  lastDoF = 0;
185  lastHasConflict = false;
186  lastHasRedundancies = false;
187  lastHasPartialRedundancies = false;
188  lastHasMalformedConstraints = false;
189  lastSolverStatus = 0;
190  lastSolveTime = 0;
191 
192  solverNeedsUpdate = false;
193 
194  noRecomputes = false;
195 
196  //NOLINTBEGIN
197  ExpressionEngine.setValidator(
198  std::bind(&Sketcher::SketchObject::validateExpression, this, sp::_1, sp::_2));
199 
200  constraintsRemovedConn = Constraints.signalConstraintsRemoved.connect(
201  std::bind(&Sketcher::SketchObject::constraintsRemoved, this, sp::_1));
202  constraintsRenamedConn = Constraints.signalConstraintsRenamed.connect(
203  std::bind(&Sketcher::SketchObject::constraintsRenamed, this, sp::_1));
204  //NOLINTEND
205 
206  analyser = new SketchAnalysis(this);
207 
208  internaltransaction = false;
209  managedoperation = false;
210 
211  registerElementCache(internalPrefix(), &InternalShape);
212 }
213 
214 SketchObject::~SketchObject() {
215  delete analyser;
216 }

218 void SketchObject::setupObject()
219 {
220  ParameterGrp::handle hGrpp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
221  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
222  ArcFitTolerance.setValue(hGrpp->GetFloat("ArcFitTolerance", Precision::Confusion()*10.0));
223  MakeInternals.setValue(hGrpp->GetBool("MakeInternals", false));
224  inherited::setupObject();
225 }
226 
227 void SketchObject::initExternalGeo() {
228  std::vector<Part::Geometry *> geos;
229  auto HLine = GeometryTypedFacade<Part::GeomLineSegment>::getTypedFacade();
230  auto VLine = GeometryTypedFacade<Part::GeomLineSegment>::getTypedFacade();
231  HLine->getTypedGeometry()->setPoints(Base::Vector3d(0,0,0),Base::Vector3d(1,0,0));
232  VLine->getTypedGeometry()->setPoints(Base::Vector3d(0,0,0),Base::Vector3d(0,1,0));
233  HLine->setConstruction(true);
234  HLine->setId(-1);
235  VLine->setConstruction(true);
236  VLine->setId(-2);
237  geos.push_back(HLine->getGeometry());
238  geos.push_back(VLine->getGeometry());
239  HLine->setOwner(false); // we have transferred the ownership to ExternalGeo
240  VLine->setOwner(false); // we have transferred the ownership to ExternalGeo
241  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
242 }
243 
244 short SketchObject::mustExecute() const
245 {
246  if (Geometry.isTouched())
247  return 1;
248  if (Constraints.isTouched())
249  return 1;
250  if (ExternalGeometry.isTouched())
251  return 1;
252  if (ExternalGeo.isTouched())
253  return 1;
254  return Part2DObject::mustExecute();
255 }
256 
257 App::DocumentObjectExecReturn* SketchObject::execute()
258 {
259  try {
260  App::DocumentObjectExecReturn* rtn = Part2DObject::execute();// to positionBySupport
261  if (rtn != App::DocumentObject::StdReturn)
262  // error
263  return rtn;
264  }
265  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
266  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn(e.what());
267  }
268 
269  // setup and diagnose the sketch
270  try {
271  rebuildExternalGeometry();
272  Constraints.acceptGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
273  }
274  catch (const Base::Exception&) {
275  // 9/16/24: We used to clear the constraints here, but we no longer want to do that
276  // as missing reference geometry is not considered an error while we sort out sketcher UI.
277  // Base::Console().Error("%s\nClear constraints to external geometry\n", e.what());
278  // we cannot trust the constraints of external geometries, so remove them
279  // delConstraintsToExternal();
280  }
281 
282  // This includes a regular solve including full geometry update, except when an error
283  // ensues
284  int err = this->solve(true);
285 
286  if (err == -4) {// over-constrained sketch
287  std::string msg = "Over-constrained sketch\n";
288  appendConflictMsg(lastConflicting, msg);
289  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn(msg.c_str(), this);
290  }
291  else if (err == -3) {// conflicting constraints
292  std::string msg = "Sketch with conflicting constraints\n";
293  appendConflictMsg(lastConflicting, msg);
294  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn(msg.c_str(), this);
295  }
296  else if (err == -2) {// redundant constraints
297  std::string msg = "Sketch with redundant constraints\n";
298  appendRedundantMsg(lastRedundant, msg);
299  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn(msg.c_str(), this);
300  }
301  else if (err == -5) {
302  std::string msg = "Sketch with malformed constraints\n";
303  appendMalformedConstraintsMsg(lastMalformedConstraints, msg);
304  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn(msg.c_str(), this);
305  }
306  else if (err == -1) {// Solver failed
307  return new App::DocumentObjectExecReturn("Solving the sketch failed", this);
308  }
309 
310  // this is not necessary for sketch representation in edit mode, unless we want to trigger an
311  // update of the objects that depend on this sketch (like pads)
312  buildShape();
313 
314  return App::DocumentObject::StdReturn;
315 }
316 
317 static bool inline checkSmallEdge(const Part::TopoShape &s) {
318  if (s.shapeType() != TopAbs_EDGE)
319  return false;
320  BRepAdaptor_Curve adapt(TopoDS::Edge(s.getShape()));
321  return GCPnts_AbscissaPoint::Length(adapt, Precision::Confusion()) <= Precision::Confusion();
322 }
323 
324 void SketchObject::buildShape() {
325  // Shape.setValue(solvedSketch.toShape());
326  // We use the following instead to map element names
327 
328  std::vector<Part::TopoShape> shapes;
329  std::vector<Part::TopoShape> vertices;
330  int geoId =0;
331 
332  // get the geometry after running the solver
333  auto geometries = solvedSketch.extractGeometry();
334  for(auto geo : geometries) {
335  ++geoId;
336  if(GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo)) {
337  continue;
338  }
339  if (geo->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
340  Part::TopoShape vertex(TopoDS::Vertex(geo->toShape()));
341  int idx = getVertexIndexGeoPos(geoId -1, Sketcher::PointPos::start);
342  std::string name = convertSubName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", idx+1), false);
343  if (!vertex.hasElementMap()) {
344  vertex.resetElementMap(std::make_shared<Data::ElementMap>());
345  } vertex.setElementName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", 1),
346  Data::MappedName::fromRawData(name.c_str()),0L);
347  vertices.push_back(vertex);
348  vertices.back().copyElementMap(vertex, Part::OpCodes::Sketch);
349  } else {
350  auto indexedName = Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Edge", geoId);
351  shapes.push_back(getEdge(geo,convertSubName(indexedName, false).c_str()));
352  if (checkSmallEdge(shapes.back())) {
353  FC_WARN("Edge too small: " << indexedName);
354  }
355  }
356  }
357 
358  for (auto geo : geometries) {
359  delete geo;
360  }
361 
362  for(int i=2;i<ExternalGeo.getSize();++i) {
363  auto geo = ExternalGeo[i];
364  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
365  if(!egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining))
366  continue;
367  auto indexedName = Data::IndexedName::fromConst("ExternalEdge", i-1);
368  shapes.push_back(getEdge(geo, convertSubName(indexedName, false).c_str()));
369  if (checkSmallEdge(shapes.back())) {
370  FC_WARN("Edge too small: " << indexedName);
371  }
372  }
373 
374  internalElementMap.clear();
375 
376  if(shapes.empty() && vertices.empty()) {
377  InternalShape.setValue(Part::TopoShape());
378  Shape.setValue(Part::TopoShape());
379  return;
380  }
381  Part::TopoShape result(0, getDocument()->getStringHasher());
382  if (vertices.empty()) {
383  // Notice here we supply op code Part::OpCodes::Sketch to makEWires().
384  result.makeElementWires(shapes,Part::OpCodes::Sketch);
385  } else {
386  std::vector<Part::TopoShape> results;
387  if (!shapes.empty()) {
388  // Note, that we HAVE TO add the Part::OpCodes::Sketch op code to all
389  // geometry exposed through the Shape property, because
390  // SketchObject::getElementName() relies on this op code to
391  // differentiate geometries that are exposed with those in edit
392  // mode.
393  auto wires = Part::TopoShape().makeElementWires(shapes, Part::OpCodes::Sketch);
394  for (const auto &wire : wires.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_WIRE))
395  results.push_back(wire);
396  }
397  results.insert(results.end(), vertices.begin(), vertices.end());
398  result.makeElementCompound(results);
399  }
400  result.Tag = getID();
401  InternalShape.setValue(buildInternals(result.located(TopLoc_Location())));
402  // Must set Shape property after InternalShape so that
403  // GeoFeature::updateElementReference() can run properly on change of Shape
404  // property, because some reference may pointing to the InternalShape
405  Shape.setValue(result);
406 }
407 
408 const std::map<std::string,std::string> SketchObject::getInternalElementMap() const
409 {
410  if (!internalElementMap.empty() || !MakeInternals.getValue())
411  return internalElementMap;
412 
413  auto internalShape = InternalShape.getShape();
414  auto shape = Shape.getShape().located(TopLoc_Location());
415  if (!internalShape.isNull() && !shape.isNull()) {
416  std::vector<std::string> names;
417  std::string prefix;
418  const std::array<TopAbs_ShapeEnum, 2> types = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE};
419  for (const auto &type : types) {
420  prefix = internalPrefix() + Part::TopoShape::shapeName(type);
421  std::size_t len = prefix.size();
422  int i=0;
423  for (const auto &v : internalShape.getSubTopoShapes(type)) {
424  ++i;
425  shape.findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(v, &names, Data::SearchOption::CheckGeometry
426  |Data::SearchOption::SingleResult);
427  if (names.empty())
428  continue;
429  prefix += std::to_string(i);
430  internalElementMap[prefix] = names.front();
431  internalElementMap[names.front()] = prefix;
432  prefix.resize(len);
433  names.clear();
434  }
435  }
436  }
437  return internalElementMap;
438 }
439 
440 Part::TopoShape SketchObject::buildInternals(const Part::TopoShape &edges) const {
441  if (!MakeInternals.getValue())
442  return Part::TopoShape();
443 
444  try {
445  Part::WireJoiner joiner;
446  joiner.setTightBound(true);
447  joiner.setMergeEdges(true);
448  joiner.addShape(edges);
449  Part::TopoShape result(getID(), getDocument()->getStringHasher());
450  if (!joiner.Shape().IsNull()) {
451  joiner.getResultWires(result, "SKF");
452  result = result.makeElementFace(result.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_WIRE),
453  /*op*/"",
454  /*maker*/"Part::FaceMakerBullseye",
455  /*pln*/nullptr
456  );
457  }
458  Part::TopoShape openWires(getID(), getDocument()->getStringHasher());
459  joiner.getOpenWires(openWires, "SKF");
460  if (openWires.isNull())
461  return result; // No open wires, return either face or empty toposhape
462  if (result.isNull())
463  return openWires; // No face, but we have open wires to return as a shape
464  return result.makeElementCompound({result, openWires}); // Compound and return both
465  } catch (Base::Exception &e) {
466  FC_WARN("Failed to make face for sketch: " << e.what());
467  } catch (Standard_Failure &e) {
468  FC_WARN("Failed to make face for sketch: " << e.GetMessageString());
469  }
470  return Part::TopoShape();
471 }
472 
473 static const char *hasSketchMarker(const char *name) {
474  static std::string marker(Part::TopoShape::elementMapPrefix()+Part::OpCodes::Sketch);
475  if (!name)
476  return nullptr;
477  return strstr(name,marker.c_str());
478 }
479 
480 int SketchObject::hasConflicts() const
481 {
482  if (lastDoF < 0)// over-constrained sketch
483  return -2;
484  if (solvedSketch.hasConflicts())// conflicting constraints
485  return -1;
486 
487  return 0;
488 }
489 
490 void SketchObject::retrieveSolverDiagnostics()
491 {
492  lastHasConflict = solvedSketch.hasConflicts();
493  lastHasRedundancies = solvedSketch.hasRedundancies();
494  lastHasPartialRedundancies = solvedSketch.hasPartialRedundancies();
495  lastHasMalformedConstraints = solvedSketch.hasMalformedConstraints();
496  lastConflicting = solvedSketch.getConflicting();
497  lastRedundant = solvedSketch.getRedundant();
498  lastPartiallyRedundant = solvedSketch.getPartiallyRedundant();
499  lastMalformedConstraints = solvedSketch.getMalformedConstraints();
500 }
501 
502 int SketchObject::solve(bool updateGeoAfterSolving /*=true*/)
503 {
504  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
505  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
506 
507  // Reset the initial movement in case of a dragging operation was ongoing on the solver.
508  solvedSketch.resetInitMove();
509 
510  // if updateGeoAfterSolving=false, the solver information is updated, but the Sketch is nothing
511  // updated. It is useful to avoid triggering an OnChange when the goeometry did not change but
512  // the solver needs to be updated.
513 
514  // We should have an updated Sketcher (sketchobject) geometry or this solve() should not have
515  // happened therefore we update our sketch solver geometry with the SketchObject one.
516  //
517  // set up a sketch (including dofs counting and diagnosing of conflicts)
518  lastDoF = solvedSketch.setUpSketch(
519  getCompleteGeometry(), Constraints.getValues(), getExternalGeometryCount());
520 
521  // At this point we have the solver information about conflicting/redundant/over-constrained,
522  // but the sketch is NOT solved. Some examples: Redundant: a vertical line, a horizontal line
523  // and an angle constraint of 90 degrees between the two lines Conflicting: a 80 degrees angle
524  // between a vertical line and another line, then adding a horizontal constraint to that other
525  // line OverConstrained: a conflicting constraint when all other DoF are already constrained (it
526  // has more constraints than parameters and the extra constraints are not redundant)
527 
528  solverNeedsUpdate = false;
529 
530  retrieveSolverDiagnostics();
531 
532  lastSolveTime = 0.0;
533 
534  // Failure is default for notifying the user unless otherwise proven
535  lastSolverStatus = GCS::Failed;
536 
537  int err = 0;
538 
539  // redundancy is a lower priority problem than conflict/over-constraint/solver error
540  // we set it here because we are indeed going to solve, as we can. However, we still want to
541  // provide the right error code.
542  if (lastHasRedundancies) {// redundant constraints
543  err = -2;
544  }
545 
546  if (lastDoF < 0) {// over-constrained sketch
547  err = -4;
548  }
549  else if (lastHasConflict) {// conflicting constraints
550  // The situation is exactly the same as in the over-constrained situation.
551  err = -3;
552  }
553  else if (lastHasMalformedConstraints) {
554  err = -5;
555  }
556  else {
557  lastSolverStatus = solvedSketch.solve();
558  if (lastSolverStatus != 0) {// solving
559  err = -1;
560  }
561  }
562 
563  if (lastHasMalformedConstraints) {
564  Base::Console().Error(
565  this->getFullLabel(),
566  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications", "The Sketch has malformed constraints!") "\n");
567  }
568 
569  if (lastHasPartialRedundancies) {
570  Base::Console().Warning(
571  this->getFullLabel(),
572  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications",
573  "The Sketch has partially redundant constraints!") "\n");
574  }
575 
576  lastSolveTime = solvedSketch.getSolveTime();
577 
578  // In uncommon situations, the analysis of QR decomposition leads to full rank, but the result
579  // does not converge. We avoid marking a sketch as fully constrained when no convergence is
580  // achieved.
581  if (err == 0) {
582  FullyConstrained.setValue(lastDoF == 0);
583  }
584 
585  if (err == 0 && updateGeoAfterSolving) {
586  // set the newly solved geometry
587  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geomlist = solvedSketch.extractGeometry();
588  Part::PropertyGeometryList tmp;
589  tmp.setValues(std::move(geomlist));
590  // Only set values if there is actual changes
591  if (!Geometry.isSame(tmp))
592  Geometry.moveValues(std::move(tmp));
593  }
594  else if (err < 0) {
595  // if solver failed, invalid constraints were likely added before solving
596  // (see solve in addConstraint), so solver information is definitely invalid.
597  //
598  // Update: ViewProviderSketch shall now rely on the signalSolverUpdate below for update
599  // this->Constraints.touch();
600  }
601 
602  signalSolverUpdate();
603 
604  return err;
605 }

610 // NOLINTNEXTLINE
611 BOOST_GEOMETRY_REGISTER_POINT_3D(Base::Vector3d, double, bg::cs::cartesian, x, y, z)
612 
613 class SketchObject::GeoHistory
614 {
615 private:
616  static constexpr int bgiMaxElements = 16;
617 
618  using Parameters = bgi::linear<bgiMaxElements>;
619  using IdSet = std::set<long>;
620  using IdSets = std::pair<IdSet, IdSet>;
621  using AdjList = std::list<IdSet>;
622 
623  // associate a geo with connected ones on both points
624  using AdjMap = std::map<long, IdSets>;
625 
626  // maps start/end points to all existing geo to query and update adjacencies
627  using Value = std::pair<Base::Vector3d, AdjList::iterator>;
628 
629  AdjList adjlist;
630  AdjMap adjmap;
631  bgi::rtree<Value,Parameters> rtree;
632 
633 public:
634  AdjList::iterator find(const Base::Vector3d &pt,bool strict=true){
635  std::vector<Value> ret;
636  rtree.query(bgi::nearest(pt, 1), std::back_inserter(ret));
637  if (!ret.empty()) {
638  // NOTE: we are using square distance here, the 1e-6 threshold is
639  // very forgiving. We should have used Precision::SquareConfisuion(),
640  // which is 1e-14. However, there is a problem with current
641  // commandGeoCreate. They create new geometry with initial point of
642  // the exact mouse position, instead of the pre-selected point
643  // position, and rely on auto constraint to snap in the new
644  // geometry. So, we cannot use a very strict threshold here.
645  double tol = strict?Precision::SquareConfusion()*10:1e-6;
646  double d = Base::DistanceP2(ret[0].first,pt);
647  if(d<tol) {
648  return ret[0].second;
649  }
650  }
651  return adjlist.end();
652  }
653 
654  void clear() {
655  rtree.clear();
656  adjlist.clear();
657  }
658 
659  void update(const Base::Vector3d &pt, long id) {
660  FC_TRACE("update " << id << ", " << FC_xyz(pt));
661  auto it = find(pt);
662  if(it==adjlist.end()) {
663  adjlist.emplace_back();
664  it = adjlist.end();
665  --it;
666  rtree.insert(std::make_pair(pt,it));
667  }
668  it->insert(id);
669  }
670 
671  void finishUpdate(const std::map<long,int> &geomap) {
672  IdSet oldset;
673  for(auto &idset : adjlist) {
674  oldset.clear();
675  for(long _id : idset) {
676  long id = abs(_id);
677  auto& v = adjmap[id];
678  auto& adj = _id > 0 ? v.first : v.second;
679  for (auto it = adj.begin(); it != adj.end(); /* don't advance here */) {
680  long other = *it;
681  auto removeId = it++; // grab ID we might erase, and advance
682  if (geomap.find(other) == geomap.end()) {
683  // remember those deleted IDs to swap in below
684  oldset.insert(other);
685  }
686  else if (idset.find(other) == idset.end()) {
687  // delete any existing IDs that are no longer in the adj list
688  adj.erase(removeId);
689  }
690  }
691  // now merge the current ones
692  for(long _id2 : idset) {
693  long id2 = abs(_id2);
694  if(id!=id2) {
695  adj.insert(id2);
696  }
697  }
698  }
699  // now reset the adjacency list with only those deleted id's,
700  // because the whole purpose of this history is to try to reuse
701  // deleted id.
702  idset.swap(oldset);
703  }
704  }
705 
706  AdjList::iterator end() {
707  return adjlist.end();
708  }
709 
710  size_t size() {
711  return rtree.size();
712  }
713 };
714 
715 void SketchObject::updateGeoHistory() {
716  if(!geoHistoryLevel) return;
717 
718  if (!geoHistory) {
719  geoHistory = std::make_unique<GeoHistory>();
720  }
721 
722  FC_TIME_INIT(t);
723  const auto &geos = getInternalGeometry();
724  geoHistory->clear();
725  for (auto geo : geos) {
726  auto pstart = getPoint(geo, PointPos::start);
727  auto pend = getPoint(geo, PointPos::end);
728  int id = GeometryFacade::getId(geo);
729  geoHistory->update(pstart,id);
730  if(pstart!=pend)
731  geoHistory->update(pend,-id);
732  }
733  geoHistory->finishUpdate(geoMap);
734  FC_TIME_LOG(t,"update geometry history (" << geoHistory->size() << ", " << geoMap.size()<<')');
735 }
736 
737 void SketchObject::generateId(const Part::Geometry *geo)
738 {
739  if(!geoHistoryLevel) {
740  GeometryFacade::setId(geo, ++geoLastId);
741  geoMap[GeometryFacade::getId(geo)] = (long)Geometry.getSize();
742  return;
743  }
744 
745  if(!geoHistory)
746  updateGeoHistory();
747 
748  // Search geo history to see if the start point and end point belongs to
749  // some deleted geometries. Prefer matching both start and end point. If
750  // can't then try start and then end. Generate new id if none is found.
751  auto pstart = getPoint(geo,PointPos::start);
752  auto it = geoHistory->find(pstart,false);
753  auto pend = getPoint(geo,PointPos::end);
754  auto it2 = it;
755  if(pstart!=pend) {
756  it2 = geoHistory->find(pend,false);
757  if(it2 == geoHistory->end())
758  it2 = it;
759  }
760  long newId = -1;
761  std::vector<long> found;
762 
763  if(geoHistoryLevel<=1 && (it==geoHistory->end() || it2==it)) {
764  // level<=1 means we only reuse id if both start and end matches
765  newId = ++geoLastId;
766  goto END;
767  }
768 
769  if(it!=geoHistory->end()) {
770  for(long id : *it) {
771  if(geoMap.find(id)==geoMap.end()) {
772  if(it2 == it) {
773  newId = id;
774  goto END;
775  }
776  found.push_back(id);
777  }else
778  FC_TRACE("ignore " << id);
779  }
780  }
781  if(it2!=it) {
782  if(found.empty()) {
783  // no candidate exists
784  for(long id : *it2) {
785  if(geoMap.find(id)==geoMap.end()) {
786  newId = id;
787  goto END;
788  }
789  FC_TRACE("ignore " << id);
790  }
791  }else{
792  // already some candidate exists, search for matching of both
793  // points
794  for(long id : found) {
795  if(it2->find(id)!=it2->end()) {
796  newId = id;
797  goto END;
798  }
799  FC_TRACE("ignore " << id);
800  }
801  }
802  }
803  if(found.size()) {
804  FC_TRACE("found " << found.front());
805  newId = found.front();
806  }else
807  newId = ++geoLastId;
808 END:
809  GeometryFacade::setId(geo, newId);
810  geoMap[newId] = (long)Geometry.getSize();
811 }
812 
813 int SketchObject::setDatum(int ConstrId, double Datum)
814 {
815  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
816  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
817 
818  // set the changed value for the constraint
819  if (this->Constraints.hasInvalidGeometry())
820  return -6;
821  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
822  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(vals.size()))
823  return -1;
824  ConstraintType type = vals[ConstrId]->Type;
825  // for tangent, value==0 is autodecide, value==Pi/2 is external and value==-Pi/2 is internal
826  if (!vals[ConstrId]->isDimensional() && type != Tangent && type != Perpendicular)
827  return -1;
828 
829  if ((type == Radius || type == Diameter || type == Weight) && Datum <= 0)
830  return (Datum == 0) ? -5 : -4;
831 
832  if (type == Distance && Datum == 0)
833  return -5;
834 
835  // copy the list
836  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
837  double oldDatum = newVals[ConstrId]->getValue();
838  newVals[ConstrId] = newVals[ConstrId]->clone();
839  newVals[ConstrId]->setValue(Datum);
840 
841  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
842 
843  int err = solve();
844 
845  if (err)
846  this->Constraints.getValues()[ConstrId]->setValue(oldDatum);// newVals is a shell now
847 
848  return err;
849 }

851 int SketchObject::setDriving(int ConstrId, bool isdriving)
852 {
853  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
854  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
855 
856  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
857 
858  int ret = testDrivingChange(ConstrId, isdriving);
859 
860  if (ret < 0)
861  return ret;
862 
863  // copy the list
864  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
865  newVals[ConstrId] = newVals[ConstrId]->clone();
866  newVals[ConstrId]->isDriving = isdriving;
867 
868  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
869 
870  if (!isdriving)
871  setExpression(Constraints.createPath(ConstrId), std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>());
872 
873  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
874  if (noRecomputes)
875  solve();
876 
877  return 0;
878 }

880 int SketchObject::getDriving(int ConstrId, bool& isdriving)
881 {
882  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
883 
884  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(vals.size()))
885  return -1;
886 
887  if (!vals[ConstrId]->isDimensional())
888  return -1;
889 
890  isdriving = vals[ConstrId]->isDriving;
891  return 0;
892 }
893 
894 int SketchObject::testDrivingChange(int ConstrId, bool isdriving)
895 {
896  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
897 
898  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(vals.size()))
899  return -1;
900 
901  if (!vals[ConstrId]->isDimensional())
902  return -2;
903 
904  if (!(vals[ConstrId]->First >= 0 || vals[ConstrId]->Second >= 0 || vals[ConstrId]->Third >= 0)
905  && isdriving) {
906  // a constraint that does not have at least one element as not-external-geometry can never
907  // be driving.
908  return -3;
909  }
910 
911  return 0;
912 }

1046 int SketchObject::setDatumsDriving(bool isdriving)
1047 {
1048  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1049  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1050 
1051  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
1052  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
1053 
1054  for (size_t i = 0; i < newVals.size(); i++) {
1055  if (!testDrivingChange(i, isdriving)) {
1056  newVals[i] = newVals[i]->clone();
1057  newVals[i]->isDriving = isdriving;
1058  }
1059  }
1060 
1061  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1062 
1063  // newVals is a shell now
1064  const std::vector<Constraint*>& uvals = this->Constraints.getValues();
1065 
1066  for (size_t i = 0; i < uvals.size(); i++) {
1067  if (!isdriving && uvals[i]->isDimensional())
1068  setExpression(Constraints.createPath(i), std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>());
1069  }
1070 
1071  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
1072  if (noRecomputes)
1073  solve();
1074 
1075  return 0;
1076 }

1078 int SketchObject::moveDatumsToEnd()
1079 {
1080  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1081  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1082 
1083  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
1084 
1085  std::vector<Constraint*> copy(vals);
1086  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals.size());
1087 
1088  int addindex = copy.size() - 1;
1089 
1090  // add the dimensionals at the end
1091  for (int i = copy.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1092  if (copy[i]->isDimensional()) {
1093  newVals[addindex] = copy[i];
1094  addindex--;
1095  }
1096  }
1097 
1098  // add the non-dimensionals
1099  for (int i = copy.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1100  if (!copy[i]->isDimensional()) {
1101  newVals[addindex] = copy[i];
1102  addindex--;
1103  }
1104  }
1105 
1106  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1107 
1108  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
1109  if (noRecomputes)
1110  solve();
1111 
1112  return 0;
1113 }

1115 void SketchObject::reverseAngleConstraintToSupplementary(Constraint* constr, int constNum)
1116 {
1117  std::swap(constr->First, constr->Second);
1118  std::swap(constr->FirstPos, constr->SecondPos);
1119  if (constr->FirstPos == constr->SecondPos) {
1120  constr->FirstPos = (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
1121  }
1122  else {
1123  constr->SecondPos = (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
1124  }
1125 
1126  // Edit the expression if any, else modify constraint value directly
1127  if (constraintHasExpression(constNum)) {
1128  std::string expression = getConstraintExpression(constNum);
1129  setConstraintExpression(constNum, reverseAngleConstraintExpression(expression));
1130  }
1131  else {
1132  double actAngle = constr->getValue();
1133  constr->setValue(M_PI - actAngle);
1134  }
1135 }
1136 
1137 void SketchObject::inverseAngleConstraint(Constraint* constr)
1138 {
1139  constr->FirstPos = (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
1140  constr->SecondPos = (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
1141 }

1148  return true;

1165 void SketchObject::setConstraintExpression(int constNum, const std::string& newExpression)
1166 {
1167  App::ObjectIdentifier path = Constraints.createPath(constNum);
1168  auto info = getExpression(path);
1169  if (info.expression) {
1170  try {
1171  std::shared_ptr<App::Expression> expr(App::Expression::parse(this, newExpression));
1172  setExpression(path, expr);
1173  }
1174  catch (const Base::Exception&) {
1175  Base::Console().Error("Failed to set constraint expression.");
1176  }
1177  }
1178 }

1180 std::string SketchObject::reverseAngleConstraintExpression(std::string expression)
1181 {
1182  // Check if expression contains units (Â°, deg, rad)
1183  if (expression.find("Â°") != std::string::npos
1184  || expression.find("deg") != std::string::npos
1185  || expression.find("rad") != std::string::npos) {
1186  if (expression.substr(0, 9) == "180 Â° - ") {
1187  expression = expression.substr(9, expression.size() - 9);
1188  }
1189  else {
1190  expression = "180 Â° - (" + expression + ")";
1191  }
1192  }
1193  else {
1194  if (expression.substr(0, 6) == "180 - ") {
1195  expression = expression.substr(6, expression.size() - 6);
1196  }
1197  else {
1198  expression = "180 - (" + expression + ")";
1199  }
1200  }
1201  return expression;
1202 }

1231 int SketchObject::setVirtualSpace(std::vector<int> constrIds, bool isinvirtualspace)
1232 {
1233  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1234  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1235 
1236  if (constrIds.empty())
1237  return 0;
1238 
1239  std::sort(constrIds.begin(), constrIds.end());
1240 
1241  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
1242 
1243  if (constrIds.front() < 0 || constrIds.back() >= int(vals.size()))
1244  return -1;
1245 
1246  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
1247 
1248  for (auto cid : constrIds) {
1249  // clone the changed Constraint
1250  if (vals[cid]->isInVirtualSpace != isinvirtualspace) {
1251  Constraint* constNew = vals[cid]->clone();
1252  constNew->isInVirtualSpace = isinvirtualspace;
1253  newVals[cid] = constNew;
1254  }
1255  }
1256 
1257  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1258 
1259  // Solver didn't actually update, but we need this to inform view provider
1260  // to redraw
1261  signalSolverUpdate();
1262 
1263  return 0;
1264 }

1305 
1306 int SketchObject::setUpSketch()
1307 {
1308  lastDoF = solvedSketch.setUpSketch(
1309  getCompleteGeometry(), Constraints.getValues(), getExternalGeometryCount());
1310 
1311  retrieveSolverDiagnostics();
1312 
1313  if (lastHasRedundancies || lastDoF < 0 || lastHasConflict || lastHasMalformedConstraints
1314  || lastHasPartialRedundancies)
1315  Constraints.touch();
1316 
1317  return lastDoF;
1318 }
1319 
1320 int SketchObject::diagnoseAdditionalConstraints(
1321  std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*> additionalconstraints)
1322 {
1323  auto objectconstraints = Constraints.getValues();
1324 
1325  std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*> allconstraints;
1326  allconstraints.reserve(objectconstraints.size() + additionalconstraints.size());
1327 
1328  std::copy(objectconstraints.begin(), objectconstraints.end(), back_inserter(allconstraints));
1329  std::copy(
1330  additionalconstraints.begin(), additionalconstraints.end(), back_inserter(allconstraints));
1331 
1332  lastDoF =
1333  solvedSketch.setUpSketch(getCompleteGeometry(), allconstraints, getExternalGeometryCount());
1334 
1335  retrieveSolverDiagnostics();
1336 
1337  return lastDoF;
1338 }
1339 
1340 int SketchObject::moveGeometries(std::vector<GeoElementId> geoEltIds, const Base::Vector3d& toPoint, bool relative,
1341  bool updateGeoBeforeMoving)
1342 {
1343 
1344  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1345  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1346 
1347  // if we are moving a point at SketchObject level, we need to start from a solved sketch
1348  // if we have conflicts we can forget about moving. However, there is the possibility that we
1349  // need to do programmatically moves of new geometry that has not been solved yet and that
1350  // because they were programmatically generated won't generate a conflict. This is the case of
1351  // Fillet for example. This is why exceptionally, it may be required to update the sketch
1352  // geometry to that of of SketchObject upon moving. => use updateGeometry parameter = true then
1353 
1354 
1355  if (updateGeoBeforeMoving || solverNeedsUpdate) {
1356  lastDoF = solvedSketch.setUpSketch(
1357  getCompleteGeometry(), Constraints.getValues(), getExternalGeometryCount());
1358 
1359  retrieveSolverDiagnostics();
1360 
1361  solverNeedsUpdate = false;
1362  }
1363 
1364  if (lastDoF < 0)// over-constrained sketch
1365  return -1;
1366  if (lastHasConflict)// conflicting constraints
1367  return -1;
1368 
1369  // move the point and solve
1370  lastSolverStatus = solvedSketch.moveGeometries(geoEltIds, toPoint, relative);
1371 
1372  // moving the point can not result in a conflict that we did not have
1373  // or a redundancy that we did not have before, or a change of DoF
1374 
1375  if (lastSolverStatus == 0) {
1376  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geomlist = solvedSketch.extractGeometry();
1377  Geometry.setValues(geomlist);
1378  // Constraints.acceptGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
1379  for (auto* geo : geomlist) {
1380  if (geo){
1381  delete geo;
1382  }
1383  }
1384  }
1385 
1386  solvedSketch.resetInitMove();// reset solver point moving mechanism
1387 
1388  return lastSolverStatus;
1389 }
1390 
1391 int SketchObject::moveGeometry(int geoId, PointPos pos, const Base::Vector3d& toPoint, bool relative,
1392  bool updateGeoBeforeMoving)
1393 {
1394  std::vector<GeoElementId> geoEltIds = { GeoElementId(geoId, pos) };
1395  return moveGeometries(geoEltIds, toPoint, relative, updateGeoBeforeMoving);
1396 }

1531 
1532 Base::Vector3d SketchObject::getPoint(const Part::Geometry *geo, PointPos PosId)
1533 {
1534  if (geo->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
1535  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomPoint>(static_cast<const Part::GeomPoint*>(geo), PosId);
1536  }
1537  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
1538  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomLineSegment>(static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo), PosId);
1539  }
1540  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
1541  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomCircle>(static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geo), PosId);
1542  }
1543  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
1544  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomEllipse>(static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geo), PosId);
1545  }
1546  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
1547  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>(static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geo), PosId);
1548  }
1549  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
1550  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>(static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geo), PosId);
1551  }
1552  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
1553  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>(static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geo), PosId);
1554  }
1555  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
1556  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>(static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geo), PosId);
1557  }
1558  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
1559  return getPointForGeometry<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>(static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo), PosId);
1560  }
1561  return Base::Vector3d();
1562 }
1563 
1564 Base::Vector3d SketchObject::getPoint(int GeoId, PointPos PosId) const
1565 {
1566  if (!(GeoId == H_Axis || GeoId == V_Axis
1567  || (GeoId <= getHighestCurveIndex() && GeoId >= -getExternalGeometryCount())))
1568  throw Base::ValueError("SketchObject::getPoint. Invalid GeoId was supplied.");
1569  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
1570  return getPoint(geo,PosId);
1571 }

1573 int SketchObject::getAxisCount() const
1574 {
1575  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1576 
1577  int count = 0;
1578  for (const auto& geo : vals) {
1579  if (geo && GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo)
1580  && geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
1581  count++;
1582  }
1583  }
1584 
1585  return count;
1586 }
1587 
1588 Base::Axis SketchObject::getAxis(int axId) const
1589 {
1590  if (axId == H_Axis || axId == V_Axis || axId == N_Axis)
1591  return Part::Part2DObject::getAxis(axId);
1592 
1593  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1594  int count = 0;
1595  for (const auto& geo : vals) {
1596  if (geo && GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo)
1597  && geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
1598  if (count == axId) {
1599  Part::GeomLineSegment* lineSeg = static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo);
1600  Base::Vector3d start = lineSeg->getStartPoint();
1601  Base::Vector3d end = lineSeg->getEndPoint();
1602  return Base::Axis(start, end - start);
1603  }
1604  count++;
1605  }
1606  }
1607 
1608  return Base::Axis();
1609 }

1611 void SketchObject::acceptGeometry()
1612 {
1613  Constraints.acceptGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
1614  rebuildVertexIndex();
1615  signalElementsChanged();
1616 }
1617 
1618 bool SketchObject::isSupportedGeometry(const Part::Geometry* geo) const
1619 {
1620  if (geo->is<Part::GeomPoint>()
1621  || geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>()
1622  || geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()
1623  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()
1624  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()
1625  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()
1626  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()
1627  || geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()
1628  || geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
1629  return true;
1630  }
1631  if (geo->is<Part::GeomTrimmedCurve>()) {
1632  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) trim = Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve)::DownCast(geo->handle());
1633  Handle(Geom_Circle) circle = Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast(trim->BasisCurve());
1634  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) ellipse = Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(trim->BasisCurve());
1635  if (!circle.IsNull() || !ellipse.IsNull()) {
1636  return true;
1637  }
1638  }
1639  return false;
1640 }
1641 
1642 std::vector<Part::Geometry*>
1643 SketchObject::supportedGeometry(const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& geoList) const
1644 {
1645  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> supportedGeoList;
1646  supportedGeoList.reserve(geoList.size());
1647  // read-in geometry that the sketcher cannot handle
1648  for (const auto& geo : geoList) {
1649  if (isSupportedGeometry(geo)) {
1650  supportedGeoList.push_back(geo);
1651  }
1652  }
1653 
1654  return supportedGeoList;
1655 }
1656 
1657 int SketchObject::addGeometry(const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& geoList,
1658  bool construction /*=false*/)
1659 {
1660  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1661  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1662 
1663  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1664 
1665  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
1666  newVals.reserve(newVals.size() + geoList.size());
1667  for (auto& v : geoList) {
1668  Part::Geometry* copy = v->copy();
1669  generateId(copy);
1670 
1671  if (construction) {
1672  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(copy, construction);
1673  }
1674 
1675  newVals.push_back(copy);
1676  }
1677 
1678  // On setting geometry the onChanged method will call acceptGeometry(), thereby updating
1679  // constraint geometry indices and rebuilding the vertex index
1680  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1681 
1682  return Geometry.getSize() - 1;
1683 }
1684 
1685 int SketchObject::addGeometry(const Part::Geometry* geo, bool construction /*=false*/)
1686 {
1687  // this copy has a new random tag (see copy() vs clone())
1688  auto geoNew = std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry>(geo->copy());
1689 
1690  return addGeometry(std::move(geoNew), construction);
1691 }
1692 
1693 int SketchObject::addGeometry(std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry> newgeo, bool construction /*=false*/)
1694 {
1695  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1696  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1697 
1698  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1699 
1700  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
1701 
1702  auto* geoNew = newgeo.release();
1703  generateId(geoNew);
1704 
1705  if (construction) {
1706  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(geoNew, construction);
1707  }
1708 
1709  newVals.push_back(geoNew);
1710 
1711  // On setting geometry the onChanged method will call acceptGeometry(), thereby updating
1712  // constraint geometry indices and rebuilding the vertex index
1713  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1714 
1715  return Geometry.getSize() - 1;
1716 }

1729  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()
1730  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()

1732  || geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>());

1734 
1735 int SketchObject::delGeometry(int GeoId, bool deleteinternalgeo)
1736 {
1737  if (GeoId < 0) {
1738  if(GeoId > GeoEnum::RefExt)
1739  return -1;
1740  return delExternal(-GeoId-1);
1741  }
1742 
1743  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1744  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1745 
1746  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1747  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId >= int(vals.size()))
1748  return -1;
1749 
1750  if (deleteinternalgeo && hasInternalGeometry(getGeometry(GeoId))) {
1751  // Only for supported types
1752  this->deleteUnusedInternalGeometry(GeoId, true);
1753  return 0;
1754  }
1755 
1756  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
1757  newVals.erase(newVals.begin() + GeoId);
1758 
1759  // Find coincident points to replace the points of the deleted geometry
1760  std::vector<int> GeoIdList;
1761  std::vector<PointPos> PosIdList;
1762  for (PointPos PosId : {PointPos::start, PointPos::end, PointPos::mid}) {
1763  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(GeoId, PosId, GeoIdList, PosIdList);
1764  if (GeoIdList.size() > 1) {
1765  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId, PosId, true /* only coincidence */);
1766  transferConstraints(GeoIdList[0], PosIdList[0], GeoIdList[1], PosIdList[1]);
1767  }
1768  }
1769 
1770  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
1771  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints;
1772  newConstraints.reserve(constraints.size());
1773  for (auto cstr : constraints) {
1774  if (cstr->First == GeoId || cstr->Second == GeoId || cstr->Third == GeoId)
1775  continue;
1776  if (cstr->First > GeoId || cstr->Second > GeoId || cstr->Third > GeoId) {
1777  cstr = cstr->clone();
1778  if (cstr->First > GeoId)
1779  cstr->First -= 1;
1780  if (cstr->Second > GeoId)
1781  cstr->Second -= 1;
1782  if (cstr->Third > GeoId)
1783  cstr->Third -= 1;
1784  }
1785  newConstraints.push_back(cstr);
1786  }
1787 
1788  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
1789  {
1790  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
1791  this->Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
1792  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
1793  }
1794 
1795  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
1796  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
1797  Geometry.touch();
1798 
1799  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
1800  if (noRecomputes)
1801  solve();
1802 
1803  return 0;
1804 }
1805 
1806 int SketchObject::delGeometries(const std::vector<int>& GeoIds)
1807 {
1808  std::vector<int> sGeoIds;
1809  std::vector<int> negativeGeoIds;
1810 
1811  // Separate GeoIds into negative (external) and non-negative GeoIds
1812  for (int geoId : GeoIds) {
1813  if (geoId < 0 && geoId <= GeoEnum::RefExt) {
1814  negativeGeoIds.push_back(geoId);
1815  }
1816  else if (geoId >= 0){
1817  sGeoIds.push_back(geoId);
1818  }
1819  }
1820 
1821  // Handle negative GeoIds by calling delExternal
1822  if (!negativeGeoIds.empty()) {
1823  int result = delExternal(negativeGeoIds);
1824  if (result != 0) {
1825  return result; // Return if deletion of external geometries failed
1826  }
1827  }
1828 
1829  // Proceed with non-negative GeoIds
1830  if (sGeoIds.empty()) {
1831  return 0; // No positive GeoIds to delete
1832  }
1833 
1834  // if a GeoId has internal geometry, it must delete internal geometries too
1835  for (auto c : Constraints.getValues()) {
1836  if (c->Type == InternalAlignment) {
1837  auto pos = std::find(sGeoIds.begin(), sGeoIds.end(), c->Second);
1838 
1839  if (pos != sGeoIds.end()) {
1840  sGeoIds.push_back(c->First);
1841  }
1842  }
1843  }
1844 
1845  std::sort(sGeoIds.begin(), sGeoIds.end());
1846  // eliminate duplicates
1847  auto newend = std::unique(sGeoIds.begin(), sGeoIds.end());
1848  sGeoIds.resize(std::distance(sGeoIds.begin(), newend));
1849 
1850  return delGeometriesExclusiveList(sGeoIds);
1851 }
1852 
1853 int SketchObject::delGeometriesExclusiveList(const std::vector<int>& GeoIds)
1854 {
1855  std::vector<int> sGeoIds(GeoIds);
1856 
1857  std::sort(sGeoIds.begin(), sGeoIds.end());
1858  if (sGeoIds.empty())
1859  return 0;
1860 
1861  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1862  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1863 
1864  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1865  if (sGeoIds.front() < 0 || sGeoIds.back() >= int(vals.size()))
1866  return -1;
1867 
1868 
1869  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
1870  for (auto it = sGeoIds.rbegin(); it != sGeoIds.rend(); ++it) {
1871  int GeoId = *it;
1872  newVals.erase(newVals.begin() + GeoId);
1873 
1874  // Find coincident points to replace the points of the deleted geometry
1875  std::vector<int> GeoIdList;
1876  std::vector<PointPos> PosIdList;
1877  for (PointPos PosId : {PointPos::start, PointPos::end, PointPos::mid}) {
1878  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(GeoId, PosId, GeoIdList, PosIdList);
1879  if (GeoIdList.size() > 1) {
1880  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId, PosId, true /* only coincidence */);
1881  transferConstraints(GeoIdList[0], PosIdList[0], GeoIdList[1], PosIdList[1]);
1882  }
1883  // loop through [start, end, mid]
1884  PosId = (PosId == PointPos::start) ? PointPos::end : PointPos::mid;
1885  }
1886  }
1887 
1888  // Copy the original constraints
1889  std::vector<Constraint*> constraints;
1890  for (const auto ptr : this->Constraints.getValues())
1891  constraints.push_back(ptr->clone());
1892  std::vector<Constraint*> filteredConstraints(0);
1893  for (auto itGeo = sGeoIds.rbegin(); itGeo != sGeoIds.rend(); ++itGeo) {
1894  int GeoId = *itGeo;
1895  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constraints.begin();
1896  it != constraints.end();
1897  ++it) {
1898 
1899  Constraint* copiedConstr(*it);
1900  if ((*it)->First != GeoId && (*it)->Second != GeoId && (*it)->Third != GeoId) {
1901  if (copiedConstr->First > GeoId)
1902  copiedConstr->First -= 1;
1903  if (copiedConstr->Second > GeoId)
1904  copiedConstr->Second -= 1;
1905  if (copiedConstr->Third > GeoId)
1906  copiedConstr->Third -= 1;
1907  filteredConstraints.push_back(copiedConstr);
1908  }
1909  else {
1910  delete copiedConstr;
1911  }
1912  }
1913 
1914  constraints = filteredConstraints;
1915  filteredConstraints.clear();
1916  }
1917 
1918  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
1919  {
1920  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
1921  this->Geometry.setValues(newVals);
1922  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(constraints));
1923  }
1924  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
1925  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
1926  Geometry.touch();
1927 
1928  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
1929  if (noRecomputes)
1930  solve();
1931 
1932  return 0;
1933 }

1935 int SketchObject::deleteAllGeometry()

1946  this->Geometry.setValues(newVals);
1947  this->Constraints.setValues(newConstraints);

1949  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
1950  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
1951  Geometry.touch();
1952 
1953  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
1954  if (noRecomputes)
1955  solve();
1956 
1957  return 0;

1976 int SketchObject::toggleConstruction(int GeoId)
1977 {
1978  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
1979  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
1980 
1981  if (GeoId >= 0) {
1982  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
1983  if (GeoId >= int(vals.size())) {
1984  return -1;
1985  }
1986 
1987  if (getGeometryFacade(GeoId)->isInternalAligned()) {
1988  return -1;
1989  }
1990 
1991  // While it may seem that there is not a need to trigger an update at this time, because the
1992  // solver has its own copy of the geometry, and updateColors of the viewprovider may be
1993  // triggered by the clearselection of the UI command, this won't update the elements widget, in
1994  // the accumulative of actions it is judged that it is worth to trigger an update here.
1995 
1996  auto gft = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[GeoId]);
1997  gft->setConstruction(!gft->getConstruction());
1998  this->Geometry.touch();
1999  }
2000  else {
2001  if (GeoId > GeoEnum::RefExt) {
2002  return -1;
2003  }
2004 
2005  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& extGeos = getExternalGeometry();
2006  auto geo = extGeos[-GeoId - 1];
2007  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
2008  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining, !egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining));
2009  this->ExternalGeo.touch();
2010  }
2011 
2012  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
2013  signalSolverUpdate(); // FIXME: In theory this is totally redundant, but now seems required
2014  // for UI to update.
2015  return 0;
2016 }
2017 
2018 int SketchObject::setConstruction(int GeoId, bool on)
2019 {
2020  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2021  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2022 
2023  Part::PropertyGeometryList *prop;
2024  int idx;
2025  if (GeoId >= 0) {
2026  prop = &Geometry;
2027  if (GeoId < Geometry.getSize())
2028  idx = GeoId;
2029  else
2030  return -1;
2031  }else if (GeoId <= GeoEnum::RefExt && -GeoId-1 < ExternalGeo.getSize()) {
2032  prop = &ExternalGeo;
2033  idx = -GeoId-1;
2034  }else
2035  return -1;
2036 
2037  // While it may seem that there is not a need to trigger an update at this time, because the
2038  // solver has its own copy of the geometry, and updateColors of the viewprovider may be
2039  // triggered by the clearselection of the UI command, this won't update the elements widget, in
2040  // the accumulative of actions it is judged that it is worth to trigger an update here.
2041 
2042  std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry> geo(prop->getValues()[idx]->clone());
2043  if(prop == &Geometry)
2044  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(geo.get(), on);
2045  else {
2046  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo.get());
2047  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining, on);
2048  }
2049 
2050  prop->set1Value(idx,std::move(geo));
2051  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
2052  return 0;
2053 }
2054 
2055 int SketchObject::toggleExternalGeometryFlag(const std::vector<int> &geoIds,
2056  const std::vector<ExternalGeometryExtension::Flag> &flags)
2057 {
2058  if (flags.empty())
2059  return 0;
2060  auto flag = flags.front();
2061 
2062  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true); // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2063 
2064  bool update = false;
2065  bool touched = false;
2066  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
2067  std::set<int> idSet(geoIds.begin(),geoIds.end());
2068  for(auto geoId : geoIds) {
2069  if(geoId > GeoEnum::RefExt || -geoId-1>=ExternalGeo.getSize())
2070  continue;
2071  if(!idSet.count(geoId))
2072  continue;
2073  idSet.erase(geoId);
2074  const int idx = -geoId - 1;
2075  auto& geo = geos[idx];
2076  const auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
2077  const bool value = !egf->testFlag(flag);
2078  if (!egf->getRef().empty()) {
2079  for (auto relatedGeoId : getRelatedGeometry(geoId)) {
2080  if (relatedGeoId == geoId) {
2081  continue;
2082  }
2083  int relatedIndex = -relatedGeoId - 1;
2084  auto& relatedGeometry = geos[relatedIndex];
2085  relatedGeometry = relatedGeometry->clone();
2086  auto relatedFacade = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(relatedGeometry);
2087  relatedFacade->setFlag(flag, value);
2088  for (size_t i = 1; i < flags.size(); ++i) {
2089  relatedFacade->setFlag(flags[i], value);
2090  }
2091  idSet.erase(relatedGeoId);
2092  }
2093  }
2094  geo = geo->clone();
2095  egf->setGeometry(geo);
2096  egf->setFlag(flag, value);
2097  for (size_t i=1; i<flags.size(); ++i)
2098  egf->setFlag(flags[i], value);
2099  if (value || flag != ExternalGeometryExtension::Frozen)
2100  update = true;
2101  touched = true;
2102  }
2103 
2104  if(!touched)
2105  return -1;
2106  ExternalGeo.setValues(geos);
2107  if (update)
2108  rebuildExternalGeometry();
2109  return 0;
2110 }

2112 void SketchObject::addGeometryState(const Constraint* cstr) const
2113 {
2114  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
2115 
2116  Sketcher::InternalType::InternalType constraintInternalAlignment = InternalType::None;
2117  bool constraintBlockedState = false;
2118 
2119  if (getInternalTypeState(cstr, constraintInternalAlignment)) {
2120  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[cstr->First]);
2121  gf->setInternalType(constraintInternalAlignment);
2122  }
2123  else if (getBlockedState(cstr, constraintBlockedState)) {
2124  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[cstr->First]);
2125  gf->setBlocked(constraintBlockedState);
2126  }
2127 }

2129 void SketchObject::removeGeometryState(const Constraint* cstr) const
2130 {
2131  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
2132 
2133  // Assign correct Internal Geometry Type (see SketchGeometryExtension)
2134  if (cstr->Type == InternalAlignment) {
2135  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[cstr->First]);
2136  gf->setInternalType(InternalType::None);
2137  }
2138 
2139  // Assign Blocked geometry mode (see SketchGeometryExtension)
2140  if (cstr->Type == Block) {
2141  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[cstr->First]);
2142  gf->setBlocked(false);
2143  }
2144 }

2146 // ConstraintList is used only to make copies.
2147 int SketchObject::addConstraints(const std::vector<Constraint*>& ConstraintList)
2148 {
2149  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2150  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2151 
2152  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2153 
2154  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
2155  newVals.insert(newVals.end(), ConstraintList.begin(), ConstraintList.end());
2156  for (std::size_t i = newVals.size() - ConstraintList.size(); i < newVals.size(); i++) {
2157  Constraint* cnew = newVals[i]->clone();
2158  newVals[i] = cnew;
2159 
2160  if (cnew->Type == Tangent || cnew->Type == Perpendicular) {
2161  AutoLockTangencyAndPerpty(cnew);
2162  }
2163 
2164  addGeometryState(cnew);
2165  }
2166 
2167  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2168 
2169  return this->Constraints.getSize() - 1;
2170 }

2172 int SketchObject::addCopyOfConstraints(const SketchObject& orig)
2173 {
2174  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2175  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2176 
2177  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2178 
2179  const std::vector<Constraint*>& origvals = orig.Constraints.getValues();
2180 
2181  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
2182 
2183  newVals.reserve(vals.size() + origvals.size());
2184 
2185  for (auto& v : origvals)
2186  newVals.push_back(v->copy());
2187 
2188  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2189 
2190  auto& uvals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2191 
2192  std::size_t uvalssize = uvals.size();
2193 
2194  for (std::size_t i = uvalssize, j = 0; i < uvals.size(); i++, j++) {
2195  if (uvals[i]->isDriving && uvals[i]->isDimensional()) {
2196 
2197  App::ObjectIdentifier spath = orig.Constraints.createPath(j);
2198 
2199  App::PropertyExpressionEngine::ExpressionInfo expr_info = orig.getExpression(spath);
2200 
2201  if (expr_info.expression) {// if there is an expression on the source dimensional
2202  App::ObjectIdentifier dpath = this->Constraints.createPath(i);
2203  setExpression(dpath,
2204  std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>(expr_info.expression->copy()));
2205  }
2206  }
2207  }
2208 
2209  if (noRecomputes) // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
2210  solve();
2211 
2212  return this->Constraints.getSize() - 1;
2213 }

2222 int SketchObject::addConstraint(std::unique_ptr<Constraint> constraint)
2223 {

2225  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2226 
2227  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2228

2230

2232 
2233  if (constNew->Type == Tangent || constNew->Type == Perpendicular)
2234  AutoLockTangencyAndPerpty(constNew);
2235

2237

2239 
2240  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2241

2245 int SketchObject::delConstraint(int ConstrId)
2246 {
2247  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2248  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2249 
2250  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2251  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(vals.size()))
2252  return -1;
2253 
2254  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
2255  auto ctriter = newVals.begin() + ConstrId;
2256  removeGeometryState(*ctriter);
2257  newVals.erase(ctriter);
2258  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2259 
2260  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
2261  if (noRecomputes)
2262  solve();
2263 
2264  return 0;
2265 }

2267 int SketchObject::delConstraints(std::vector<int> ConstrIds, bool updategeometry)
2268 {
2269  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2270  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2271  if (ConstrIds.empty())
2272  return 0;
2273 
2274  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2275 
2276  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
2277 
2278  std::sort(ConstrIds.begin(), ConstrIds.end());
2279 
2280  if (ConstrIds.front() < 0 || ConstrIds.back() >= int(vals.size()))
2281  return -1;
2282 
2283  for (auto rit = ConstrIds.rbegin(); rit != ConstrIds.rend(); rit++) {
2284  auto ctriter = newVals.begin() + *rit;
2285  removeGeometryState(*ctriter);
2286  newVals.erase(ctriter);
2287  }
2288 
2289  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2290 
2291  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
2292  if (noRecomputes)
2293  solve(updategeometry);
2294 
2295  return 0;
2296 }
