2298 int SketchObject::delConstraintOnPoint(int VertexId, bool onlyCoincident)
2299 {
2300  int GeoId;
2301  PointPos PosId;
2302  if (VertexId == GeoEnum::RtPnt) {// RootPoint
2303  GeoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::RtPnt;
2304  PosId = PointPos::start;
2305  }
2306  else
2307  getGeoVertexIndex(VertexId, GeoId, PosId);
2308 
2309  return delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId, PosId, onlyCoincident);
2310 }
2311 
2312 int SketchObject::delConstraintOnPoint(int GeoId, PointPos PosId, bool onlyCoincident)
2313 {
2314  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2315  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2316 
2317  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2318 
2319  // check if constraints can be redirected to some other point
2320  int replaceGeoId = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
2321  PointPos replacePosId = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
2322  if (!onlyCoincident) {
2323  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end(); ++it) {
2324  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Coincident) {
2325  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId) {
2326  replaceGeoId = (*it)->Second;
2327  replacePosId = (*it)->SecondPos;
2328  break;
2329  }
2330  else if ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId) {
2331  replaceGeoId = (*it)->First;
2332  replacePosId = (*it)->FirstPos;
2333  break;
2334  }
2335  }
2336  }
2337  }
2338 
2339  // remove or redirect any constraints associated with the given point
2340  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(0);
2341  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end(); ++it) {
2342  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Coincident) {
2343  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId) {
2344  // redirect this constraint
2345  if (replaceGeoId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef
2346  && (replaceGeoId != (*it)->Second || replacePosId != (*it)->SecondPos)) {
2347  (*it)->First = replaceGeoId;
2348  (*it)->FirstPos = replacePosId;
2349  }
2350  else
2351  continue;// skip this constraint
2352  }
2353  else if ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId) {
2354  // redirect this constraint
2355  if (replaceGeoId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef
2356  && (replaceGeoId != (*it)->First || replacePosId != (*it)->FirstPos)) {
2357  (*it)->Second = replaceGeoId;
2358  (*it)->SecondPos = replacePosId;
2359  }
2360  else
2361  continue;// skip this constraint
2362  }
2363  }
2364  else if (!onlyCoincident) {
2365  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Distance || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceX
2366  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceY) {
2367  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PointPos::none
2368  && (PosId == PointPos::start || PosId == PointPos::end)) {
2369  // remove the constraint even if it is not directly associated
2370  // with the given point
2371  continue;// skip this constraint
2372  }
2373  else if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId) {
2374  if (replaceGeoId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {// redirect this constraint
2375  (*it)->First = replaceGeoId;
2376  (*it)->FirstPos = replacePosId;
2377  }
2378  else
2379  continue;// skip this constraint
2380  }
2381  else if ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId) {
2382  if (replaceGeoId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {// redirect this constraint
2383  (*it)->Second = replaceGeoId;
2384  (*it)->SecondPos = replacePosId;
2385  }
2386  else
2387  continue;// skip this constraint
2388  }
2389  }
2390  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::PointOnObject) {
2391  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId) {
2392  if (replaceGeoId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {// redirect this constraint
2393  (*it)->First = replaceGeoId;
2394  (*it)->FirstPos = replacePosId;
2395  }
2396  else
2397  continue;// skip this constraint
2398  }
2399  }
2400  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Tangent || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Perpendicular) {
2401  if (((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId)
2402  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId)) {
2403  // we could keep the tangency constraint by converting it
2404  // to a simple one but it is not really worth
2405  continue;// skip this constraint
2406  }
2407  }
2408  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Symmetric) {
2409  if (((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId)
2410  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId)) {
2411  continue;// skip this constraint
2412  }
2413  }
2414  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Vertical || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Horizontal) {
2415  if (((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId)
2416  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId)) {
2417  continue;// skip this constraint
2418  }
2419  }
2420  }
2421  newVals.push_back(*it);
2422  }
2423  if (newVals.size() < vals.size()) {
2424  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2425 
2426  return 0;
2427  }
2428 
2429  return -1;// no such constraint
2430 }
2431 
2432 void SketchObject::transferFilletConstraints(int geoId1, PointPos posId1, int geoId2,
2433  PointPos posId2)
2434 {
2435  // If the lines don't intersect, there's no original corner to work with so
2436  // don't try to transfer the constraints. But we should delete line length and equal
2437  // constraints and constraints on the affected endpoints because they're about
2438  // to move unpredictably.
2439  if (!arePointsCoincident(geoId1, posId1, geoId2, posId2)) {
2440  // Delete constraints on the endpoints
2441  delConstraintOnPoint(geoId1, posId1, false);
2442  delConstraintOnPoint(geoId2, posId2, false);
2443 
2444  // Delete line length and equal constraints
2445  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
2446  std::vector<int> deleteme;
2447  for (int i = 0; i < int(constraints.size()); i++) {
2448  const Constraint* c = constraints[i];
2449  if (c->Type == Sketcher::Distance || c->Type == Sketcher::Equal) {
2450  bool line1 = c->First == geoId1 && c->FirstPos == PointPos::none;
2451  bool line2 = c->First == geoId2 && c->FirstPos == PointPos::none;
2452  if (line1 || line2) {
2453  deleteme.push_back(i);
2454  }
2455  }
2456  }
2457  delConstraints(deleteme, false);
2458  return;
2459  }
2460 
2461  // If the lines aren't straight, don't try to transfer the constraints.
2462  // TODO: Add support for curved lines.
2463  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = getGeometry(geoId1);
2464  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = getGeometry(geoId2);
2465  if (geo1->getTypeId() != Part::GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId()
2466  || geo2->getTypeId() != Part::GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId()) {
2467  delConstraintOnPoint(geoId1, posId1, false);
2468  delConstraintOnPoint(geoId2, posId2, false);
2469  return;
2470  }
2471 
2472  // Add a vertex to preserve the original intersection of the filleted lines
2473  Part::GeomPoint* originalCorner = new Part::GeomPoint(getPoint(geoId1, posId1));
2474  int originalCornerId = addGeometry(originalCorner, true);
2475  delete originalCorner;
2476 
2477  // Constrain the vertex to the two lines
2478  Sketcher::Constraint* cornerToLine1 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
2479  cornerToLine1->Type = Sketcher::PointOnObject;
2480  cornerToLine1->First = originalCornerId;
2481  cornerToLine1->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2482  cornerToLine1->Second = geoId1;
2483  cornerToLine1->SecondPos = PointPos::none;
2484  addConstraint(cornerToLine1);
2485  delete cornerToLine1;
2486  Sketcher::Constraint* cornerToLine2 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
2487  cornerToLine2->Type = Sketcher::PointOnObject;
2488  cornerToLine2->First = originalCornerId;
2489  cornerToLine2->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2490  cornerToLine2->Second = geoId2;
2491  cornerToLine2->SecondPos = PointPos::none;
2492  addConstraint(cornerToLine2);
2493  delete cornerToLine2;
2494 
2495  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2496 
2497  // Loop through all the constraints and try to do reasonable things with the affected ones
2498  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints;
2499  for (auto c : this->Constraints.getValues()) {
2500  // Keep track of whether the affected lines and endpoints appear in this constraint
2501  bool point1First = c->First == geoId1 && c->FirstPos == posId1;
2502  bool point2First = c->First == geoId2 && c->FirstPos == posId2;
2503  bool point1Second = c->Second == geoId1 && c->SecondPos == posId1;
2504  bool point2Second = c->Second == geoId2 && c->SecondPos == posId2;
2505  bool point1Third = c->Third == geoId1 && c->ThirdPos == posId1;
2506  bool point2Third = c->Third == geoId2 && c->ThirdPos == posId2;
2507  bool line1First = c->First == geoId1 && c->FirstPos == PointPos::none;
2508  bool line2First = c->First == geoId2 && c->FirstPos == PointPos::none;
2509  bool line1Second = c->Second == geoId1 && c->SecondPos == PointPos::none;
2510  bool line2Second = c->Second == geoId2 && c->SecondPos == PointPos::none;
2511 
2512  if (c->Type == Sketcher::Coincident) {
2513  if ((point1First && point2Second) || (point2First && point1Second)) {
2514  // This is the constraint holding the two edges together that are about to be
2515  // filleted. This constraint goes away because the edges will touch the fillet
2516  // instead.
2517  continue;
2518  }
2519  if (point1First || point2First) {
2520  // Move the coincident constraint to the new corner point
2521  c->First = originalCornerId;
2522  c->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2523  }
2524  if (point1Second || point2Second) {
2525  // Move the coincident constraint to the new corner point
2526  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2527  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2528  }
2529  }
2530  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::Horizontal || c->Type == Sketcher::Vertical) {
2531  // Point-to-point horizontal or vertical constraint, move to new corner point
2532  if (point1First || point2First) {
2533  c->First = originalCornerId;
2534  c->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2535  }
2536  if (point1Second || point2Second) {
2537  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2538  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2539  }
2540  }
2541  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::Distance || c->Type == Sketcher::DistanceX
2542  || c->Type == Sketcher::DistanceY) {
2543  // Point-to-point distance constraint. Move it to the new corner point
2544  if (point1First || point2First) {
2545  c->First = originalCornerId;
2546  c->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2547  }
2548  if (point1Second || point2Second) {
2549  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2550  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2551  }
2552 
2553  // Distance constraint on the line itself. Change it to point-point between the far end
2554  // of the line and the new corner
2555  if (line1First) {
2556  c->FirstPos = (posId1 == PointPos::start) ? PointPos::end : PointPos::start;
2557  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2558  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2559  }
2560  if (line2First) {
2561  c->FirstPos = (posId2 == PointPos::start) ? PointPos::end : PointPos::start;
2562  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2563  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2564  }
2565  }
2566  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::PointOnObject) {
2567  // The corner to be filleted was touching some other object.
2568  if (point1First || point2First) {
2569  c->First = originalCornerId;
2570  c->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2571  }
2572  }
2573  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::Equal) {
2574  // Equal length constraints are dicey because the lines are getting shorter. Safer to
2575  // delete them and let the user notice the underconstraint.
2576  if (line1First || line2First || line1Second || line2Second) {
2577  continue;
2578  }
2579  }
2580  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::Symmetric) {
2581  // Symmetries should probably be preserved relative to the original corner
2582  if (point1First || point2First) {
2583  c->First = originalCornerId;
2584  c->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
2585  }
2586  else if (point1Second || point2Second) {
2587  c->Second = originalCornerId;
2588  c->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
2589  }
2590  else if (point1Third || point2Third) {
2591  c->Third = originalCornerId;
2592  c->ThirdPos = PointPos::start;
2593  }
2594  }
2595  else if (c->Type == Sketcher::SnellsLaw) {
2596  // Can't imagine any cases where you'd fillet a vertex going through a lens, so let's
2597  // delete to be safe.
2598  continue;
2599  }
2600  else if (point1First || point2First || point1Second || point2Second || point1Third
2601  || point2Third) {
2602  // Delete any other point-based constraints on the relevant points
2603  continue;
2604  }
2605 
2606  // Default: keep all other constraints
2607  newConstraints.push_back(c->clone());
2608  }
2609  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
2610 }
2611 
2612 int SketchObject::transferConstraints(int fromGeoId, PointPos fromPosId, int toGeoId,
2613  PointPos toPosId, bool doNotTransformTangencies)
2614 {
2615  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
2616  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
2617 
2618  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
2619  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);
2620  bool changed = false;
2621  for (int i = 0; i < int(newVals.size()); i++) {
2622  if (vals[i]->First == fromGeoId && vals[i]->FirstPos == fromPosId
2623  && !(vals[i]->Second == toGeoId && vals[i]->SecondPos == toPosId)
2624  && !(toGeoId < 0 && vals[i]->Second < 0)) {
2625 
2626  std::unique_ptr<Constraint> constNew(newVals[i]->clone());
2627  constNew->First = toGeoId;
2628  constNew->FirstPos = toPosId;
2629 
2630  // If not explicitly confirmed, nothing guarantees that a tangent can be freely
2631  // transferred to another coincident point, as the transfer destination edge most likely
2632  // won't be intended to be tangent. However, if it is an end to end point tangency, the
2633  // user expects it to be substituted by a coincidence constraint.
2634  if (vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Tangent || vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Perpendicular) {
2635  if (!doNotTransformTangencies) {
2636  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
2637  }
2638  }
2639  // With respect to angle constraints, if it is a DeepSOIC style angle constraint
2640  // (segment+segment+point), then no problem arises as the segments are PosId=none. In
2641  // this case there is no call to this function.
2642  //
2643  // However, other angle constraints are problematic because they are created on
2644  // segments, but internally operate on vertices, PosId=start Such constraint may not be
2645  // successfully transferred on deletion of the segments.
2646  else if (vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Angle) {
2647  continue;
2648  }
2649 
2650  Constraint* constPtr = constNew.release();
2651  newVals[i] = constPtr;
2652  changed = true;
2653  }
2654  else if (vals[i]->Second == fromGeoId && vals[i]->SecondPos == fromPosId
2655  && !(vals[i]->First == toGeoId && vals[i]->FirstPos == toPosId)
2656  && !(toGeoId < 0 && vals[i]->First < 0)) {
2657 
2658  std::unique_ptr<Constraint> constNew(newVals[i]->clone());
2659  constNew->Second = toGeoId;
2660  constNew->SecondPos = toPosId;
2661  // If not explicitly confirmed, nothing guarantees that a tangent can be freely
2662  // transferred to another coincident point, as the transfer destination edge most likely
2663  // won't be intended to be tangent. However, if it is an end to end point tangency, the
2664  // user expects it to be substituted by a coincidence constraint.
2665  if (vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Tangent || vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Perpendicular) {
2666  if (!doNotTransformTangencies) {
2667  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
2668  }
2669  }
2670  else if (vals[i]->Type == Sketcher::Angle) {
2671  continue;
2672  }
2673 
2674  Constraint* constPtr = constNew.release();
2675  newVals[i] = constPtr;
2676  changed = true;
2677  }
2678  }
2679 
2680  // assign the new values only if something has changed
2681  if (changed) {
2682  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
2683  }
2684  return 0;
2685 }
2686 
2687 int SketchObject::fillet(int GeoId, PointPos PosId, double radius, bool trim, bool createCorner, bool chamfer)
2688 {
2689  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
2690  return -1;
2691 
2692  // Find the other geometry Id associated with the coincident point
2693  std::vector<int> GeoIdList;
2694  std::vector<PointPos> PosIdList;
2695  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(GeoId, PosId, GeoIdList, PosIdList);
2696 
2697  // only coincident points between two (non-external) edges can be filleted
2698  if (GeoIdList.size() == 2 && GeoIdList[0] >= 0 && GeoIdList[1] >= 0) {
2699  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = getGeometry(GeoIdList[0]);
2700  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = getGeometry(GeoIdList[1]);
2701  if (geo1->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()
2702  && geo2->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
2703  auto* lineSeg1 = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo1);
2704  auto* lineSeg2 = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo2);
2705 
2706  Base::Vector3d midPnt1 = (lineSeg1->getStartPoint() + lineSeg1->getEndPoint()) / 2;
2707  Base::Vector3d midPnt2 = (lineSeg2->getStartPoint() + lineSeg2->getEndPoint()) / 2;
2708  return fillet(GeoIdList[0], GeoIdList[1], midPnt1, midPnt2, radius, trim, createCorner, chamfer);
2709  }
2710  }
2711 
2712  return -1;
2713 }
2714 
2715 int SketchObject::fillet(int GeoId1, int GeoId2, const Base::Vector3d& refPnt1,
2716  const Base::Vector3d& refPnt2, double radius, bool trim, bool createCorner, bool chamfer)
2717 {
2718  if (GeoId1 < 0 || GeoId1 > getHighestCurveIndex() || GeoId2 < 0 || GeoId2 > getHighestCurveIndex()) {
2719  return -1;
2720  }
2721 
2722  // If either of the two input lines are locked, don't try to trim since it won't work anyway
2723  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = getGeometry(GeoId1);
2724  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = getGeometry(GeoId2);
2725  if (trim && (GeometryFacade::getBlocked(geo1) || GeometryFacade::getBlocked(geo2))) {
2726  trim = false;
2727  }
2728 
2729  Base::Vector3d p1, p2;
2730  PointPos PosId1 = PointPos::none;
2731  PointPos PosId2 = PointPos::none;
2732  PointPos filletPosId1 = PointPos::none;
2733  PointPos filletPosId2 = PointPos::none;
2734  int filletId;
2735 
2736  if (geo1->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>() && geo2->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
2737  auto* lineSeg1 = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo1);
2738  auto* lineSeg2 = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo2);
2739 
2740  Base::Vector3d filletCenter;
2741  if (!Part::findFilletCenter(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, radius, refPnt1, refPnt2, filletCenter)) {
2742  return -1;
2743  }
2744  Base::Vector3d dir1 = lineSeg1->getEndPoint() - lineSeg1->getStartPoint();
2745  Base::Vector3d dir2 = lineSeg2->getEndPoint() - lineSeg2->getStartPoint();
2746 
2747  // the intersection point will and two distances will be necessary later for trimming the
2748  // lines
2749  Base::Vector3d intersection, dist1, dist2;
2750 
2751  // create arc from known parameters and lines
2752  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomArcOfCircle> arc(
2753  Part::createFilletGeometry(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, filletCenter, radius));
2754  if (!arc) {
2755  return -1;
2756  }
2757 
2758  // calculate intersection and distances before we invalidate lineSeg1 and lineSeg2
2759  if (!find2DLinesIntersection(lineSeg1, lineSeg2, intersection)) {
2760  return -1;
2761  }
2762 
2763  p1 = arc->getStartPoint(/*emulateCCW=*/true);
2764  p2 = arc->getEndPoint(/*emulateCCW=*/true);
2765 
2766  dist1.ProjectToLine(p1 - intersection, dir1);
2767  dist2.ProjectToLine(p1 - intersection, dir2);
2768  filletId = addGeometry(arc.get());
2769 
2770  if (trim) {
2771  PosId1 = (filletCenter - intersection) * dir1 > 0 ? PointPos::start : PointPos::end;
2772  PosId2 = (filletCenter - intersection) * dir2 > 0 ? PointPos::start : PointPos::end;
2773 
2774  if (createCorner) {
2775  transferFilletConstraints(GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2);
2776  }
2777  else {
2778  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId1, PosId1, false);
2779  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId2, PosId2, false);
2780  }
2781 
2782  if (dist1.Length() < dist2.Length()) {
2783  filletPosId1 = PointPos::start;
2784  filletPosId2 = PointPos::end;
2785  moveGeometry(GeoId1, PosId1, p1, false, true);
2786  moveGeometry(GeoId2, PosId2, p2, false, true);
2787  }
2788  else {
2789  filletPosId1 = PointPos::end;
2790  filletPosId2 = PointPos::start;
2791  moveGeometry(GeoId1, PosId1, p2, false, true);
2792  moveGeometry(GeoId2, PosId2, p1, false, true);
2793  }
2794 
2795  auto tangent1 = std::make_unique<Sketcher::Constraint>();
2796  auto tangent2 = std::make_unique<Sketcher::Constraint>();
2797 
2798  tangent1->Type = Sketcher::Tangent;
2799  tangent1->First = GeoId1;
2800  tangent1->FirstPos = PosId1;
2801  tangent1->Second = filletId;
2802  tangent1->SecondPos = filletPosId1;
2803 
2804  tangent2->Type = Sketcher::Tangent;
2805  tangent2->First = GeoId2;
2806  tangent2->FirstPos = PosId2;
2807  tangent2->Second = filletId;
2808  tangent2->SecondPos = filletPosId2;
2809 
2810  addConstraint(std::move(tangent1));
2811  addConstraint(std::move(tangent2));
2812  }
2813  }
2814  else if (geo1->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomBoundedCurve>() && geo2->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomBoundedCurve>()) {
2815 
2816  auto distancetorefpoints =
2817  [](Base::Vector3d ip1, Base::Vector3d ip2, Base::Vector3d ref1, Base::Vector3d ref2) {
2818  return (ip1 - ref1).Length() + (ip2 - ref2).Length();
2819  };
2820 
2821  auto selectintersection =
2822  [&distancetorefpoints](std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>>& points,
2823  std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>& interpoints,
2824  const Base::Vector3d& refPnt1,
2825  const Base::Vector3d& refPnt2) {
2826  if (points.empty()) {
2827  return -1;
2828  }
2829  else {
2830  double dist =
2831  distancetorefpoints(points[0].first, points[0].second, refPnt1, refPnt2);
2832  int i = 0, si = 0;
2833 
2834  for (auto ipoints : points) {
2835  double d =
2836  distancetorefpoints(ipoints.first, ipoints.second, refPnt1, refPnt2);
2837 
2838  if (d < dist) {
2839  si = i;
2840  dist = d;
2841  }
2842 
2843  i++;
2844  }
2845 
2846  interpoints = points[si];
2847 
2848  return 0;
2849  }
2850  };
2851 
2852  // NOTE: While it is not a requirement that the endpoints of the corner to trim are
2853  // coincident
2854  // for GeomTrimmedCurves, it is for GeomBoundedCurves. The reason is that there is no
2855  // basiscurve that can be extended to find an intersection.
2856  //
2857  // However, GeomTrimmedCurves sometimes run into problems when trying to calculate the
2858  // intersection of basis curves, for example in the case of hyperbola sometimes the
2859  // cosh goes out of range while calculating this intersection of basis curves.
2860  //
2861  // Consequently:
2862  // i. for GeomBoundedCurves, other than GeomTrimmedCurves, a coincident endpoint is
2863  // mandatory. ii. for GeomTrimmedCurves, if there is a coincident endpoint, it is
2864  // used for the fillet, iii. for GeomTrimmedCurves, if there is not a coincident
2865  // endpoint, an intersection of basis curves
2866  // is attempted.
2867 
2868  const Part::GeomCurve* curve1 = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo1);
2869  const Part::GeomCurve* curve2 = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo2);
2870 
2871  double refparam1;
2872  double refparam2;
2873 
2874  try {
2875  if (!curve1->closestParameter(refPnt1, refparam1))
2876  return -1;
2877  }
2878  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
2879  e.ReportException();
2880  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2881  "Unable to determine the parameter of the first selected curve at the reference "
2882  "point.")
2883  }
2884 
2885  try {
2886  if (!curve2->closestParameter(refPnt2, refparam2))
2887  return -1;
2888  }
2889  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
2890  e.ReportException();
2891  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2892  "Unable to determine the parameter of the second selected curve at the "
2893  "reference point.")
2894  }
2895 
2896 #ifdef DEBUG
2897  Base::Console().Log("\n\nFILLET DEBUG\n\n");
2898  Base::Console().Log("Ref param: (%f);(%f)", refparam1, refparam2);
2899 #endif
2900 
2901  std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d> interpoints;
2902  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>> points;
2903 
2904 
2905  // look for coincident constraints between curves, take the coincident closest to the
2906  // refpoints
2907  double dist = INFINITY;
2908 
2909  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
2910 
2911  for (auto& constr : constraints) {
2912  if (constr->Type == Sketcher::Coincident || constr->Type == Sketcher::Perpendicular
2913  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Tangent) {
2914  if (constr->First == GeoId1 && constr->Second == GeoId2
2915  && constr->FirstPos != PointPos::none
2916  && constr->SecondPos != PointPos::none) {
2917  Base::Vector3d tmpp1 = getPoint(constr->First, constr->FirstPos);
2918  Base::Vector3d tmpp2 = getPoint(constr->Second, constr->SecondPos);
2919  double tmpdist = distancetorefpoints(tmpp1, tmpp2, refPnt1, refPnt2);
2920  if (tmpdist < dist) {
2921  PosId1 = constr->FirstPos;
2922  PosId2 = constr->SecondPos;
2923  dist = tmpdist;
2924  interpoints = std::make_pair(tmpp1, tmpp2);
2925  }
2926  }
2927  else if (constr->First == GeoId2 && constr->Second == GeoId1
2928  && constr->FirstPos != PointPos::none
2929  && constr->SecondPos != PointPos::none) {
2930  Base::Vector3d tmpp2 = getPoint(constr->First, constr->FirstPos);
2931  Base::Vector3d tmpp1 = getPoint(constr->Second, constr->SecondPos);
2932  double tmpdist = distancetorefpoints(tmpp1, tmpp2, refPnt1, refPnt2);
2933  if (tmpdist < dist) {
2934  PosId2 = constr->FirstPos;
2935  PosId1 = constr->SecondPos;
2936  dist = tmpdist;
2937  interpoints = std::make_pair(tmpp1, tmpp2);
2938  }
2939  }
2940  }
2941  }
2942 
2943  if (PosId1 == PointPos::none) {
2944  // no coincident was found, try basis curve intersection if GeomTrimmedCurve
2945  if (geo1->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomTrimmedCurve>()
2946  && geo2->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomTrimmedCurve>()) {
2947 
2948  auto* tcurve1 =static_cast<const Part::GeomTrimmedCurve*>(geo1);
2949  auto* tcurve2 = static_cast<const Part::GeomTrimmedCurve*>(geo2);
2950 
2951  try {
2952  if (!tcurve1->intersectBasisCurves(tcurve2, points))
2953  return -1;
2954  }
2955  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
2956  e.ReportException();
2957  THROWMT(Base::CADKernelError,
2958  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions",
2959  "Unable to guess intersection of curves. Try adding "
2960  "a coincident constraint between the vertices of the "
2961  "curves you are intending to fillet."))
2962  }
2963 
2964  int res = selectintersection(points, interpoints, refPnt1, refPnt2);
2965 
2966  if (res != 0) {
2967  return res;
2968  }
2969  }
2970  else {
2971  return -1;// not a GeomTrimmedCurve and no coincident point.
2972  }
2973  }
2974 
2975  // Now that we know where the curves intersect, get the parameters in the curves of those
2976  // points
2977  double intparam1;
2978  double intparam2;
2979 
2980  try {
2981  if (!curve1->closestParameter(interpoints.first, intparam1)) {
2982  return -1;
2983  }
2984  }
2985  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
2986  e.ReportException();
2987  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2988  "Unable to determine the parameter of the first selected curve at the "
2989  "intersection of the curves.")
2990  }
2991 
2992  try {
2993  if (!curve2->closestParameter(interpoints.second, intparam2)) {
2994  return -1;
2995  }
2996  }
2997  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
2998  e.ReportException();
2999  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
3000  "Unable to determine the parameter of the second selected curve at the "
3001  "intersection of the curves.")
3002  }
3003 
3004  // get the starting parameters of each curve
3005  double spc1 = curve1->getFirstParameter();
3006  double spc2 = curve2->getFirstParameter();
3007 
3008  // get a fillet radius if zero was given
3009  Base::Vector3d ref21 = refPnt2 - refPnt1;
3010 
3011  if (radius == .0f) {
3012  // guess a radius
3013  // https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&t=31594&start=50#p266658
3014  //
3015  // We do not know the actual tangency points until we intersect the offset curves, but
3016  // we do not have offset curves before with decide on a radius.
3017  //
3018  // This estimation guesses a radius as the average of the distances from the reference
3019  // points with respect to the intersection of the normals at those reference points.
3020 
3021  try {
3022  Base::Vector3d tdir1;
3023  Base::Vector3d tdir2;
3024 
3025  // We want normals, but OCCT normals require curves to be 2 times derivable, and
3026  // lines are not tangency calculation requires 1 time derivable.
3027 
3028  if (!curve1->tangent(refparam1, tdir1))
3029  return -1;
3030 
3031  if (!curve2->tangent(refparam2, tdir2))
3032  return -1;
3033 
3034  Base::Vector3d dir1(tdir1.y, -tdir1.x, 0);
3035  Base::Vector3d dir2(tdir2.y, -tdir2.x, 0);
3036 
3037  double det = -dir1.x * dir2.y + dir2.x * dir1.y;
3038 
3039  if (std::abs(det) < Precision::Confusion()) {
3040  // no intersection of normals
3041  throw Base::RuntimeError("No intersection of normals");
3042  }
3043 
3044  Base::Vector3d refp1 = curve1->pointAtParameter(refparam1);
3045  Base::Vector3d refp2 = curve2->pointAtParameter(refparam2);
3046 
3047  // Base::Console().Log("refpoints:
3048  // (%f,%f,%f);(%f,%f,%f)",refp1.x,refp1.y,refp1.z,refp2.x,refp2.y,refp2.z);
3049 
3050  Base::Vector3d normalintersect(
3051  (-dir1.x * dir2.x * refp1.y + dir1.x * dir2.x * refp2.y
3052  - dir1.x * dir2.y * refp2.x + dir2.x * dir1.y * refp1.x)
3053  / det,
3054  (-dir1.x * dir2.y * refp1.y + dir2.x * dir1.y * refp2.y
3055  + dir1.y * dir2.y * refp1.x - dir1.y * dir2.y * refp2.x)
3056  / det,
3057  0);
3058 
3059  radius = ((refp1 - normalintersect).Length() + (refp2 - normalintersect).Length()) / 2;
3060  }
3061  catch (const Base::Exception&) {
3062  radius = ref21.Length();// fall-back to simplest estimation.
3063  }
3064  }
3065 
3066 
3067 #ifdef DEBUG
3068  Base::Console().Log("Start param: (%f);(%f)\n", spc1, spc2);
3069 
3070  Base::Vector3d c1pf = curve1->pointAtParameter(spc1);
3071  Base::Vector3d c2pf = curve2->pointAtParameter(spc2);
3072 
3073  Base::Console().Log("start point curves: (%f,%f,%f);(%f,%f,%f)\n",
3074  c1pf.x,
3075  c1pf.y,
3076  c1pf.z,
3077  c2pf.x,
3078  c2pf.y,
3079  c2pf.z);
3080 #endif
3081  // We create Offset curves at the suggested radius, the direction of offset is estimated
3082  // from the tangency vector
3083  Base::Vector3d tdir1 = curve1->firstDerivativeAtParameter(refparam1);
3084  Base::Vector3d tdir2 = curve2->firstDerivativeAtParameter(refparam2);
3085 
3086 #ifdef DEBUG
3087  Base::Console().Log("tangent vectors: (%f,%f,%f);(%f,%f,%f)\n",
3088  tdir1.x,
3089  tdir1.y,
3090  tdir1.z,
3091  tdir2.x,
3092  tdir2.y,
3093  tdir2.z);
3094  Base::Console().Log("inter-ref vector: (%f,%f,%f)\n", ref21.x, ref21.y, ref21.z);
3095 #endif
3096

3098 
3099  double sdir1 = tdir1.Cross(ref21).Dot(vn);
3100  double sdir2 = tdir2.Cross(-ref21).Dot(vn);
3101 
3102 #ifdef DEBUG
3103  Base::Console().Log("sign of offset: (%f,%f)\n", sdir1, sdir2);
3104  Base::Console().Log("radius: %f\n", radius);
3105 #endif
3106 
3107  Part::GeomOffsetCurve* ocurve1 = new Part::GeomOffsetCurve(
3108  Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(curve1->handle()), (sdir1 < 0) ? radius : -radius, vn);
3109 
3110  Part::GeomOffsetCurve* ocurve2 = new Part::GeomOffsetCurve(
3111  Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(curve2->handle()), (sdir2 < 0) ? radius : -radius, vn);
3112 
3113 #ifdef DEBUG
3114  Base::Vector3d oc1pf = ocurve1->pointAtParameter(ocurve1->getFirstParameter());
3115  Base::Vector3d oc2pf = ocurve2->pointAtParameter(ocurve2->getFirstParameter());
3116 
3117  Base::Console().Log("start point offset curves: (%f,%f,%f);(%f,%f,%f)\n",
3118  oc1pf.x,
3119  oc1pf.y,
3120  oc1pf.z,
3121  oc2pf.x,
3122  oc2pf.y,
3123  oc2pf.z);
3124  // To enable detailed Log of ten intermediate points along the curves uncomment this
3125  /*auto printoffsetcurve = [](Part::GeomOffsetCurve *c) {
3126 
3127  for(double param = c->getFirstParameter(); param < c->getLastParameter(); param = param
3128  + (c->getLastParameter()-c->getFirstParameter())/10) Base::Console().Log("\n%f:
3129  (%f,%f,0)\n", param, c->pointAtParameter(param).x,c->pointAtParameter(param).y);
3130 
3131  };
3132 
3133  printoffsetcurve(ocurve1);
3134  printoffsetcurve(ocurve2);*/
3135 #endif
3136 
3137  // Next we calculate the intersection of offset curves to get the center of the fillet
3138  std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d> filletcenterpoint;
3139  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>> offsetintersectionpoints;
3140 
3141  try {
3142  if (!ocurve1->intersect(ocurve2, offsetintersectionpoints)) {
3143 #ifdef DEBUG
3144  Base::Console().Log("No intersection between offset curves\n");
3145 #endif
3146  return -1;
3147  }
3148  }
3149  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
3150  e.ReportException();
3151  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Unable to find intersection between offset curves.")
3152  }
3153 
3154 #ifdef DEBUG
3155  for (auto inter : offsetintersectionpoints) {
3156  Base::Console().Log("offset int(%f,%f,0)\n", inter.first.x, inter.first.y);
3157  }
3158 #endif
3159 
3160  int res = selectintersection(offsetintersectionpoints, filletcenterpoint, refPnt1, refPnt2);
3161 
3162  if (res != 0) {
3163  return res;
3164  }
3165 
3166 #ifdef DEBUG
3167  Base::Console().Log(
3168  "selected offset int(%f,%f,0)\n", filletcenterpoint.first.x, filletcenterpoint.first.y);
3169 #endif
3170 
3171  double refoparam1;
3172  double refoparam2;
3173 
3174  try {
3175  if (!curve1->closestParameter(filletcenterpoint.first, refoparam1)) {
3176  return -1;
3177  }
3178  }
3179  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
3180  e.ReportException();
3181  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Unable to determine the starting point of the arc.")
3182  }
3183 
3184  try {
3185  if (!curve2->closestParameter(filletcenterpoint.second, refoparam2)) {
3186  return -1;
3187  }
3188  }
3189  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
3190  e.ReportException();
3191  THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Unable to determine the end point of the arc.")
3192  }
3193 
3194  // Next we calculate the closest points to the fillet center, so the points where tangency
3195  // is to be applied
3196  Base::Vector3d refp1 = curve1->pointAtParameter(refoparam1);
3197  Base::Vector3d refp2 = curve2->pointAtParameter(refoparam2);
3198 
3199 #ifdef DEBUG
3200  Base::Console().Log("refpoints: (%f,%f,%f);(%f,%f,%f)",
3201  refp1.x,
3202  refp1.y,
3203  refp1.z,
3204  refp2.x,
3205  refp2.y,
3206  refp2.z);
3207 #endif
3208  // Now we create arc for the fillet
3209  double startAngle, endAngle, range;
3210 
3211  Base::Vector3d radDir1 = refp1 - filletcenterpoint.first;
3212  Base::Vector3d radDir2 = refp2 - filletcenterpoint.first;
3213 
3214  startAngle = atan2(radDir1.y, radDir1.x);
3215 
3216  range = atan2(-radDir1.y * radDir2.x + radDir1.x * radDir2.y,
3217  radDir1.x * radDir2.x + radDir1.y * radDir2.y);
3218 
3219  endAngle = startAngle + range;
3220 
3221  if (endAngle < startAngle) {
3222  std::swap(startAngle, endAngle);
3223  }
3224 
3225  if (endAngle > 2 * M_PI) {
3226  endAngle -= 2 * M_PI;
3227  }
3228 
3229  if (startAngle < 0) {
3230  endAngle += 2 * M_PI;
3231  }
3232 
3233  // Create Arc Segment
3234  auto* arc = new Part::GeomArcOfCircle();
3235  arc->setRadius(radDir1.Length());
3236  arc->setCenter(filletcenterpoint.first);
3237  arc->setRange(startAngle, endAngle, /*emulateCCWXY=*/true);
3238 
3239  p1 = arc->getStartPoint(true);
3240  p2 = arc->getEndPoint(true);
3241 
3242  // add arc to sketch geometry
3243  filletId = addGeometry(arc);
3244  if (filletId < 0) {
3245  delete arc;
3246  return -1;
3247  }
3248 
3249  if (trim) {
3250  auto selectend = [](double intparam, double refparam, double startparam) {
3251  if ((intparam > refparam && startparam >= refparam)
3252  || (intparam < refparam && startparam <= refparam)) {
3253  return PointPos::start;
3254  }
3255  else {
3256  return PointPos::end;
3257  }
3258  };
3259 
3260  // Two cases:
3261  // a) there as a coincidence constraint
3262  // b) we used the basis curve intersection
3263 
3264 
3265  if (PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
3266  PosId1 = selectend(intparam1, refoparam1, spc1);
3267  PosId2 = selectend(intparam2, refoparam2, spc2);
3268  }
3269 
3270 
3271  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId1, PosId1, false);
3272  delConstraintOnPoint(GeoId2, PosId2, false);
3273 
3274  double dist1 = (refp1 - p1).Length();
3275  double dist2 = (refp1 - p2).Length();
3276 
3277  if (dist1 < dist2) {
3278  filletPosId1 = PointPos::start;
3279  filletPosId2 = PointPos::end;
3280  moveGeometry(GeoId1, PosId1, p1, false, true);
3281  moveGeometry(GeoId2, PosId2, p2, false, true);
3282  }
3283  else {
3284  filletPosId1 = PointPos::end;
3285  filletPosId2 = PointPos::start;
3286  moveGeometry(GeoId1, PosId1, p2, false, true);
3287  moveGeometry(GeoId2, PosId2, p1, false, true);
3288  }
3289 
3290  auto* tangent1 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
3291  auto* tangent2 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
3292 
3293  tangent1->Type = Sketcher::Tangent;
3294  tangent1->First = GeoId1;
3295  tangent1->FirstPos = PosId1;
3296  tangent1->Second = filletId;
3297  tangent1->SecondPos = filletPosId1;
3298 
3299  tangent2->Type = Sketcher::Tangent;
3300  tangent2->First = GeoId2;
3301  tangent2->FirstPos = PosId2;
3302  tangent2->Second = filletId;
3303  tangent2->SecondPos = filletPosId2;
3304 
3305  addConstraint(tangent1);
3306  addConstraint(tangent2);
3307  delete tangent1;
3308  delete tangent2;
3309  }
3310  delete arc;
3311  delete ocurve1;
3312  delete ocurve2;
3313 
3314 #ifdef DEBUG
3315  Base::Console().Log("\n\nEND OF FILLET DEBUG\n\n");
3316 #endif
3317  }
3318  else {
3319  return -1;
3320  }
3321 
3322  if (chamfer) {
3323  auto line = std::make_unique<Part::GeomLineSegment>();
3324  line->setPoints(p1, p2);
3325  int lineGeoId = addGeometry(line.get());
3326 
3327 
3328  auto coinc1 = std::make_unique<Sketcher::Constraint>();
3329  auto coinc2 = std::make_unique<Sketcher::Constraint>();
3330 
3331  coinc1->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3332  coinc1->First = lineGeoId;
3333  coinc1->FirstPos = filletPosId1;
3334 
3335  coinc2->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3336  coinc2->First = lineGeoId;
3337  coinc2->FirstPos = filletPosId2;
3338 
3339  if (trim) {
3340  coinc1->Second = GeoId1;
3341  coinc1->SecondPos = PosId1;
3342  coinc2->Second = GeoId2;
3343  coinc2->SecondPos = PosId2;
3344  }
3345  else {
3346  coinc1->Second = filletId;
3347  coinc1->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
3348  coinc2->Second = filletId;
3349  coinc2->SecondPos = PointPos::end;
3350  }
3351 
3352  addConstraint(std::move(coinc1));
3353  addConstraint(std::move(coinc2));
3354 
3355  setConstruction(filletId, true);
3356  }
3357 
3358  // if we do not have a recompute after the geometry creation, the sketch must be solved to
3359  // update the DoF of the solver
3360  if (noRecomputes) {
3361  solve();
3362  }
3363 
3364  return 0;
3365 }

3367 int SketchObject::extend(int GeoId, double increment, PointPos endpoint)
3368 {
3369  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
3370  return -1;
3371 
3372  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& geomList = getInternalGeometry();
3373  Part::Geometry* geom = geomList[GeoId];
3374  int retcode = -1;
3375  if (geom->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
3376  Part::GeomLineSegment* seg = static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
3377  Base::Vector3d startVec = seg->getStartPoint();
3378  Base::Vector3d endVec = seg->getEndPoint();
3379  if (endpoint == PointPos::start) {
3380  Base::Vector3d newPoint = startVec - endVec;
3381  double scaleFactor = newPoint.Length() + increment;
3382  newPoint.Normalize();
3383  newPoint.Scale(scaleFactor, scaleFactor, scaleFactor);
3384  newPoint = newPoint + endVec;
3385  retcode = moveGeometry(GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::start, newPoint, false, true);
3386  }
3387  else if (endpoint == PointPos::end) {
3388  Base::Vector3d newPoint = endVec - startVec;
3389  double scaleFactor = newPoint.Length() + increment;
3390  newPoint.Normalize();
3391  newPoint.Scale(scaleFactor, scaleFactor, scaleFactor);
3392  newPoint = newPoint + startVec;
3393  retcode = moveGeometry(GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::end, newPoint, false, true);
3394  }
3395  }
3396  else if (geom->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
3397  Part::GeomArcOfCircle* arc = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
3398  double startArc, endArc;
3399  arc->getRange(startArc, endArc, true);
3400  if (endpoint == PointPos::start) {
3401  arc->setRange(startArc - increment, endArc, true);
3402  retcode = 0;
3403  }
3404  else if (endpoint == PointPos::end) {
3405  arc->setRange(startArc, endArc + increment, true);
3406  retcode = 0;
3407  }
3408  }
3409  if (retcode == 0 && noRecomputes) {
3410  solve();
3411  }
3412  return retcode;
3413 }

3418 {

3420 
3421  newConstr->Type = constrType;
3422  newConstr->First = firstGeoId;
3423  newConstr->FirstPos = firstPos;
3424  newConstr->Second = secondGeoId;
3425  newConstr->SecondPos = secondPos;
3426  newConstr->Third = thirdGeoId;
3427  newConstr->ThirdPos = thirdPos;
3428  return newConstr;
3429 }

3442 bool SketchObject::seekTrimPoints(int GeoId, const Base::Vector3d& point, int& GeoId1,
3443  Base::Vector3d& intersect1, int& GeoId2,
3444  Base::Vector3d& intersect2)
3445 {
3446  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
3447  return false;
3448 
3449  auto geos = getCompleteGeometry();// this includes the axes too
3450 
3451  geos.resize(geos.size() - 2);// remove the axes to avoid intersections with the axes
3452 
3453  int localindex1, localindex2;
3454 
3455  // Not found in will be returned as -1, not as GeoUndef, Part WB is agnostic to the concept of
3456  // GeoUndef
3457  if (!Part2DObject::seekTrimPoints(
3458  geos, GeoId, point, localindex1, intersect1, localindex2, intersect2))
3459  return false;
3460 
3461  // invalid complete geometry indices are mapped to GeoUndef
3462  GeoId1 = getGeoIdFromCompleteGeometryIndex(localindex1);
3463  GeoId2 = getGeoIdFromCompleteGeometryIndex(localindex2);
3464 
3465  return true;
3466 }

3468 int SketchObject::trim(int GeoId, const Base::Vector3d& point)
3469 {
3470  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
3471  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
3472 
3473  //******************* Basic checks rejecting the operation
3474  //****************************************//
3475  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
3476  return -1;
3477 
3478  auto geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
3479 
3480  if (!GeometryFacade::isInternalType(geo, InternalType::None))
3481  return -1;// internal alignment geometry is not trimmable
3482 
3483  //******************* Lambdas - common functions for different intersections
3484  //****************************************//
3485 
3486  // returns true if the point defined by (GeoId1, pos1) can be considered to be coincident with
3487  // point.
3488  auto arePointsWithinPrecision = [](Base::Vector3d point1, Base::Vector3d& point2) {
3489  // From testing: 500x (or 0.000050) is needed in order to not falsely distinguish points
3490  // calculated with seekTrimPoints
3491  return ((point1 - point2).Length() < 500 * Precision::Confusion()) ;
3492  };
3493 
3494  auto isPointAtPosition = [this, &arePointsWithinPrecision]
3495  (int GeoId1, PointPos pos1, Base::Vector3d point) {
3496  Base::Vector3d pp = getPoint(GeoId1, pos1);
3497 
3498  return arePointsWithinPrecision(point, pp);
3499  };
3500 #if 0
3501  // Checks whether preexisting constraints must be converted to new constraints.
3502  // Preexisting point on object constraints get converted to coincidents, unless an end-to-end
3503  // tangency is more relevant. returns by reference:
3504  // - The type of constraint that should be used to constraint GeoId1 and GeoId
3505  // - The element of GeoId1 to which the constraint should be applied.
3506  auto transformPreexistingConstraint = [this, isPointAtPosition](int GeoId,
3507  int GeoId1,
3508  Base::Vector3d point1,
3509  Constraint* constr) {
3510  // TODO: Move code currently later in this method (that does as per the following description) here.
3511  /* It is possible that the trimming entity has both a PointOnObject constraint to the
3512  * trimmed entity, and a simple Tangent constraint to the trimmed entity. In this case we
3513  * want to change to a single end-to-end tangency, i.e we want to ensure that constrType1 is
3514  * set to Sketcher::Tangent, that the secondPos1 is captured from the PointOnObject, and
3515  * also make sure that the PointOnObject constraint is deleted. The below loop ensures this,
3516  * also in case the ordering of the constraints is first Tangent and then PointOnObject. */
3517  };
3518 #endif
3519  // makes an equality constraint between GeoId1 and GeoId2
3520  auto constrainAsEqual = [this](int GeoId1, int GeoId2) {
3521  auto newConstr = std::make_unique<Sketcher::Constraint>();
3522 
3523  // Build Constraints associated with new pair of arcs
3524  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
3525  newConstr->First = GeoId1;
3526  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
3527  newConstr->Second = GeoId2;
3528  newConstr->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
3529  addConstraint(std::move(newConstr));
3530  };
3531 
3532  // given a geometry and tree points, returns the corresponding parameters of the geometry points
3533  // closest to them
3534  auto getIntersectionParameters = [](const Part::Geometry* geo,
3535  const Base::Vector3d point,
3536  double& pointParam,
3537  const Base::Vector3d point1,
3538  double& point1Param,
3539  const Base::Vector3d point2,
3540  double& point2Param) {
3541  auto curve = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo);
3542 
3543  try {
3544  curve->closestParameter(point, pointParam);
3545  curve->closestParameter(point1, point1Param);
3546  curve->closestParameter(point2, point2Param);
3547  }
3548  catch (Base::CADKernelError& e) {
3549  e.ReportException();
3550  return false;
3551  }
3552 
3553  return true;
3554  };
3555 
3556  //******************* Step A => Detection of intersection - Common to all Geometries
3557  //****************************************//
3558  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
3559  Base::Vector3d point1, point2;
3560 
3561  // Remove internal geometry beforehand so GeoId1 and GeoId2 do not change
3562  deleteUnusedInternalGeometryAndUpdateGeoId(GeoId);
3563  geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
3564 
3565  // Using SketchObject wrapper, as Part2DObject version returns GeoId = -1 when intersection not
3566  // found, which is wrong for a GeoId (axis). seekTrimPoints returns:
3567  // - For a parameter associated with "point" between an intersection and the end point
3568  // (non-periodic case) GeoId1 != GeoUndef and GeoId2 == GeoUndef
3569  // - For a parameter associated with "point" between the start point and an intersection
3570  // (non-periodic case) GeoId2 != GeoUndef and GeoId1 == GeoUndef
3571  // - For a parameter associated with "point" between two intersection points, GeoId1 != GeoUndef
3572  // and GeoId2 != GeoUndef
3573  //
3574  // FirstParam < point1param < point2param < LastParam
3575  if (!SketchObject::seekTrimPoints(GeoId, point, GeoId1, point1, GeoId2, point2)) {
3576  // If no suitable trim points are found, then trim defaults to deleting the geometry
3577  delGeometry(GeoId);
3578  return 0;
3579  }
3580 
3581  if (GeoId1 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef && GeoId2 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef
3582  && arePointsWithinPrecision(point1, point2)) {
3583  // If both points are detected and are coincident, deletion is the only option.
3584  delGeometry(GeoId);
3585  return 0;
3586  }
3587 
3588  const auto* geoAsCurve = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo);
3589  double firstParam = geoAsCurve->getFirstParameter();
3590  double lastParam = geoAsCurve->getLastParameter();
3591  double pointParam, point1Param, point2Param;
3592  if (!getIntersectionParameters(
3593  geo, point, pointParam, point1, point1Param, point2, point2Param)) {
3594  return -1;
3595  }
3596 
3597  bool startPointRemains = false;
3598  bool endPointRemains = false;
3599  std::vector<std::pair<double, double> > paramsOfNewGeos;
3600  std::vector<int> newIds;
3601  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newGeos;
3602  std::vector<const Part::Geometry*> newGeosAsConsts;
3603 
3604  if (isClosedCurve(geo)) {
3605  startPointRemains = false;
3606  endPointRemains = false;
3607  if (GeoId1 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef && GeoId2 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
3608  paramsOfNewGeos.emplace_back(point2Param, point1Param);
3609  }
3610  }
3611  else {
3612  if (GeoId1 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
3613  startPointRemains = true;
3614  paramsOfNewGeos.emplace_back(firstParam, point1Param);
3615  }
3616  if (GeoId2 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
3617  endPointRemains = true;
3618  paramsOfNewGeos.emplace_back(point2Param, lastParam);
3619  }
3620  }
3621 
3622  for (auto& [u1, u2] : paramsOfNewGeos) {
3623  auto newGeo = geoAsCurve->createArc(u1, u2);
3624  assert(newGeo);
3625  newGeos.push_back(newGeo);
3626  newGeosAsConsts.push_back(newGeo);
3627  }
3628 
3629  switch (newGeos.size()) {
3630  case 0: {
3631  delGeometry(GeoId);
3632  return 0;
3633  }
3634  case 1: {
3635  newIds.push_back(GeoId);
3636  break;
3637  }
3638  case 2: {
3639  newIds.push_back(GeoId);
3640  newIds.push_back(getHighestCurveIndex() + 1);
3641  break;
3642  }
3643  default: {
3644  for (auto& newGeo : newGeos) {
3645  delete newGeo;
3646  }
3647  return -1;
3648  }
3649  }
3650 
3651  // Now that we have the new curves, change constraints as needed
3652  // Some are covered with `deriveConstraintsForPieces`, others are specific to trim
3653  // FIXME: We are using non-smart pointers since that's what's needed in `addConstraints`.
3654  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints;
3655 
3656  // A geoId we expect to never exist during this operation (but still not `GeoEnum::GeoUndef`).
3657  // We use it because newIds.front() is supposed to be `GeoId`, but we will delete constraints
3658  // on it down the line, even if we may need it later.
3659  // Note that this will cause some malformed constraints until they are transferred back.
3660  int nonexistentGeoId = getHighestCurveIndex() + newIds.size();
3661  newIds.front() = nonexistentGeoId;
3662 
3663  // Constraints related to start/mid/end points of original
3664  if (startPointRemains) {
3665  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::start, newIds.front(), PointPos::start, true);
3666  }
3667  if (endPointRemains) {
3668  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::end, newIds.back(), PointPos::end, true);
3669  }
3670  bool geomHasMid = geo->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomConic>() || geo->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomArcOfConic>();
3671  if (geomHasMid) {
3672  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::mid, newIds.front(), PointPos::mid, true);
3673  // Make centers coincident
3674  if (newIds.size() > 1) {
3675  Constraint* joint = new Constraint();
3676  joint = new Constraint();
3677  joint->Type = Coincident;
3678  joint->First = newIds.front();
3679  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::mid;
3680  joint->Second = newIds.back();
3681  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::mid;
3682  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
3683 
3684  // Any radius etc. equality constraints here
3685  constrainAsEqual(newIds.front(), newIds.back());
3686  // TODO: ensure alignment as well?
3687  }
3688  }
3689 
3690  newIds.front() = GeoId;
3691 
3692  std::vector<int> idsOfOldConstraints;
3693  getConstraintIndices(GeoId, idsOfOldConstraints);
3694 
3695  const auto& allConstraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
3696 
3697  bool isPoint1ConstrainedOnGeoId1 = false;
3698  bool isPoint2ConstrainedOnGeoId2 = false;
3699 
3700  // Workaround to avoid https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/issues/15484.
3701  // We will delete its internal geometry first and then replace GeoId with one of the curves.
3702  // Of course, this will change `newIds`, and that's why we offset them.
3703  std::set< int, std::greater<> > geoIdsToBeDeleted;
3704  // geoIdsToBeDeleted.push_back(GeoId);
3705 
3706  for (const auto& oldConstrId: idsOfOldConstraints) {
3707  // trim-specific changes first
3708  const Constraint* con = allConstraints[oldConstrId];
3709  bool constraintWasModified = false;
3710  switch (con->Type) {
3711  case PointOnObject: {
3712  // we might want to transform this (and the new point-on-object constraints) into a coincidence
3713  if (con->First == GeoId1 && con->Second == GeoId
3714  && isPointAtPosition(con->First, con->FirstPos, point1)) {
3715  // This concerns the start portion of the trim
3716  Constraint* newConstr = con->copy();
3717  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3718  newConstr->Second = newIds.front();
3719  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::end;
3720  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3721  isPoint1ConstrainedOnGeoId1 = true;
3722  constraintWasModified = true;
3723  }
3724  else if (con->First == GeoId2 && con->Second == GeoId
3725  && isPointAtPosition(con->First, con->FirstPos, point2)) {
3726  // This concerns the end portion of the trim
3727  Constraint* newConstr = con->copy();
3728  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3729  newConstr->Second = newIds.back();
3730  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
3731  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3732  isPoint2ConstrainedOnGeoId2 = true;
3733  constraintWasModified = true;
3734  }
3735  break;
3736  }
3737  case Tangent:
3738  case Perpendicular: {
3739  // These may have to be turned into endpoint-to-endpoint or endpoint-to-edge
3740  // TODO: could there be tangent/perpendicular constraints not involving the trim that are modified below?
3741  if (con->involvesGeoId(GeoId1) && con->involvesGeoIdAndPosId(GeoId, PointPos::none)) {
3742  Constraint* newConstr = con->copy();
3743  newConstr->substituteIndexAndPos(GeoId, PointPos::none, newIds.front(), PointPos::end);
3744  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3745  isPoint1ConstrainedOnGeoId1 = true;
3746  constraintWasModified = true;
3747  }
3748  if (con->involvesGeoId(GeoId2) && con->involvesGeoIdAndPosId(GeoId, PointPos::none)) {
3749  Constraint* newConstr = con->copy();
3750  newConstr->substituteIndexAndPos(GeoId, PointPos::none, newIds.back(), PointPos::start);
3751  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3752  isPoint2ConstrainedOnGeoId2 = true;
3753  constraintWasModified = true;
3754  }
3755  if (constraintWasModified) {
3756  // make sure the first position is a point
3757  if (newConstraints.back()->FirstPos == PointPos::none) {
3758  std::swap(newConstraints.back()->First, newConstraints.back()->Second);
3759  std::swap(newConstraints.back()->FirstPos, newConstraints.back()->SecondPos);
3760  }
3761  // there is no need for the third point if it exists
3762  newConstraints.back()->Third = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
3763  newConstraints.back()->ThirdPos = PointPos::none;
3764  }
3765  break;
3766  }
3767  case InternalAlignment: {
3768  geoIdsToBeDeleted.insert(con->First);
3769  break;
3770  }
3771  default:
3772  break;
3773  }
3774  if (!constraintWasModified) {
3775  deriveConstraintsForPieces(GeoId, newIds, newGeosAsConsts, con, newConstraints);
3776  }
3777  }
3778 
3779  // Add point-on-object/coincidence constraints with the newly exposed points.
3780  // This will need to account for the constraints that were already converted
3781  // to coincident or end-to-end tangency/perpendicularity.
3782  // TODO: Tangent/perpendicular not yet covered
3783 
3784  if (GeoId1 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef && !isPoint1ConstrainedOnGeoId1) {
3785  Constraint* newConstr = new Constraint();
3786  newConstr->First = newIds.front();
3787  newConstr->FirstPos = PointPos::end;
3788  newConstr->Second = GeoId1;
3789  if (isPointAtPosition(GeoId1, Sketcher::PointPos::start, point1)) {
3790  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3791  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
3792  }
3793  else if (isPointAtPosition(GeoId1, Sketcher::PointPos::end, point1)) {
3794  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3795  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::end;
3796  }
3797  else {
3798  // Points are sufficiently far apart: use point-on-object
3799  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::PointOnObject;
3800  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::none;
3801  }
3802  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3803  }
3804 
3805  if (GeoId2 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef && !isPoint2ConstrainedOnGeoId2) {
3806  Constraint* newConstr = new Constraint();
3807  newConstr->First = newIds.back();
3808  newConstr->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
3809  newConstr->Second = GeoId2;
3810  if (isPointAtPosition(GeoId2, Sketcher::PointPos::start, point2)) {
3811  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3812  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
3813  }
3814  else if (isPointAtPosition(GeoId2, Sketcher::PointPos::end, point2)) {
3815  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
3816  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::end;
3817  }
3818  else {
3819  // Points are sufficiently far apart: use point-on-object
3820  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::PointOnObject;
3821  newConstr->SecondPos = PointPos::none;
3822  }
3823  newConstraints.push_back(newConstr);
3824  }
3825 
3826  // Workaround to avoid https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/issues/15484.
3827  // Delete the geometry first to avoid it happening.
3828  // Of course, this will change `newIds`, and that's why we offset them.
3829  delConstraints(idsOfOldConstraints);
3830 
3831  // Retransfer constraints we put away to `nonexistentGeoId`
3832  transferConstraints(nonexistentGeoId, PointPos::start, GeoId, PointPos::start, true);
3833  transferConstraints(nonexistentGeoId, PointPos::end, GeoId, PointPos::end, true);
3834  transferConstraints(nonexistentGeoId, PointPos::mid, GeoId, PointPos::mid, true);
3835 
3836  auto vals = getInternalGeometry();
3837  auto newVals(vals);
3838  newVals[GeoId] = newGeos.front();
3839  if (newGeos.size() > 1) {
3840  newVals.push_back(newGeos.back());
3841  generateId(newGeos.back());
3842  newIds.back() = newVals.size() - 1;
3843  }
3844  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
3845 
3846  // FIXME: Somewhere here we need to delete the internal geometry (even if in use)
3847  // FIXME: Set the second geoid as construction or not depending on what the original was
3848 
3849  if (noRecomputes) {
3850  solve();
3851  }
3852 
3853  for (auto& deletedGeoId : geoIdsToBeDeleted) {
3854  for (auto& cons : newConstraints) {
3855  changeConstraintAfterDeletingGeo(cons, deletedGeoId);
3856  }
3857  }
3858  addConstraints(newConstraints);
3859 
3860  if (noRecomputes)
3861  solve();
3862 
3863  // Since we used regular "non-smart" pointers, we have to handle cleanup
3864  for (auto& cons : newConstraints) {
3865  delete cons;
3866  }
3867 
3868  return 0;
3869 }
3870 
3871 std::unique_ptr<Constraint>
3872 SketchObject::getConstraintAfterDeletingGeo(const Constraint* constr,
3873  const int deletedGeoId) const
3874 {
3875  if (constr->First == deletedGeoId ||
3876  constr->Second == deletedGeoId ||
3877  constr->Third == deletedGeoId) {
3878  return nullptr;
3879  }
3880 
3881  // TODO: While this is not incorrect, it recreates all constraints regardless of whether or not we need to.
3882  auto newConstr = std::unique_ptr<Constraint>(constr->clone());
3883 
3884  changeConstraintAfterDeletingGeo(newConstr.get(), deletedGeoId);
3885 
3886  return newConstr;
3887 }
3888 
3889 void SketchObject::changeConstraintAfterDeletingGeo(Constraint* constr,
3890  const int deletedGeoId) const
3891 {
3892  int step = 1;
3893  std::function<bool (const int&)> needsUpdate = [&deletedGeoId](const int& givenId) -> bool {
3894  return givenId > deletedGeoId;
3895  };
3896  if (deletedGeoId < 0) {
3897  step = -1;
3898  needsUpdate = [&deletedGeoId](const int& givenId) -> bool {
3899  return givenId < deletedGeoId && givenId != GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
3900  };
3901  }
3902 
3903  if (needsUpdate(constr->First)) {
3904  constr->First -= step;
3905  }
3906  if (needsUpdate(constr->Second)) {
3907  constr->Second -= step;
3908  }
3909  if (needsUpdate(constr->Third)) {
3910  constr->Third -= step;
3911  }
3912 }
3913 
3914 bool SketchObject::deriveConstraintsForPieces(const int oldId,
3915  const std::vector<int>& newIds,
3916  const Constraint* con,
3917  std::vector<Constraint*>& newConstraints)
3918 {
3919  std::vector<const Part::Geometry*> newGeos;
3920  for (auto& newId: newIds) {
3921  newGeos.push_back(getGeometry(newId));
3922  }
3923 
3924  return deriveConstraintsForPieces(oldId, newIds, newGeos, con, newConstraints);
3925 }
3926 
3927 bool SketchObject::deriveConstraintsForPieces(const int oldId,
3928  const std::vector<int>& newIds,
3929  const std::vector<const Part::Geometry*>& newGeos,
3930  const Constraint* con,
3931  std::vector<Constraint*>& newConstraints)
3932 {
3933  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(oldId);
3934  int conId = con->First;
3935  PointPos conPos = con->FirstPos;
3936  if (conId == oldId) {
3937  conId = con->Second;
3938  conPos = con->SecondPos;
3939  }
3940 
3941  bool transferToAll = false;
3942  switch (con->Type) {
3943  case Horizontal:
3944  case Vertical:
3945  case Parallel: {
3946  transferToAll = geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>();
3947  break;
3948  }
3949  case Tangent:
3950  case Perpendicular: {
3951  if (geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
3952  transferToAll = true;
3953  break;
3954  }
3955 
3956  const Part::Geometry* conGeo = getGeometry(conId);
3957  if (!(conGeo && conGeo->isDerivedFrom<Part::GeomCurve>())) {
3958  return false;
3959  }
3960 
3961  // For now: just transfer to the first intersection
3962  // TODO: Actually check that there was perpendicularity earlier
3963  // TODO: Choose piece based on parameters ("values" of the constraint)
3964  for (size_t i = 0; i < newIds.size(); ++i) {
3965  std::vector<std::pair<Base::Vector3d, Base::Vector3d>> intersections;
3966  bool intersects = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(newGeos[i])->intersect(
3967  static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(conGeo), intersections);
3968 
3969  if (intersects) {
3970  Constraint* trans = con->copy();
3971  trans->substituteIndex(oldId, newIds[i]);
3972  newConstraints.push_back(trans);
3973  return true;
3974  }
3975  }
3976 
3977  break;
3978  }
3979  case Distance:
3980  case DistanceX:
3981  case DistanceY:
3982  case PointOnObject: {
3983  if (con->FirstPos == PointPos::none && con->SecondPos == PointPos::none && newIds.size() > 1) {
3984  Constraint* dist = con->copy();
3985  dist->First = newIds.front();
3986  dist->FirstPos = PointPos::start;
3987  dist->Second = newIds.back();
3988  dist->SecondPos = PointPos::end;
3989  newConstraints.push_back(dist);
3990  return true;
3991  }
3992 
3993  Base::Vector3d conPoint(getPoint(conId, conPos));
3994  double conParam;
3995  auto geoAsCurve = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo);
3996  geoAsCurve->closestParameter(conPoint, conParam);
3997  // Choose based on where the closest point lies
3998  // If it's not there, just leave this constraint out
3999  for (size_t i = 0; i < newIds.size(); ++i) {
4000  double newGeoFirstParam = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(newGeos[i])->getFirstParameter();
4001  double newGeoLastParam = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(newGeos[i])->getLastParameter();
4002  // For periodic curves the point may need a full revolution
4003  if ((newGeoFirstParam - conParam) > Precision::PApproximation()
4004  && isClosedCurve(geo)) {
4005  conParam += (geoAsCurve->getLastParameter() - geoAsCurve->getFirstParameter());
4006  }
4007  if ((newGeoFirstParam - conParam) <= Precision::PApproximation()
4008  && (conParam - newGeoLastParam) <= Precision::PApproximation()) {
4009  Constraint* trans = con->copy();
4010  trans->First = conId;
4011  trans->FirstPos = conPos;
4012  trans->Second = newIds[i];
4013  trans->SecondPos = PointPos::none;
4014  newConstraints.push_back(trans);
4015  return true;
4016  }
4017  }
4018 
4019  break;
4020  }
4021  case Radius:
4022  case Diameter:
4023  case Equal: {
4024  // FIXME: This sounds good by itself, but results in redundant constraints when equality is applied between newIds
4025  transferToAll = geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>()
4026  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>();
4027  break;
4028  }
4029  default:
4030  // Release other constraints
4031  break;
4032  }
4033 
4034  if (transferToAll) {
4035  for (auto& newId : newIds) {
4036  Constraint* trans = con->copy();
4037  trans->substituteIndex(oldId, newId);
4038  newConstraints.push_back(trans);
4039  }
4040 
4041  return true;
4042  }
4043 
4044  return false;
4045 }
4046 
4047 int SketchObject::split(int GeoId, const Base::Vector3d& point)
4048 {
4049  // No need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation
4050 
4051  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
4052 
4053  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex()) {
4054  return -1;
4055  }
4056 
4057  bool originalIsPeriodic = false;
4058  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
4059  std::vector<int> newIds;
4060  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints;
4061 
4062  Base::Vector3d startPoint, endPoint, splitPoint;
4063  double startParam, endParam, splitParam = 0.0;
4064 
4065  auto createGeosFromPeriodic = [&](const Part::GeomCurve* curve,
4066  auto getCurveWithLimitParams,
4067  auto createAndTransferConstraints) {
4068  // find split point
4069  curve->closestParameter(point, splitParam);
4070  double period = curve->getLastParameter() - curve->getFirstParameter();
4071  startParam = splitParam;
4072  endParam = splitParam + period;
4073 
4074  // create new arc and restrict it
4075  auto newCurve = getCurveWithLimitParams(curve, startParam, endParam);
4076  int newId(GeoEnum::GeoUndef);
4077  newId = addGeometry(std::move(newCurve));// after here newCurve is a shell
4078  if (newId < 0) {
4079  return false;
4080  }
4081 
4082  newIds.push_back(newId);
4083  setConstruction(newId, GeometryFacade::getConstruction(curve));
4084  exposeInternalGeometry(newId);
4085 
4086  // transfer any constraints
4087  createAndTransferConstraints(GeoId, newId);
4088  return true;
4089  };
4090 
4091  auto createGeosFromNonPeriodic = [&](const Part::GeomBoundedCurve* curve,
4092  auto getCurveWithLimitParams,
4093  auto createAndTransferConstraints) {
4094  startPoint = curve->getStartPoint();
4095  endPoint = curve->getEndPoint();
4096 
4097  // find split point
4098  curve->closestParameter(point, splitParam);
4099  startParam = curve->getFirstParameter();
4100  endParam = curve->getLastParameter();
4101  // TODO: Using parameter difference as a poor substitute of length.
4102  // Computing length of an arc of a generic conic would be expensive.
4103  if (endParam - splitParam < Precision::PConfusion()
4104  || splitParam - startParam < Precision::PConfusion()) {
4105  THROWM(ValueError, "Split point is at one of the end points of the curve.");
4106  }
4107 
4108  // create new curves
4109  auto newCurve = getCurveWithLimitParams(curve, startParam, splitParam);
4110  int newId(GeoEnum::GeoUndef);
4111  newId = addGeometry(std::move(newCurve));
4112  if (newId < 0) {
4113  return false;
4114  }
4115  newIds.push_back(newId);
4116  setConstruction(newId, GeometryFacade::getConstruction(curve));
4117  exposeInternalGeometry(newId);
4118 
4119  // the "second" half
4120  newCurve = getCurveWithLimitParams(curve, splitParam, endParam);
4121  newId = addGeometry(std::move(newCurve));
4122  if (newId < 0) {
4123  return false;
4124  }
4125  newIds.push_back(newId);
4126  setConstruction(newId, GeometryFacade::getConstruction(curve));
4127  exposeInternalGeometry(newId);
4128 
4129  // TODO: Certain transfers and new constraint can be directly made here.
4130  // But this may reduce readability.
4131  // apply appropriate constraints on the new points at split point and
4132  // transfer constraints from start and end of original spline
4133  createAndTransferConstraints(GeoId, newIds[0], newIds[1]);
4134  return true;
4135  };
4136 
4137  bool ok = false;
4138  if (geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
4139  originalIsPeriodic = false;
4140  ok = createGeosFromNonPeriodic(
4141  static_cast<const Part::GeomBoundedCurve*>(geo),
4142  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4143  auto newArc = std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomLineSegment>(
4144  static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(curve->copy()));
4145  newArc->setRange(startParam, endParam);
4146  return newArc;
4147  },
4148  [this, &newConstraints](int GeoId, int newId0, int newId1) {
4149  Constraint* joint = new Constraint();
4150  joint->Type = Coincident;
4151  joint->First = newId0;
4152  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::end;
4153  joint->Second = newId1;
4154  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
4155  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
4156 
4157  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::start, newId0, PointPos::start);
4158  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::end, newId1, PointPos::end);
4159  });
4160  }
4161  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
4162  originalIsPeriodic = true;
4163  ok = createGeosFromPeriodic(
4164  static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo),
4165  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4166  auto newArc = std::make_unique<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>(
4167  Handle(Geom_Circle)::DownCast(curve->handle()->Copy()));
4168  newArc->setRange(startParam, endParam, false);
4169  return newArc;
4170  },
4171  [this](int GeoId, int newId) {
4172  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::mid, newId, PointPos::mid);
4173  });
4174  }
4175  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
4176  originalIsPeriodic = true;
4177  ok = createGeosFromPeriodic(
4178  static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo),
4179  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4180  auto newArc = std::make_unique<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>(
4181  Handle(Geom_Ellipse)::DownCast(curve->handle()->Copy()));
4182  newArc->setRange(startParam, endParam, false);
4183  return newArc;
4184  },
4185  [this](int GeoId, int newId) {
4186  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::mid, newId, PointPos::mid);
4187  });
4188  }
4189  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
4190  originalIsPeriodic = false;
4191  ok = createGeosFromNonPeriodic(
4192  static_cast<const Part::GeomBoundedCurve*>(geo),
4193  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4194  auto newArc = std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>(
4195  static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(curve->copy()));
4196  newArc->setRange(startParam, endParam, false);
4197  return newArc;
4198  },
4199  [this, &newConstraints](int GeoId, int newId0, int newId1) {
4200  Constraint* joint = new Constraint();
4201  joint->Type = Coincident;
4202  joint->First = newId0;
4203  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::end;
4204  joint->Second = newId1;
4205  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
4206  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
4207 
4208  joint = new Constraint();
4209  joint->Type = Coincident;
4210  joint->First = newId0;
4211  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::mid;
4212  joint->Second = newId1;
4213  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::mid;
4214  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
4215 
4216  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::start, newId0, PointPos::start, true);
4217  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::mid, newId0, PointPos::mid);
4218  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::end, newId1, PointPos::end, true);
4219  });
4220  }
4221  else if (geo->isDerivedFrom(Part::GeomArcOfConic::getClassTypeId())) {
4222  originalIsPeriodic = false;
4223  ok = createGeosFromNonPeriodic(
4224  static_cast<const Part::GeomBoundedCurve*>(geo),
4225  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4226  auto newArc = std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomArcOfConic>(
4227  static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfConic*>(curve->copy()));
4228  newArc->setRange(startParam, endParam);
4229  return newArc;
4230  },
4231  [this, &newConstraints](int GeoId, int newId0, int newId1) {
4232  // apply appropriate constraints on the new points at split point
4233  Constraint* joint = new Constraint();
4234  joint->Type = Coincident;
4235  joint->First = newId0;
4236  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::end;
4237  joint->Second = newId1;
4238  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
4239  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
4240 
4241  // TODO: Do we apply constraints on center etc of the conics?
4242 
4243  // transfer constraints from start, mid and end of original
4244  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::start, newId0, PointPos::start, true);
4245  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::mid, newId0, PointPos::mid);
4246  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::end, newId1, PointPos::end, true);
4247  });
4248  }
4249  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
4250  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
4251 
4252  // what to do for periodic b-splines?
4253  originalIsPeriodic = bsp->isPeriodic();
4254  if (originalIsPeriodic) {
4255  ok = createGeosFromPeriodic(
4256  static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo),
4257  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4258  auto newBsp = std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>(
4259  static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(curve->copy()));
4260  newBsp->Trim(startParam, endParam);
4261  return newBsp;
4262  },
4263  [](int, int) {
4264  // no constraints to transfer here, and we assume the split is to "break" the
4265  // b-spline
4266  });
4267  }
4268  else {
4269  ok = createGeosFromNonPeriodic(
4270  static_cast<const Part::GeomBoundedCurve*>(geo),
4271  [](const Part::GeomCurve* curve, double startParam, double endParam) {
4272  auto newBsp = std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>(
4273  static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(curve->copy()));
4274  newBsp->Trim(startParam, endParam);
4275  return newBsp;
4276  },
4277  [this, &newConstraints](int GeoId, int newId0, int newId1) {
4278  // apply appropriate constraints on the new points at split point
4279  Constraint* joint = new Constraint();
4280  joint->Type = Coincident;
4281  joint->First = newId0;
4282  joint->FirstPos = PointPos::end;
4283  joint->Second = newId1;
4284  joint->SecondPos = PointPos::start;
4285  newConstraints.push_back(joint);
4286 
4287  // transfer constraints from start and end of original spline
4288  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::start, newId0, PointPos::start, true);
4289  transferConstraints(GeoId, PointPos::end, newId1, PointPos::end, true);
4290  });
4291  }
4292  }
4293 
4294  if (!ok) {
4295  for (auto& cons : newConstraints) {
4296  delete cons;
4297  }
4298 
4299  return -1;
4300  }
4301 
4302  std::vector<int> idsOfOldConstraints;
4303  getConstraintIndices(GeoId, idsOfOldConstraints);
4304 
4305  const auto& allConstraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
4306 
4307  // keep constraints on internal geometries so they are deleted
4308  // when the old curve is deleted
4309  idsOfOldConstraints.erase(std::remove_if(idsOfOldConstraints.begin(),
4310  idsOfOldConstraints.end(),
4311  [=](const auto& i) {
4312  return allConstraints[i]->Type == InternalAlignment;
4313  }),
4314  idsOfOldConstraints.end());
4315 
4316  for (const auto& oldConstrId: idsOfOldConstraints) {
4317  Constraint* con = allConstraints[oldConstrId];
4318  deriveConstraintsForPieces(GeoId, newIds, con, newConstraints);
4319  }
4320 
4321  if (noRecomputes)
4322  solve();
4323 
4324  delConstraints(idsOfOldConstraints);
4325  addConstraints(newConstraints);
4326 
4327  for (auto& cons : newConstraints) {
4328  delete cons;
4329  }
4330 
4331  delGeometry(GeoId);
4332  return 0;
4333 }
4334 
4335 int SketchObject::join(int geoId1, Sketcher::PointPos posId1, int geoId2, Sketcher::PointPos posId2, int continuity)
4336 {
4337  // No need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation
4338 
4339  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
4340 
4341  if (Sketcher::PointPos::start != posId1 && Sketcher::PointPos::end != posId1
4342  && Sketcher::PointPos::start != posId2 && Sketcher::PointPos::end != posId2) {
4343  THROWM(ValueError, "Invalid position(s): points must be start or end points of a curve.");
4344  return -1;
4345  }
4346 
4347  if (geoId1 == geoId2) {
4348  THROWM(ValueError, "Connecting the end points of the same curve is not yet supported.");
4349  return -1;
4350  }
4351 
4352  if (geoId1 < 0 || geoId1 > getHighestCurveIndex() || geoId2 < 0
4353  || geoId2 > getHighestCurveIndex()) {
4354  return -1;
4355  }
4356 
4357  // get the old splines
4358  auto* geo1 = dynamic_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(getGeometry(geoId1));
4359  auto* geo2 = dynamic_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(getGeometry(geoId2));
4360 
4361  if (GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo1) != GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo2)) {
4362  THROWM(ValueError, "Cannot join construction and non-construction geometries.");
4363  return -1;
4364  }
4365 
4366  // TODO: make both curves b-splines here itself
4367  if (!geo1 || !geo2) {
4368  return -1;
4369  }
4370 
4371  // TODO: is there a cleaner way to get our mutable bsp's?
4372  // we need the splines to be mutable because we may reverse them
4373  // and/or change their degree
4374  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve> bsp1(
4375  geo1->toNurbs(geo1->getFirstParameter(), geo1->getLastParameter()));
4376  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve> bsp2(
4377  geo2->toNurbs(geo2->getFirstParameter(), geo2->getLastParameter()));
4378 
4379  if (bsp1->isPeriodic() || bsp2->isPeriodic()) {
4380  THROWM(ValueError, "It is only possible to join non-periodic curves.");
4381  return -1;
4382  }
4383 
4384  // reverse the splines if needed: join end of 1st to start of 2nd
4385  if (Sketcher::PointPos::start == posId1)
4386  bsp1->reverse();
4387  if (Sketcher::PointPos::end == posId2)
4388  bsp2->reverse();
4389 
4390  // ensure the degrees of both curves are the same
4391  if (bsp1->getDegree() < bsp2->getDegree())
4392  bsp1->increaseDegree(bsp2->getDegree());
4393  else if (bsp2->getDegree() < bsp1->getDegree())
4394  bsp2->increaseDegree(bsp1->getDegree());
4395 
4396  // TODO: Check for tangent constraint here
4397  bool makeC1Continuous = (continuity >= 1);
4398 
4399  // TODO: Rescale one or both sections to fulfill some purpose.
4400  // This could include making param between [0,1], and/or making
4401  // C1 continuity possible.
4402  if (makeC1Continuous) {
4403  // We assume here that there is already G1 continuity.
4404  // Just scale parameters to get C1.
4405  Base::Vector3d slope1 = bsp1->firstDerivativeAtParameter(bsp1->getLastParameter());
4406  Base::Vector3d slope2 = bsp2->firstDerivativeAtParameter(bsp2->getFirstParameter());
4407  // TODO: slope2 can technically be a zero vector
4408  // But that seems not possible unless the spline is trivial.
4409  // Prove or account for the possibility.
4410  double scale = slope2.Length() / slope1.Length();
4411  bsp2->scaleKnotsToBounds(0, scale * (bsp2->getLastParameter() - bsp2->getFirstParameter()));
4412  }
4413 
4414  // set up vectors for new poles, knots, mults
4415  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles1 = bsp1->getPoles();
4416  std::vector<double> weights1 = bsp1->getWeights();
4417  std::vector<double> knots1 = bsp1->getKnots();
4418  std::vector<int> mults1 = bsp1->getMultiplicities();
4419  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles2 = bsp2->getPoles();
4420  std::vector<double> weights2 = bsp2->getWeights();
4421  std::vector<double> knots2 = bsp2->getKnots();
4422  std::vector<int> mults2 = bsp2->getMultiplicities();
4423 
4424  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> newPoles(std::move(poles1));
4425  std::vector<double> newWeights(std::move(weights1));
4426  std::vector<double> newKnots(std::move(knots1));
4427  std::vector<int> newMults(std::move(mults1));
4428 
4429 
4430  poles2.erase(poles2.begin());
4431  if (makeC1Continuous)
4432  newPoles.erase(newPoles.end()-1);
4433  newPoles.insert(newPoles.end(),
4434  std::make_move_iterator(poles2.begin()),
4435  std::make_move_iterator(poles2.end()));
4436 
4437  // TODO: Weights might need to be scaled
4438  weights2.erase(weights2.begin());
