4439  if (makeC1Continuous)
4440  newWeights.erase(newWeights.end()-1);
4441  newWeights.insert(newWeights.end(),
4442  std::make_move_iterator(weights2.begin()),
4443  std::make_move_iterator(weights2.end()));
4444 
4445  // knots of the second spline come after all of the first
4446  double offset = newKnots.back() - knots2.front();
4447  knots2.erase(knots2.begin());
4448  for (auto& knot : knots2)
4449  knot += offset;
4450  newKnots.insert(newKnots.end(),
4451  std::make_move_iterator(knots2.begin()),
4452  std::make_move_iterator(knots2.end()));
4453 
4454  // end knots can have a multiplicity of (degree + 1)
4455  if (bsp1->getDegree() < newMults.back()) {
4456  if (makeC1Continuous) {
4457  newMults.back() = bsp1->getDegree()-1;
4458  }
4459  else {
4460  newMults.back() = bsp1->getDegree();
4461  }
4462  }
4463 
4464  mults2.erase(mults2.begin());
4465  newMults.insert(newMults.end(),
4466  std::make_move_iterator(mults2.begin()),
4467  std::make_move_iterator(mults2.end()));
4468 
4469  Part::GeomBSplineCurve* newSpline = new Part::GeomBSplineCurve(
4470  newPoles, newWeights, newKnots, newMults, bsp1->getDegree(), false, true);
4471 
4472  int newGeoId = addGeometry(newSpline);
4473 
4474  if (newGeoId < 0) {
4475  THROWM(ValueError, "Failed to create joined curve.");
4476  return -1;
4477  }
4478  else {
4479  exposeInternalGeometry(newGeoId);
4480  setConstruction(newGeoId, GeometryFacade::getConstruction(geo1));
4481 
4482  // TODO: transfer constraints on the non-connected ends
4483  auto otherPosId1 = (Sketcher::PointPos::start == posId1) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end
4484  : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4485  auto otherPosId2 = (Sketcher::PointPos::start == posId2) ? Sketcher::PointPos::end
4486  : Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4487 
4488  transferConstraints(geoId1, otherPosId1, newGeoId, PointPos::start, true);
4489  transferConstraints(geoId2, otherPosId2, newGeoId, PointPos::end, true);
4490 
4491  delGeometries({geoId1, geoId2});
4492  return 0;
4493  }
4494 
4495  return -1;
4496 }
4497 
4498 bool SketchObject::isExternalAllowed(App::Document* pDoc, App::DocumentObject* pObj,
4499  eReasonList* rsn) const
4500 {
4501  if (rsn)
4502  *rsn = rlAllowed;
4503 
4504  // Externals outside of the Document are NOT allowed
4505  if (this->getDocument() != pDoc) {
4506  if (rsn)
4507  *rsn = rlOtherDoc;
4508  return false;
4509  }
4510 
4511  // circular reference prevention
4512  try {
4513  if (!(this->testIfLinkDAGCompatible(pObj))) {
4514  if (rsn)
4515  *rsn = rlCircularReference;
4516  return false;
4517  }
4518  }
4519  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
4520  Base::Console().Warning(
4521  "Probably, there is a circular reference in the document. Error: %s\n", e.what());
4522  return true;// prohibiting this reference won't remove the problem anyway...
4523  }
4524 
4525 
4526  // Note: Checking for the body of the support doesn't work when the support are the three base
4527  // planes
4528  // App::DocumentObject *support = this->AttachmentSupport.getValue();
4529  Part::BodyBase* body_this = Part::BodyBase::findBodyOf(this);
4530  Part::BodyBase* body_obj = Part::BodyBase::findBodyOf(pObj);
4531  App::Part* part_this = App::Part::getPartOfObject(this);
4532  App::Part* part_obj = App::Part::getPartOfObject(pObj);
4533  if (part_this == part_obj) {// either in the same part, or in the root of document
4534  if (!body_this) {
4535  return true;
4536  }
4537  else if (body_this == body_obj) {
4538  return true;
4539  }
4540  else {
4541  if (rsn)
4542  *rsn = rlOtherBody;
4543  return false;
4544  }
4545  }
4546  else {
4547  // cross-part link. Disallow, should be done via shapebinders only
4548  if (rsn)
4549  *rsn = rlOtherPart;
4550  return false;
4551  }
4552 }
4553 
4554 bool SketchObject::isCarbonCopyAllowed(App::Document* pDoc, App::DocumentObject* pObj, bool& xinv,
4555  bool& yinv, eReasonList* rsn) const
4556 {
4557  if (rsn) {
4558  *rsn = rlAllowed;
4559  }
4560 
4561  std::string sketchArchType ("Sketcher::SketchObjectPython");
4562 
4563  // Only applicable to sketches
4564  if (pObj->getTypeId() != Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId()
4565  && sketchArchType != pObj->getTypeId().getName()) {
4566  if (rsn) {
4567  *rsn = rlNotASketch;
4568  }
4569  return false;
4570  }
4571 
4572 
4573  SketchObject* psObj = static_cast<SketchObject*>(pObj);
4574 
4575  // Sketches outside of the Document are NOT allowed
4576  if (this->getDocument() != pDoc) {
4577  if (rsn) {
4578  *rsn = rlOtherDoc;
4579  }
4580  return false;
4581  }
4582 
4583  // circular reference prevention
4584  try {
4585  if (!(this->testIfLinkDAGCompatible(pObj))) {
4586  if (rsn) {
4587  *rsn = rlCircularReference;
4588  }
4589  return false;
4590  }
4591  }
4592  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
4593  Base::Console().Warning(
4594  "Probably, there is a circular reference in the document. Error: %s\n", e.what());
4595  return true;// prohibiting this reference won't remove the problem anyway...
4596  }
4597 
4598 
4599  // Note: Checking for the body of the support doesn't work when the support are the three base
4600  // planes
4601  // App::DocumentObject *support = this->AttachmentSupport.getValue();
4602  Part::BodyBase* body_this = Part::BodyBase::findBodyOf(this);
4603  Part::BodyBase* body_obj = Part::BodyBase::findBodyOf(pObj);
4604  App::Part* part_this = App::Part::getPartOfObject(this);
4605  App::Part* part_obj = App::Part::getPartOfObject(pObj);
4606  if (part_this == part_obj) {// either in the same part, or in the root of document
4607  if (body_this) {
4608  if (body_this != body_obj) {
4609  if (!this->allowOtherBody) {
4610  if (rsn)
4611  *rsn = rlOtherBody;
4612  return false;
4613  }
4614  // if the original sketch has external geometry AND it is not in this body prevent
4615  // link
4616  else if (psObj->getExternalGeometryCount() > 2) {
4617  if (rsn)
4618  *rsn = rlOtherBodyWithLinks;
4619  return false;
4620  }
4621  }
4622  }
4623  }
4624  else {
4625  // cross-part relation. Disallow, should be done via shapebinders only
4626  if (rsn)
4627  *rsn = rlOtherPart;
4628  return false;
4629  }
4630 
4631 
4632  const Rotation& srot = psObj->Placement.getValue().getRotation();
4633  const Rotation& lrot = this->Placement.getValue().getRotation();
4634 
4635  Base::Vector3d snormal(0, 0, 1);
4636  Base::Vector3d sx(1, 0, 0);
4637  Base::Vector3d sy(0, 1, 0);
4638  srot.multVec(snormal, snormal);
4639  srot.multVec(sx, sx);
4640  srot.multVec(sy, sy);
4641 
4642  Base::Vector3d lnormal(0, 0, 1);
4643  Base::Vector3d lx(1, 0, 0);
4644  Base::Vector3d ly(0, 1, 0);
4645  lrot.multVec(lnormal, lnormal);
4646  lrot.multVec(lx, lx);
4647  lrot.multVec(ly, ly);
4648 
4649  double dot = snormal * lnormal;
4650  double dotx = sx * lx;
4651  double doty = sy * ly;
4652 
4653  // the planes of the sketches must be parallel
4654  if (!allowUnaligned && fabs(fabs(dot) - 1) > Precision::Confusion()) {
4655  if (rsn)
4656  *rsn = rlNonParallel;
4657  return false;
4658  }
4659 
4660  // the axis must be aligned
4661  if (!allowUnaligned
4662  && ((fabs(fabs(dotx) - 1) > Precision::Confusion())
4663  || (fabs(fabs(doty) - 1) > Precision::Confusion()))) {
4664  if (rsn)
4665  *rsn = rlAxesMisaligned;
4666  return false;
4667  }
4668 
4669 
4670  // the origins of the sketches must be aligned or be the same
4671  Base::Vector3d ddir =
4672  (psObj->Placement.getValue().getPosition() - this->Placement.getValue().getPosition())
4673  .Normalize();
4674 
4675  double alignment = ddir * lnormal;
4676 
4677  if (!allowUnaligned && (fabs(fabs(alignment) - 1) > Precision::Confusion())
4678  && (psObj->Placement.getValue().getPosition()
4679  != this->Placement.getValue().getPosition())) {
4680  if (rsn)
4681  *rsn = rlOriginsMisaligned;
4682  return false;
4683  }
4684 
4685  xinv = allowUnaligned ? false : (fabs(dotx - 1) > Precision::Confusion());
4686  yinv = allowUnaligned ? false : (fabs(doty - 1) > Precision::Confusion());
4687 
4688  return true;
4689 }
4690 
4691 int SketchObject::addSymmetric(const std::vector<int>& geoIdList, int refGeoId,
4692  Sketcher::PointPos refPosId /*=Sketcher::PointPos::none*/,
4693  bool addSymmetryConstraints /*= false*/)
4694 {
4695  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
4696  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
4697 
4698  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constrvals = this->Constraints.getValues();
4699  std::vector<Constraint*> newconstrVals(constrvals);
4700 
4701  std::map<int, int> geoIdMap;
4702  std::map<int, bool> isStartEndInverted;
4703 
4704  // Find out if reference is aligned with V or H axis,
4705  // if so we can keep Vertical and Horizontal constraints in the mirrored geometry.
4706  bool refIsLine = refPosId == Sketcher::PointPos::none;
4707  bool refIsAxisAligned = false;
4708  if (refGeoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis || refGeoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis || !refIsLine) {
4709  refIsAxisAligned = true;
4710  }
4711  else {
4712  for (auto* constr : constrvals) {
4713  if (constr->First == refGeoId
4714  && (constr->Type == Sketcher::Vertical || constr->Type == Sketcher::Horizontal)){
4715  refIsAxisAligned = true;
4716  }
4717  }
4718  }
4719 
4720  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> symgeos = getSymmetric(geoIdList, geoIdMap, isStartEndInverted, refGeoId, refPosId);
4721 
4722  {
4723  addGeometry(symgeos);
4724 
4725  for (auto* constr : constrvals) {
4726  // we look in the map, because we might have skipped internal alignment geometry
4727  auto fit = geoIdMap.find(constr->First);
4728 
4729  if (fit != geoIdMap.end()) {// if First of constraint is in geoIdList
4730  if (addSymmetryConstraints && constr->Type != Sketcher::InternalAlignment) {
4731  // if we are making symmetric constraints, then we don't want to copy all constraints
4732  continue;
4733  }
4734 
4735  if (constr->Second == GeoEnum::GeoUndef /*&& constr->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef*/) {
4736  if (refIsAxisAligned) {
4737  // in this case we want to keep the Vertical, Horizontal constraints
4738  // DistanceX ,and DistanceY constraints should also be possible to keep in
4739  // this case, but keeping them causes segfault, not sure why.
4740 
4741  if (constr->Type != Sketcher::DistanceX
4742  && constr->Type != Sketcher::DistanceY) {
4743  Constraint* constNew = constr->copy();
4744  constNew->Name = ""; // Make sure we don't have 2 constraint with same name.
4745  constNew->First = fit->second;
4746  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
4747  }
4748  }
4749  else if (constr->Type != Sketcher::DistanceX
4750  && constr->Type != Sketcher::DistanceY
4751  && constr->Type != Sketcher::Vertical
4752  && constr->Type != Sketcher::Horizontal) {
4753  // this includes all non-directional single GeoId constraints, as radius,
4754  // diameter, weight,...
4755 
4756  Constraint* constNew = constr->copy();
4757  constNew->Name = "";
4758  constNew->First = fit->second;
4759  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
4760  }
4761  }
4762  else {// other geoids intervene in this constraint
4763 
4764  auto sit = geoIdMap.find(constr->Second);
4765 
4766  if (sit != geoIdMap.end()) {// Second is also in the list
4767 
4768  if (constr->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
4769  if (constr->Type == Sketcher::Coincident
4770  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Perpendicular
4771  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Parallel
4772  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Tangent
4773  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Distance
4774  || constr->Type == Sketcher::Equal || constr->Type == Sketcher::Angle
4775  || constr->Type == Sketcher::PointOnObject
4776  || constr->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment) {
4777  Constraint* constNew = constr->copy();
4778  constNew->Name = "";
4779  constNew->First = fit->second;
4780  constNew->Second = sit->second;
4781  if (isStartEndInverted[constr->First]) {
4782  if (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
4783  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
4784  else if (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
4785  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4786  }
4787  if (isStartEndInverted[constr->Second]) {
4788  if (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
4789  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
4790  else if (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
4791  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4792  }
4793 
4794  if (constNew->Type == Tangent || constNew->Type == Perpendicular)
4795  AutoLockTangencyAndPerpty(constNew, true);
4796 
4797  if ((constr->Type == Sketcher::Angle)
4798  && (refPosId == Sketcher::PointPos::none)) {
4799  constNew->setValue(-constr->getValue());
4800  }
4801 
4802  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
4803  }
4804  }
4805  else {// three GeoIds intervene in constraint
4806  auto tit = geoIdMap.find(constr->Third);
4807 
4808  if (tit != geoIdMap.end()) {// Third is also in the list
4809  Constraint* constNew = constr->copy();
4810  constNew->Name = "";
4811  constNew->First = fit->second;
4812  constNew->Second = sit->second;
4813  constNew->Third = tit->second;
4814  if (isStartEndInverted[constr->First]) {
4815  if (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
4816  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
4817  else if (constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
4818  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4819  }
4820  if (isStartEndInverted[constr->Second]) {
4821  if (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
4822  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
4823  else if (constr->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
4824  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4825  }
4826  if (isStartEndInverted[constr->Third]) {
4827  if (constr->ThirdPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
4828  constNew->ThirdPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
4829  else if (constr->ThirdPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
4830  constNew->ThirdPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4831  }
4832  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
4833  }
4834  }
4835  }
4836  }
4837  }
4838  }
4839 
4840  if (addSymmetryConstraints) {
4841  auto createSymConstr = [&]
4842  (int first, int second, Sketcher::PointPos firstPos, Sketcher::PointPos secondPos) {
4843  auto symConstr = new Constraint();
4844  symConstr->Type = Symmetric;
4845  symConstr->First = first;
4846  symConstr->Second = second;
4847  symConstr->Third = refGeoId;
4848  symConstr->FirstPos = firstPos;
4849  symConstr->SecondPos = secondPos;
4850  symConstr->ThirdPos = refPosId;
4851  newconstrVals.push_back(symConstr);
4852  };
4853  auto createEqualityConstr = [&]
4854  (int first, int second) {
4855  auto symConstr = new Constraint();
4856  symConstr->Type = Equal;
4857  symConstr->First = first;
4858  symConstr->Second = second;
4859  newconstrVals.push_back(symConstr);
4860  };
4861 
4862  for (auto geoIdPair : geoIdMap) {
4863  int geoId1 = geoIdPair.first;
4864  int geoId2 = geoIdPair.second;
4865  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(geoId1);
4866 
4867  if (geo->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
4868  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
4869  if (!gf->isInternalAligned()) {
4870  // Note internal aligned lines (ellipse, parabola, hyperbola) are causing redundant constraint.
4871  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::start, isStartEndInverted[geoId1] ? PointPos::end : PointPos::start);
4872  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::end, isStartEndInverted[geoId1] ? PointPos::start : PointPos::end);
4873  }
4874  }
4875  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>() || geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
4876  createEqualityConstr(geoId1, geoId2);
4877  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::mid, PointPos::mid);
4878  }
4879  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()
4880  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()
4881  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()
4882  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
4883  createEqualityConstr(geoId1, geoId2);
4884  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::start, isStartEndInverted[geoId1] ? PointPos::end : PointPos::start);
4885  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::end, isStartEndInverted[geoId1] ? PointPos::start : PointPos::end);
4886  }
4887  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
4888  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
4889  if (!gf->isInternalAligned()) {
4890  createSymConstr(geoId1, geoId2, PointPos::start, PointPos::start);
4891  }
4892  }
4893  // Note bspline has symmetric by the internal aligned circles.
4894  }
4895  }
4896 
4897  if (newconstrVals.size() > constrvals.size()){
4898  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newconstrVals));
4899  }
4900  }
4901 
4902  // we delayed update, so trigger it now.
4903  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
4904  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
4905  Geometry.touch();
4906 
4907  return Geometry.getSize() - 1;
4908 }
4909 
4910 
4911 std::vector<Part::Geometry*> SketchObject::getSymmetric(const std::vector<int>& geoIdList,
4912  std::map<int, int>& geoIdMap,
4913  std::map<int, bool>& isStartEndInverted,
4914  int refGeoId,
4915  Sketcher::PointPos refPosId)
4916 {
4917  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> symmetricVals;
4918  bool refIsLine = refPosId == Sketcher::PointPos::none;
4919  int cgeoid = getHighestCurveIndex() + 1;
4920 
4921  auto shouldCopyGeometry = [&](auto* geo, int geoId) -> bool {
4922  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
4923  if (gf->isInternalAligned()) {
4924  // only add if the corresponding geometry it defines is also in the list.
4925  int definedGeo = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
4926  for (auto c : Constraints.getValues()) {
4927  if (c->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && c->First == geoId) {
4928  definedGeo = c->Second;
4929  break;
4930  }
4931  }
4932  // Return true if definedGeo is in geoIdList, false otherwise
4933  return std::find(geoIdList.begin(), geoIdList.end(), definedGeo) != geoIdList.end();
4934  }
4935  // Return true if not internal aligned, indicating it should always be copied
4936  return true;
4937  };
4938 
4939  if (refIsLine) {
4940  const Part::Geometry* georef = getGeometry(refGeoId);
4941  if (!georef->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
4942  return {};
4943  }
4944 
4945  auto* refGeoLine = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(georef);
4946  // line
4947  Base::Vector3d refstart = refGeoLine->getStartPoint();
4948  Base::Vector3d vectline = refGeoLine->getEndPoint() - refstart;
4949 
4950  for (auto geoId : geoIdList) {
4951  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(geoId);
4952  Part::Geometry* geosym;
4953 
4954  if (!shouldCopyGeometry(geo, geoId)) {
4955  continue;
4956  }
4957 
4958  geosym = geo->copy();
4959 
4960  // Handle Geometry
4961  if (geosym->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
4962  auto* geosymline = static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geosym);
4963  Base::Vector3d sp = geosymline->getStartPoint();
4964  Base::Vector3d ep = geosymline->getEndPoint();
4965 
4966  geosymline->setPoints(
4967  sp + 2.0 * (sp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - sp),
4968  ep + 2.0 * (ep.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - ep));
4969  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
4970  }
4971  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
4972  auto* geosymcircle = static_cast<Part::GeomCircle*>(geosym);
4973  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymcircle->getCenter();
4974 
4975  geosymcircle->setCenter(
4976  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp));
4977  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
4978  }
4979  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
4980  auto* geoaoc = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geosym);
4981  Base::Vector3d sp = geoaoc->getStartPoint(true);
4982  Base::Vector3d ep = geoaoc->getEndPoint(true);
4983  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoc->getCenter();
4984 
4985  Base::Vector3d ssp =
4986  sp + 2.0 * (sp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - sp);
4987  Base::Vector3d sep =
4988  ep + 2.0 * (ep.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - ep);
4989  Base::Vector3d scp =
4990  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp);
4991 
4992  double theta1 = Base::fmod(atan2(sep.y - scp.y, sep.x - scp.x), 2.f * M_PI);
4993  double theta2 = Base::fmod(atan2(ssp.y - scp.y, ssp.x - scp.x), 2.f * M_PI);
4994 
4995  geoaoc->setCenter(scp);
4996  geoaoc->setRange(theta1, theta2, true);
4997  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, true));
4998  }
4999  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
5000  auto* geosymellipse = static_cast<Part::GeomEllipse*>(geosym);
5001  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymellipse->getCenter();
5002 
5003  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymellipse->getMajorAxisDir();
5004  double majord = geosymellipse->getMajorRadius();
5005  double minord = geosymellipse->getMinorRadius();
5006  double df = sqrt(majord * majord - minord * minord);
5007  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5008 
5009  Base::Vector3d sf1 =
5010  f1 + 2.0 * (f1.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - f1);
5011  Base::Vector3d scp =
5012  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp);
5013 
5014  geosymellipse->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5015 
5016  geosymellipse->setCenter(scp);
5017  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5018  }
5019  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
5020  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geosym);
5021  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5022 
5023  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymaoe->getMajorAxisDir();
5024  double majord = geosymaoe->getMajorRadius();
5025  double minord = geosymaoe->getMinorRadius();
5026  double df = sqrt(majord * majord - minord * minord);
5027  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5028 
5029  Base::Vector3d sf1 =
5030  f1 + 2.0 * (f1.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - f1);
5031  Base::Vector3d scp =
5032  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp);
5033 
5034  geosymaoe->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5035 
5036  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5037 
5038  double theta1, theta2;
5039  geosymaoe->getRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5040  theta1 = 2.0 * M_PI - theta1;
5041  theta2 = 2.0 * M_PI - theta2;
5042  std::swap(theta1, theta2);
5043  if (theta1 < 0) {
5044  theta1 += 2.0 * M_PI;
5045  theta2 += 2.0 * M_PI;
5046  }
5047 
5048  geosymaoe->setRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5049  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, true));
5050  }
5051  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
5052  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geosym);
5053  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5054 
5055  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymaoe->getMajorAxisDir();
5056  double majord = geosymaoe->getMajorRadius();
5057  double minord = geosymaoe->getMinorRadius();
5058  double df = sqrt(majord * majord + minord * minord);
5059  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5060 
5061  Base::Vector3d sf1 =
5062  f1 + 2.0 * (f1.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - f1);
5063  Base::Vector3d scp =
5064  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp);
5065 
5066  geosymaoe->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5067 
5068  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5069 
5070  double theta1, theta2;
5071  geosymaoe->getRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5072  theta1 = -theta1;
5073  theta2 = -theta2;
5074  std::swap(theta1, theta2);
5075 
5076  geosymaoe->setRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5077  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, true));
5078  }
5079  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
5080  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geosym);
5081  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5082 
5083  Base::Vector3d f1 = geosymaoe->getFocus();
5084 
5085  Base::Vector3d sf1 =
5086  f1 + 2.0 * (f1.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - f1);
5087  Base::Vector3d scp =
5088  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp);
5089 
5090  geosymaoe->setXAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5091  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5092 
5093  double theta1, theta2;
5094  geosymaoe->getRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5095  theta1 = -theta1;
5096  theta2 = -theta2;
5097  std::swap(theta1, theta2);
5098 
5099  geosymaoe->setRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5100  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, true));
5101  }
5102  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
5103  auto* geosymbsp = static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geosym);
5104 
5105  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = geosymbsp->getPoles();
5106 
5107  for (auto& pole : poles) {
5108  pole = pole
5109  + 2.0 * (pole.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - pole);
5110  }
5111 
5112  geosymbsp->setPoles(poles);
5113 
5114  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5115  }
5116  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
5117  auto* geosympoint = static_cast<Part::GeomPoint*>(geosym);
5118  Base::Vector3d cp = geosympoint->getPoint();
5119 
5120  geosympoint->setPoint(
5121  cp + 2.0 * (cp.Perpendicular(refGeoLine->getStartPoint(), vectline) - cp));
5122  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5123  }
5124  else {
5125  Base::Console().Error("Unsupported Geometry!! Just copying it.\n");
5126  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5127  }
5128 
5129  symmetricVals.push_back(geosym);
5130  geoIdMap.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, cgeoid));
5131  cgeoid++;
5132  }
5133  }
5134  else {// reference is a point
5135  Vector3d refpoint;
5136  const Part::Geometry* georef = getGeometry(refGeoId);
5137 
5138  if (georef->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
5139  refpoint = static_cast<const Part::GeomPoint*>(georef)->getPoint();
5140  }
5141  else if (refGeoId == -1 && refPosId == Sketcher::PointPos::start) {
5142  refpoint = Vector3d(0, 0, 0);
5143  }
5144  else {
5145  if (refPosId == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5146  Base::Console().Error("Wrong PointPosId.\n");
5147  return {};
5148  }
5149  refpoint = getPoint(georef, refPosId);
5150  }
5151 
5152  for (auto geoId : geoIdList) {
5153  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(geoId);
5154  Part::Geometry* geosym;
5155 
5156  if (!shouldCopyGeometry(geo, geoId)) {
5157  continue;
5158  }
5159 
5160  geosym = geo->copy();
5161 
5162  // Handle Geometry
5163  if (geosym->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
5164  auto* geosymline = static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geosym);
5165  Base::Vector3d sp = geosymline->getStartPoint();
5166  Base::Vector3d ep = geosymline->getEndPoint();
5167  Base::Vector3d ssp = sp + 2.0 * (refpoint - sp);
5168  Base::Vector3d sep = ep + 2.0 * (refpoint - ep);
5169 
5170  geosymline->setPoints(ssp, sep);
5171  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5172  }
5173  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
5174  auto* geosymcircle = static_cast<Part::GeomCircle*>(geosym);
5175  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymcircle->getCenter();
5176 
5177  geosymcircle->setCenter(cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp));
5178  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5179  }
5180  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
5181  auto* geoaoc = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geosym);
5182  Base::Vector3d sp = geoaoc->getStartPoint(true);
5183  Base::Vector3d ep = geoaoc->getEndPoint(true);
5184  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoc->getCenter();
5185 
5186  Base::Vector3d ssp = sp + 2.0 * (refpoint - sp);
5187  Base::Vector3d sep = ep + 2.0 * (refpoint - ep);
5188  Base::Vector3d scp = cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp);
5189 
5190  double theta1 = Base::fmod(atan2(ssp.y - scp.y, ssp.x - scp.x), 2.f * M_PI);
5191  double theta2 = Base::fmod(atan2(sep.y - scp.y, sep.x - scp.x), 2.f * M_PI);
5192 
5193  geoaoc->setCenter(scp);
5194  geoaoc->setRange(theta1, theta2, true);
5195  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5196  }
5197  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
5198  auto* geosymellipse = static_cast<Part::GeomEllipse*>(geosym);
5199  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymellipse->getCenter();
5200 
5201  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymellipse->getMajorAxisDir();
5202  double majord = geosymellipse->getMajorRadius();
5203  double minord = geosymellipse->getMinorRadius();
5204  double df = sqrt(majord * majord - minord * minord);
5205  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5206 
5207  Base::Vector3d sf1 = f1 + 2.0 * (refpoint - f1);
5208  Base::Vector3d scp = cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp);
5209 
5210  geosymellipse->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5211 
5212  geosymellipse->setCenter(scp);
5213  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5214  }
5215  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
5216  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geosym);
5217  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5218 
5219  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymaoe->getMajorAxisDir();
5220  double majord = geosymaoe->getMajorRadius();
5221  double minord = geosymaoe->getMinorRadius();
5222  double df = sqrt(majord * majord - minord * minord);
5223  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5224 
5225  Base::Vector3d sf1 = f1 + 2.0 * (refpoint - f1);
5226  Base::Vector3d scp = cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp);
5227 
5228  geosymaoe->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5229 
5230  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5231  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5232  }
5233  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
5234  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geosym);
5235  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5236 
5237  Base::Vector3d majdir = geosymaoe->getMajorAxisDir();
5238  double majord = geosymaoe->getMajorRadius();
5239  double minord = geosymaoe->getMinorRadius();
5240  double df = sqrt(majord * majord + minord * minord);
5241  Base::Vector3d f1 = cp + df * majdir;
5242 
5243  Base::Vector3d sf1 = f1 + 2.0 * (refpoint - f1);
5244  Base::Vector3d scp = cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp);
5245 
5246  geosymaoe->setMajorAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5247 
5248  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5249  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5250  }
5251  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
5252  auto* geosymaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geosym);
5253  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymaoe->getCenter();
5254 
5255  /*double df= geosymaoe->getFocal();*/
5256  Base::Vector3d f1 = geosymaoe->getFocus();
5257 
5258  Base::Vector3d sf1 = f1 + 2.0 * (refpoint - f1);
5259  Base::Vector3d scp = cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp);
5260 
5261  geosymaoe->setXAxisDir(sf1 - scp);
5262  geosymaoe->setCenter(scp);
5263 
5264  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5265  }
5266  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
5267  auto* geosymbsp = static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geosym);
5268 
5269  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = geosymbsp->getPoles();
5270 
5271  for (auto& pole : poles) {
5272  pole = pole + 2.0 * (refpoint - pole);
5273  }
5274 
5275  geosymbsp->setPoles(poles);
5276 
5277  }
5278  else if (geosym->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
5279  auto* geosympoint = static_cast<Part::GeomPoint*>(geosym);
5280  Base::Vector3d cp = geosympoint->getPoint();
5281 
5282  geosympoint->setPoint(cp + 2.0 * (refpoint - cp));
5283  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5284  }
5285  else {
5286  Base::Console().Error("Unsupported Geometry!! Just copying it.\n");
5287  isStartEndInverted.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, false));
5288  }
5289 
5290  symmetricVals.push_back(geosym);
5291  geoIdMap.insert(std::make_pair(geoId, cgeoid));
5292  cgeoid++;
5293  }
5294  }
5295  return symmetricVals;
5296 }
5297 
5298 int SketchObject::addCopy(const std::vector<int>& geoIdList, const Base::Vector3d& displacement,
5299  bool moveonly /*=false*/, bool clone /*=false*/, int csize /*=2*/,
5300  int rsize /*=1*/, bool constraindisplacement /*= false*/,
5301  double perpscale /*= 1.0*/)
5302 {
5303  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
5304  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
5305 
5306  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& geovals = getInternalGeometry();
5307  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newgeoVals(geovals);
5308 
5309  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constrvals = this->Constraints.getValues();
5310  std::vector<Constraint*> newconstrVals(constrvals);
5311 
5312  if (!moveonly) {
5313  newgeoVals.reserve(geovals.size() + geoIdList.size());
5314  }
5315 
5316  std::vector<int> newgeoIdList(geoIdList);
5317 
5318  if (newgeoIdList.empty()) {// default option to operate on all the geometry
5319  for (int i = 0; i < int(geovals.size()); i++)
5320  newgeoIdList.push_back(i);
5321  }
5322 
5323  int cgeoid = getHighestCurveIndex() + 1;
5324 
5325  int iterfirstgeoid = -1;
5326 
5327  Base::Vector3d iterfirstpoint;
5328 
5329  int refgeoid = -1;
5330 
5331  int colrefgeoid = 0, rowrefgeoid = 0;
5332 
5333  int currentrowfirstgeoid = -1, prevrowstartfirstgeoid = -1, prevfirstgeoid = -1;
5334 
5335  Sketcher::PointPos refposId = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5336 
5337  std::map<int, int> geoIdMap;
5338 
5339  Base::Vector3d perpendicularDisplacement =
5340  Base::Vector3d(perpscale * displacement.y, perpscale * -displacement.x, 0);
5341 
5342  int x, y;
5343 
5344  for (y = 0; y < rsize; y++) {
5345  for (x = 0; x < csize; x++) {
5346  // the reference for constraining array elements is the first valid point of the first
5347  // element
5348  if (x == 0 && y == 0) {
5349  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(*(newgeoIdList.begin()));
5350 
5351  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
5352 
5353  if (gf->isInternalAligned() && !moveonly) {
5354  // only add this geometry if the corresponding geometry it defines is also in
5355  // the list.
5356  int definedGeo = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5357 
5358  for (auto c : Constraints.getValues()) {
5359  if (c->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment
5360  && c->First == *(newgeoIdList.begin())) {
5361  definedGeo = c->Second;
5362  break;
5363  }
5364  }
5365 
5366  if (std::find(newgeoIdList.begin(), newgeoIdList.end(), definedGeo)
5367  == newgeoIdList.end()) {
5368  // the first element setting the reference is an internal alignment
5369  // geometry, wherein the geometry it defines is not part of the copy
5370  // operation.
5371  THROWM(Base::ValueError,
5372  "A move/copy/array operation on an internal alignment geometry is "
5373  "only possible together with the geometry it defines.")
5374  }
5375  }
5376 
5377  refgeoid = *(newgeoIdList.begin());
5378  currentrowfirstgeoid = refgeoid;
5379  iterfirstgeoid = refgeoid;
5380  if (geo->is<Part::GeomCircle>()
5381  || geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
5382  refposId = Sketcher::PointPos::mid;
5383  }
5384  else
5385  refposId = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5386 
5387  continue;// the first element is already in place
5388  }
5389  else {
5390  prevfirstgeoid = iterfirstgeoid;
5391 
5392  iterfirstgeoid = cgeoid;
5393 
5394  if (x == 0) {// if first element of second row
5395  prevrowstartfirstgeoid = currentrowfirstgeoid;
5396  currentrowfirstgeoid = cgeoid;
5397  }
5398  }
5399 
5400  int index = 0;
5401  for (std::vector<int>::const_iterator it = newgeoIdList.begin();
5402  it != newgeoIdList.end();
5403  ++it, index++) {
5404  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(*it);
5405 
5406  Part::Geometry* geocopy;
5407 
5408  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
5409 
5410  if (gf->isInternalAligned() && !moveonly) {
5411  // only add this geometry if the corresponding geometry it defines is also in
5412  // the list.
5413  int definedGeo = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5414 
5415  for (auto c : Constraints.getValues()) {
5416  if (c->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && c->First == *it) {
5417  definedGeo = c->Second;
5418  break;
5419  }
5420  }
5421 
5422  if (std::find(newgeoIdList.begin(), newgeoIdList.end(), definedGeo)
5423  == newgeoIdList.end()) {
5424  // we should not copy internal alignment geometry, unless the element they
5425  // define is also mirrored
5426  continue;
5427  }
5428  }
5429 
5430  // We have already cloned all geometry and constraints, we only need a copy if not
5431  // moving
5432  if (!moveonly) {
5433  geocopy = geo->copy();
5434  generateId(geocopy);
5435  } else
5436  geocopy = newgeoVals[*it];
5437 
5438  // Handle Geometry
5439  if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
5440  Part::GeomLineSegment* geosymline =
5441  static_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geocopy);
5442  Base::Vector3d ep = geosymline->getEndPoint();
5443  Base::Vector3d ssp = geosymline->getStartPoint() + double(x) * displacement
5444  + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5445 
5446  geosymline->setPoints(
5447  ssp, ep + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement);
5448 
5449  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5450  iterfirstpoint = ssp;
5451  }
5452  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
5453  Part::GeomCircle* geosymcircle = static_cast<Part::GeomCircle*>(geocopy);
5454  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymcircle->getCenter();
5455  Base::Vector3d scp =
5456  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5457 
5458  geosymcircle->setCenter(scp);
5459 
5460  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5461  iterfirstpoint = scp;
5462  }
5463  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
5464  Part::GeomArcOfCircle* geoaoc = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geocopy);
5465  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoc->getCenter();
5466  Base::Vector3d scp =
5467  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5468 
5469  geoaoc->setCenter(scp);
5470 
5471  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5472  iterfirstpoint = geoaoc->getStartPoint(true);
5473  }
5474  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
5475  Part::GeomEllipse* geosymellipse = static_cast<Part::GeomEllipse*>(geocopy);
5476  Base::Vector3d cp = geosymellipse->getCenter();
5477  Base::Vector3d scp =
5478  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5479 
5480  geosymellipse->setCenter(scp);
5481 
5482  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5483  iterfirstpoint = scp;
5484  }
5485  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
5486  Part::GeomArcOfEllipse* geoaoe = static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geocopy);
5487  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoe->getCenter();
5488  Base::Vector3d scp =
5489  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5490 
5491  geoaoe->setCenter(scp);
5492 
5493  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5494  iterfirstpoint = geoaoe->getStartPoint(true);
5495  }
5496  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
5497  Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola* geoaoe =
5498  static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geocopy);
5499  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoe->getCenter();
5500  Base::Vector3d scp =
5501  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5502 
5503  geoaoe->setCenter(scp);
5504 
5505  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5506  iterfirstpoint = geoaoe->getStartPoint(true);
5507  }
5508  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
5509  Part::GeomArcOfParabola* geoaoe =
5510  static_cast<Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geocopy);
5511  Base::Vector3d cp = geoaoe->getCenter();
5512  Base::Vector3d scp =
5513  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5514 
5515  geoaoe->setCenter(scp);
5516 
5517  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5518  iterfirstpoint = geoaoe->getStartPoint(true);
5519  }
5520  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
5521  Part::GeomBSplineCurve* geobsp = static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geocopy);
5522 
5523  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = geobsp->getPoles();
5524 
5525  for (std::vector<Base::Vector3d>::iterator jt = poles.begin();
5526  jt != poles.end();
5527  ++jt) {
5528 
5529  (*jt) = (*jt) + double(x) * displacement
5530  + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5531  }
5532 
5533  geobsp->setPoles(poles);
5534 
5535  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5536  iterfirstpoint = geobsp->getStartPoint();
5537  }
5538  else if (geocopy->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
5539  Part::GeomPoint* geopoint = static_cast<Part::GeomPoint*>(geocopy);
5540  Base::Vector3d cp = geopoint->getPoint();
5541  Base::Vector3d scp =
5542  cp + double(x) * displacement + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement;
5543  geopoint->setPoint(scp);
5544 
5545  if (it == newgeoIdList.begin())
5546  iterfirstpoint = scp;
5547  }
5548  else {
5549  Base::Console().Error("Unsupported Geometry!! Just skipping it.\n");
5550  continue;
5551  }
5552 
5553  if (!moveonly) {// we are copying
5554  newgeoVals.push_back(geocopy);
5555  geoIdMap.insert(std::make_pair(*it, cgeoid));
5556  cgeoid++;
5557  }
5558  }
5559 
5560  if (!moveonly) {
5561  // handle geometry constraints
5562  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constrvals.begin();
5563  it != constrvals.end();
5564  ++it) {
5565 
5566  auto fit = geoIdMap.find((*it)->First);
5567 
5568  if (fit != geoIdMap.end()) {// if First of constraint is in geoIdList
5569 
5570  if ((*it)->Second
5571  == GeoEnum::GeoUndef /*&& (*it)->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef*/) {
5572  if (((*it)->Type != Sketcher::DistanceX
5573  && (*it)->Type != Sketcher::DistanceY)
5574  || (*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5575  // if it is not a point locking DistanceX/Y
5576  if (((*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceX
5577  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceY
5578  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Distance
5579  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Diameter
5580  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Weight
5581  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Radius)
5582  && clone) {
5583  // Distances on a single Element are mapped to equality
5584  // constraints in clone mode
5585  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5586  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
5587  constNew->isDriving = true;
5588  // first is already (*it->First)
5589  constNew->Second = fit->second;
5590  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5591  }
5592  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Angle && clone) {
5593  if (getGeometry((*it)->First)->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
5594  // Angles on a single Element are mapped to parallel
5595  // constraints in clone mode
5596  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5597  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Parallel;
5598  constNew->isDriving = true;
5599  // first is already (*it->First)
5600  constNew->Second = fit->second;
5601  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5602  }
5603  }
5604  else {
5605  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5606  constNew->First = fit->second;
5607  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5608  }
5609  }
5610  }
5611  else {// other geoids intervene in this constraint
5612 
5613  auto sit = geoIdMap.find((*it)->Second);
5614 
5615  if (sit != geoIdMap.end()) {// Second is also in the list
5616  if ((*it)->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5617  if (((*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceX
5618  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::DistanceY
5619  || (*it)->Type == Sketcher::Distance)
5620  && ((*it)->First == (*it)->Second) && clone) {
5621  // Distances on a two Elements, which must be points of the
5622  // same line are mapped to equality constraints in clone
5623  // mode
5624  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5625  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
5626  constNew->isDriving = true;
5627  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5628  // first is already (*it->First)
5629  constNew->Second = fit->second;
5630  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5631  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5632  }
5633  else {// this includes InternalAlignment constraints
5634  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5635  constNew->First = fit->second;
5636  constNew->Second = sit->second;
5637  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5638  }
5639  }
5640  else {
5641  auto tit = geoIdMap.find((*it)->Third);
5642 
5643  if (tit != geoIdMap.end()) {// Third is also in the list
5644  Constraint* constNew = (*it)->copy();
5645  constNew->First = fit->second;
5646  constNew->Second = sit->second;
5647  constNew->Third = tit->second;
5648 
5649  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5650  }
5651  }
5652  }
5653  }
5654  }
5655  }
5656 
5657  // handle inter-geometry constraints
5658  if (constraindisplacement) {
5659 
5660  // add a construction line
5661  Part::GeomLineSegment* constrline = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
5662 
5663  // position of the reference point
5664  Base::Vector3d sp = getPoint(refgeoid, refposId)
5665  + ((x == 0) ? (double(x) * displacement
5666  + double(y - 1) * perpendicularDisplacement)
5667  : (double(x - 1) * displacement
5668  + double(y) * perpendicularDisplacement));
5669 
5670  // position of the current instance corresponding point
5671  Base::Vector3d ep = iterfirstpoint;
5672  constrline->setPoints(sp, ep);
5673  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(constrline, true);
5674 
5675  generateId(constrline);
5676  newgeoVals.push_back(constrline);
5677 
5678  Constraint* constNew;
5679 
5680  if (x == 0) {// first element of a row
5681 
5682  // add coincidents for construction line
5683  constNew = new Constraint();
5684  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
5685  constNew->First = prevrowstartfirstgeoid;
5686  constNew->FirstPos = refposId;
5687  constNew->Second = cgeoid;
5688  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5689  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5690 
5691  constNew = new Constraint();
5692  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
5693  constNew->First = iterfirstgeoid;
5694  constNew->FirstPos = refposId;
5695  constNew->Second = cgeoid;
5696  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
5697  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5698 
5699  // it is the first added element of this row in the perpendicular to
5700  // displacementvector direction
5701  if (y == 1) {
5702  rowrefgeoid = cgeoid;
5703  cgeoid++;
5704 
5705  // add length (or equal if perpscale==1) and perpendicular
5706  if (perpscale == 1.0) {
5707  constNew = new Constraint();
5708  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
5709  constNew->First = rowrefgeoid;
5710  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5711  constNew->Second = colrefgeoid;
5712  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5713  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5714  }
5715  else {
5716  constNew = new Constraint();
5717  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Distance;
5718  constNew->First = rowrefgeoid;
5719  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5720  constNew->setValue(perpendicularDisplacement.Length());
5721  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5722  }
5723 
5724  constNew = new Constraint();
5725  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Perpendicular;
5726  constNew->First = rowrefgeoid;
5727  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5728  constNew->Second = colrefgeoid;
5729  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5730  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5731  }
5732  else {// it is just one more element in the col direction
5733  cgeoid++;
5734 
5735  // all other first rowers get an equality and perpendicular constraint
5736  constNew = new Constraint();
5737  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
5738  constNew->First = rowrefgeoid;
5739  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5740  constNew->Second = cgeoid - 1;
5741  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5742  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5743 
5744  constNew = new Constraint();
5745  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Perpendicular;
5746  constNew->First = cgeoid - 1;
5747  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5748  constNew->Second = colrefgeoid;
5749  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5750  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5751  }
5752  }
5753  else {// any element not being the first element of a row
5754 
5755  // add coincidents for construction line
5756  constNew = new Constraint();
5757  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
5758  constNew->First = prevfirstgeoid;
5759  constNew->FirstPos = refposId;
5760  constNew->Second = cgeoid;
5761  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5762  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5763 
5764  constNew = new Constraint();
5765  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Coincident;
5766  constNew->First = iterfirstgeoid;
5767  constNew->FirstPos = refposId;
5768  constNew->Second = cgeoid;
5769  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
5770  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5771 
5772  if (y == 0 && x == 1) {// first element of the first row
5773  colrefgeoid = cgeoid;
5774  cgeoid++;
5775 
5776  // add length and Angle
5777  constNew = new Constraint();
5778  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Distance;
5779  constNew->First = colrefgeoid;
5780  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5781  constNew->setValue(displacement.Length());
5782  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5783 
5784  constNew = new Constraint();
5785  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Angle;
5786  constNew->First = colrefgeoid;
5787  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5788  constNew->setValue(atan2(displacement.y, displacement.x));
5789  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5790  }
5791  else {// any other element
5792  cgeoid++;
5793 
5794  // all other elements get an equality and parallel constraint
5795  constNew = new Constraint();
5796  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
5797  constNew->First = colrefgeoid;
5798  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5799  constNew->Second = cgeoid - 1;
5800  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5801  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5802 
5803  constNew = new Constraint();
5804  constNew->Type = Sketcher::Parallel;
5805  constNew->First = cgeoid - 1;
5806  constNew->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5807  constNew->Second = colrefgeoid;
5808  constNew->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5809  newconstrVals.push_back(constNew);
5810  }
5811  }
5812  }
5813  // after each creation reset map so that the key-value is univoque (only for
5814  // operations other than move)
5815  geoIdMap.clear();
5816  }
5817  }
5818  }
5819 
5820  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
5821  {
5822  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
5823  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newgeoVals));
5824 
5825  if (newconstrVals.size() > constrvals.size())
5826  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newconstrVals));
5827  }
5828 
5829  // we inhibited update, so we trigger it now
5830  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
5831  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
5832  Geometry.touch();
5833 
5834  return Geometry.getSize() - 1;
5835 }
5836 
5837 
5838 int SketchObject::removeAxesAlignment(const std::vector<int>& geoIdList)
5839 {
5840  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
5841  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
5842 
5843  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constrvals = this->Constraints.getValues();
5844 
5845  unsigned int nhoriz = 0;
5846  unsigned int nvert = 0;
5847 
5848  bool changed = false;
5849 
5850  std::vector<std::pair<size_t, Sketcher::ConstraintType>> changeConstraintIndices;
5851 
5852  for (size_t i = 0; i < constrvals.size(); i++) {
5853  for (auto geoid : geoIdList) {
5854  if (constrvals[i]->First == geoid || constrvals[i]->Second == geoid
5855  || constrvals[i]->Third == geoid) {
5856  switch (constrvals[i]->Type) {
5857  case Sketcher::Horizontal:
5858  if (constrvals[i]->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none
5859  && constrvals[i]->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5860  changeConstraintIndices.emplace_back(i, constrvals[i]->Type);
5861  nhoriz++;
5862  }
5863  break;
5864  case Sketcher::Vertical:
5865  if (constrvals[i]->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none
5866  && constrvals[i]->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5867  changeConstraintIndices.emplace_back(i, constrvals[i]->Type);
5868  nvert++;
5869  }
5870  break;
5871  case Sketcher::Symmetric:// only remove symmetric to axes
5872  if ((constrvals[i]->Third == GeoEnum::HAxis
5873  || constrvals[i]->Third == GeoEnum::VAxis)
5874  && constrvals[i]->ThirdPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none)
5875  changeConstraintIndices.emplace_back(i, constrvals[i]->Type);
5876  break;
5877  case Sketcher::PointOnObject:
5878  if ((constrvals[i]->Second == GeoEnum::HAxis
5879  || constrvals[i]->Second == GeoEnum::VAxis)
5880  && constrvals[i]->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none)
5881  changeConstraintIndices.emplace_back(i, constrvals[i]->Type);
5882  break;
5883  case Sketcher::DistanceX:
5884  case Sketcher::DistanceY:
5885  changeConstraintIndices.emplace_back(i, constrvals[i]->Type);
5886  break;
5887  default:
5888  break;
5889  }
5890  }
5891  }
5892  }
5893 
5894  if (changeConstraintIndices.empty())
5895  return 0;// nothing to be done
5896 
5897  std::vector<Constraint*> newconstrVals;
5898  newconstrVals.reserve(constrvals.size());
5899 
5900  int referenceHorizontal = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5901  int referenceVertical = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5902 
5903  int cindex = 0;
5904  for (size_t i = 0; i < constrvals.size(); i++) {
5905  if (i == changeConstraintIndices[cindex].first) {
5906  if (changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::Horizontal && nhoriz > 0) {
5907  changed = true;
5908  if (referenceHorizontal == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5909  referenceHorizontal = constrvals[i]->First;
5910  }
5911  else {
5912 
5913  auto newConstr = new Constraint();
5914 
5915  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Parallel;
5916  newConstr->First = referenceHorizontal;
5917  newConstr->Second = constrvals[i]->First;
5918 
5919  newconstrVals.push_back(newConstr);
5920  }
5921  }
5922  else if (changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::Vertical && nvert > 0) {
5923  changed = true;
5924  if (referenceVertical == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5925  referenceVertical = constrvals[i]->First;
5926  ;
5927  }
5928  else {
5929  auto newConstr = new Constraint();
5930 
5931  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Parallel;
5932  newConstr->First = referenceVertical;
5933  newConstr->Second = constrvals[i]->First;
5934 
5935  newconstrVals.push_back(newConstr);
5936  }
5937  }
5938  else if (changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::Symmetric
5939  || changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::PointOnObject) {
5940  changed = true;// We remove symmetric on axes
5941  }
5942  else if (changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::DistanceX
5943  || changeConstraintIndices[cindex].second == Sketcher::DistanceY) {
5944  changed = true;// We remove symmetric on axes
5945  newconstrVals.push_back(constrvals[i]->clone());
5946  newconstrVals.back()->Type = Sketcher::Distance;
5947  }
5948 
5949  cindex++;
5950  }
5951  else {
5952  newconstrVals.push_back(constrvals[i]);
5953  }
5954  }
5955 
5956  if (nhoriz > 0 && nvert > 0) {
5957  auto newConstr = new Constraint();
5958 
5959  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::Perpendicular;
5960  newConstr->First = referenceVertical;
5961  newConstr->Second = referenceHorizontal;
5962 
5963  newconstrVals.push_back(newConstr);
5964  }
5965 
5966  if (changed)
5967  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newconstrVals));
5968 
5969  return 0;
5970 }
5971 
5972 int SketchObject::exposeInternalGeometry(int GeoId)
5973 {
5974  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
5975  return -1;
5976 
5977  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
5978  // Only for supported types
5979  if (geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()
5980  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
5981  // First we search what has to be restored
5982  bool major = false;
5983  bool minor = false;
5984  bool focus1 = false;
5985  bool focus2 = false;
5986 
5987  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
5988 
5989  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
5990  ++it) {
5991  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
5992  switch ((*it)->AlignmentType) {
5993  case Sketcher::EllipseMajorDiameter:
5994  major = true;
5995  break;
5996  case Sketcher::EllipseMinorDiameter:
5997  minor = true;
5998  break;
5999  case Sketcher::EllipseFocus1:
6000  focus1 = true;
6001  break;
6002  case Sketcher::EllipseFocus2:
6003  focus2 = true;
6004  break;
6005  default:
6006  return -1;
6007  }
6008  }
6009  }
6010 
6011  int currentgeoid = getHighestCurveIndex();
6012  int incrgeo = 0;
6013 
6014  Base::Vector3d center;
6015  double majord;
6016  double minord;
6017  Base::Vector3d majdir;
6018 
6019  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> igeo;
6020  std::vector<Constraint*> icon;
6021 
6022  if (geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
6023  const Part::GeomEllipse* ellipse = static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geo);
6024 
6025  center = ellipse->getCenter();
6026  majord = ellipse->getMajorRadius();
6027  minord = ellipse->getMinorRadius();
6028  majdir = ellipse->getMajorAxisDir();
6029  }
6030  else {
6031  const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse* aoe = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geo);
6032 
6033  center = aoe->getCenter();
6034  majord = aoe->getMajorRadius();
6035  minord = aoe->getMinorRadius();
6036  majdir = aoe->getMajorAxisDir();
6037  }
6038 
6039  Base::Vector3d mindir = Vector3d(-majdir.y, majdir.x);
6040 
6041  Base::Vector3d majorpositiveend = center + majord * majdir;
6042  Base::Vector3d majornegativeend = center - majord * majdir;
6043  Base::Vector3d minorpositiveend = center + minord * mindir;
6044  Base::Vector3d minornegativeend = center - minord * mindir;
6045 
6046  double df = sqrt(majord * majord - minord * minord);
6047 
6048  Base::Vector3d focus1P = center + df * majdir;
6049  Base::Vector3d focus2P = center - df * majdir;
6050 
6051  if (!major) {
6052  Part::GeomLineSegment* lmajor = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
6053  lmajor->setPoints(majorpositiveend, majornegativeend);
6054 
6055  igeo.push_back(lmajor);
6056 
6057  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6058  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6059  newConstr->AlignmentType = EllipseMajorDiameter;
6060  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6061  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6062 
6063  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6064  incrgeo++;
6065  }
6066  if (!minor) {
6067  Part::GeomLineSegment* lminor = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
6068  lminor->setPoints(minorpositiveend, minornegativeend);
6069 
6070  igeo.push_back(lminor);
6071 
6072  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6073  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6074  newConstr->AlignmentType = EllipseMinorDiameter;
6075  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6076  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6077 
6078  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6079  incrgeo++;
6080  }
6081  if (!focus1) {
6082  Part::GeomPoint* pf1 = new Part::GeomPoint();
6083  pf1->setPoint(focus1P);
6084 
6085  igeo.push_back(pf1);
6086 
6087  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6088  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6089  newConstr->AlignmentType = EllipseFocus1;
6090  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6091  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
6092  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6093 
6094  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6095  incrgeo++;
6096  }
6097  if (!focus2) {
6098  Part::GeomPoint* pf2 = new Part::GeomPoint();
6099  pf2->setPoint(focus2P);
6100  igeo.push_back(pf2);
6101 
6102  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6103  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6104  newConstr->AlignmentType = EllipseFocus2;
6105  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6106  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
6107  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6108 
6109  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6110  }
6111 
6112  this->addGeometry(igeo, true);
6113  this->addConstraints(icon);
6114 
6115  for (std::vector<Part::Geometry*>::iterator it = igeo.begin(); it != igeo.end(); ++it) {
6116  if (*it)
6117  delete *it;
6118  }
6119 
6120  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::iterator it = icon.begin(); it != icon.end(); ++it) {
6121  if (*it)
6122  delete *it;
6123  }
6124 
6125  icon.clear();
6126  igeo.clear();
6127 
6128  return incrgeo;// number of added elements
6129  }
6130  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
6131  // First we search what has to be restored
6132  bool major = false;
6133  bool minor = false;
6134  bool focus = false;
6135

6137 
6138  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6139  ++it) {
6140  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
6141  switch ((*it)->AlignmentType) {
6142  case Sketcher::HyperbolaMajor:
6143  major = true;
6144  break;
6145  case Sketcher::HyperbolaMinor:
6146  minor = true;
6147  break;
6148  case Sketcher::HyperbolaFocus:
6149  focus = true;
6150  break;
6151  default:

6154  }

6164  double minord = aoh->getMinorRadius();

6198  lminor->setPoints(minorpositiveend, minornegativeend);
6199

6203  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;

6205  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;

6253  ++it) {

6304  newConstr->AlignmentType = Sketcher::ParabolaFocalAxis;

6306  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
6307  newConstr->Second = GeoId;

6310

6312  }

6328  igeo.clear();
6329

6331  }
6332  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
6333 
6334  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
6335  // First we search what has to be restored
6336  std::vector<bool> controlpoints(bsp->countPoles());
6337  std::vector<int> controlpointgeoids(bsp->countPoles());
6338 
6339  std::vector<bool> knotpoints(bsp->countKnots());
6340  std::vector<int> knotgeoids(bsp->countKnots());
6341 
6342  bool isfirstweightconstrained = false;
6343 
6344  std::vector<bool>::iterator itb;
6345  std::vector<int>::iterator it;
6346 
6347  for (it = controlpointgeoids.begin(), itb = controlpoints.begin();
6348  it != controlpointgeoids.end() && itb != controlpoints.end();
6349  ++it, ++itb) {
6350  (*it) = -1;
6351  (*itb) = false;
6352  }
6353 
6354  for (it = knotgeoids.begin(), itb = knotpoints.begin();
6355  it != knotgeoids.end() && itb != knotpoints.end();
6356  ++it, ++itb) {
6357  (*it) = -1;
6358  (*itb) = false;
6359  }
6360 
6361  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
6362 
6363  // search for existing poles
6364  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6365  ++it) {
6366  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
6367  switch ((*it)->AlignmentType) {
6368  case Sketcher::BSplineControlPoint:
6369  controlpoints[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = true;
6370  controlpointgeoids[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = (*it)->First;
6371  break;
6372  case Sketcher::BSplineKnotPoint:
6373  knotpoints[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = true;
6374  knotgeoids[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = (*it)->First;
6375  break;
6376  default:
6377  return -1;
6378  }
6379  }
6380  }
6381 
6382  if (controlpoints[0]) {
6383  // search for first pole weight constraint
6384  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin();
6385  it != vals.end();
6386  ++it) {
6387  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Weight && (*it)->First == controlpointgeoids[0]) {
6388  isfirstweightconstrained = true;
6389  }
6390  }
6391  }
6392 
6393  int currentgeoid = getHighestCurveIndex();
6394  int incrgeo = 0;
6395 
6396  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> igeo;
6397  std::vector<Constraint*> icon;
6398 
6399  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = bsp->getPoles();
6400  std::vector<double> weights = bsp->getWeights();
6401  std::vector<double> knots = bsp->getKnots();
6402 
6403  double distance_p0_p1 = (poles[1] - poles[0]).Length();// for visual purposes only
6404 
6405  int index = 0;
6406 
6407  for (it = controlpointgeoids.begin(), itb = controlpoints.begin();
6408  it != controlpointgeoids.end() && itb != controlpoints.end();
6409  ++it, ++itb, index++) {
6410 
6411  if (!(*itb))// if controlpoint not existing
6412  {
6413  Part::GeomCircle* pc = new Part::GeomCircle();
6414  pc->setCenter(poles[index]);
6415  pc->setRadius(distance_p0_p1 / 6);
6416 
6417  igeo.push_back(pc);
6418 
6419  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6420  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6421  newConstr->AlignmentType = Sketcher::BSplineControlPoint;
6422  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6423  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::mid;
6424  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6425  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = index;
6426 
6427  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6428 
6429  if (it != controlpointgeoids.begin()) {
6430  if (isfirstweightconstrained && weights[0] == weights[index]) {
6431  // if pole-weight newly created AND first weight is radius-constrained,
6432  // AND these weights are equal, constrain them to be equal
6433  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr2 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6434  newConstr2->Type = Sketcher::Equal;
6435  newConstr2->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6436  newConstr2->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
6437  newConstr2->Second = controlpointgeoids[0];
6438  newConstr2->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
6439 
6440  icon.push_back(newConstr2);
6441  }
6442  }
6443  else {
6444  controlpointgeoids[0] = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6445  if (weights[0] == 1.0) {
6446  // if the first weight is 1.0 it's probably going to be non-rational
6447  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr3 = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6448  newConstr3->Type = Sketcher::Weight;
6449  newConstr3->First = controlpointgeoids[0];
6450  newConstr3->setValue(weights[0]);
6451 
6452  icon.push_back(newConstr3);
6453 
6454  isfirstweightconstrained = true;
6455  }
6456  }
6457  incrgeo++;
6458  }
6459  }
6460 
6461  index = 0;
6462 
6463  for (it = knotgeoids.begin(), itb = knotpoints.begin();
6464  it != knotgeoids.end() && itb != knotpoints.end();
6465  ++it, ++itb, index++) {
6466 
6467  if (!(*itb))// if knot point not existing
6468  {
6469  Part::GeomPoint* kp = new Part::GeomPoint();
6470 
6471  kp->setPoint(bsp->pointAtParameter(knots[index]));
6472 
6473  igeo.push_back(kp);
6474 
6475  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
6476  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
6477  newConstr->AlignmentType = Sketcher::BSplineKnotPoint;
6478  newConstr->First = currentgeoid + incrgeo + 1;
6479  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
6480  newConstr->Second = GeoId;
6481  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = index;
6482 
6483  icon.push_back(newConstr);
6484 
6485  incrgeo++;
6486  }
6487  }
6488 
6489  Q_UNUSED(isfirstweightconstrained);
6490 
6491  this->addGeometry(igeo, true);
6492  this->addConstraints(icon);
6493 
6494  for (std::vector<Part::Geometry*>::iterator it = igeo.begin(); it != igeo.end(); ++it)
6495  if (*it)
6496  delete *it;
6497 
6498  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::iterator it = icon.begin(); it != icon.end(); ++it)
6499  if (*it)
6500  delete *it;
6501 
6502  icon.clear();
6503  igeo.clear();
6504 
6505  return incrgeo;// number of added elements
6506  }
6507  else
6508  return -1;// not supported type
6509 }
6510 
6511 int SketchObject::deleteUnusedInternalGeometry(int GeoId, bool delgeoid)
6512 {
6513  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
6514  return -1;
6515 
6516  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
6517  // Only for supported types
6518  if (geo->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()
6519  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()
6520  || geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
6521 
6522  int majorelementindex = -1;
6523  int minorelementindex = -1;
6524  int focus1elementindex = -1;
6525  int focus2elementindex = -1;
6526 
6527  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
6528 
6529  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6530  ++it) {
6531  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
6532  switch ((*it)->AlignmentType) {
6533  case Sketcher::EllipseMajorDiameter:
6534  case Sketcher::HyperbolaMajor:
6535  majorelementindex = (*it)->First;
6536  break;
6537  case Sketcher::EllipseMinorDiameter:
6538  case Sketcher::HyperbolaMinor:
6539  minorelementindex = (*it)->First;
6540  break;
6541  case Sketcher::EllipseFocus1:
6542  case Sketcher::HyperbolaFocus:
6543  focus1elementindex = (*it)->First;
6544  break;
6545  case Sketcher::EllipseFocus2:
6546  focus2elementindex = (*it)->First;
6547  break;
6548  default:
6549  return -1;
6550  }
6551  }
6552  }
6553 
6554  // Hide unused geometry here
6555  int majorconstraints = 0;// number of constraints associated to the geoid of the major axis
6556  int minorconstraints = 0;
6557  int focus1constraints = 0;
6558  int focus2constraints = 0;
6559 
6560  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6561  ++it) {
6562 
6563  if ((*it)->Second == majorelementindex || (*it)->First == majorelementindex
6564  || (*it)->Third == majorelementindex)
6565  majorconstraints++;
6566  else if ((*it)->Second == minorelementindex || (*it)->First == minorelementindex
6567  || (*it)->Third == minorelementindex)
6568  minorconstraints++;
6569  else if ((*it)->Second == focus1elementindex || (*it)->First == focus1elementindex
6570  || (*it)->Third == focus1elementindex)
6571  focus1constraints++;
6572  else if ((*it)->Second == focus2elementindex || (*it)->First == focus2elementindex
6573  || (*it)->Third == focus2elementindex)
6574  focus2constraints++;
6575  }
6576 
6577  std::vector<int> delgeometries;
6578 
6579  // those with less than 2 constraints must be removed
6580  if (focus2constraints < 2)
6581  delgeometries.push_back(focus2elementindex);
6582 
6583  if (focus1constraints < 2)
6584  delgeometries.push_back(focus1elementindex);
6585 
6586  if (minorconstraints < 2)
6587  delgeometries.push_back(minorelementindex);
6588 
6589  if (majorconstraints < 2)
6590  delgeometries.push_back(majorelementindex);
6591 
6592  if (delgeoid)
6593  delgeometries.push_back(GeoId);
6594 
6595  // indices over an erased element get automatically updated!!
6596  std::sort(delgeometries.begin(), delgeometries.end());
6597 
6598  if (!delgeometries.empty()) {
6599  for (std::vector<int>::reverse_iterator it = delgeometries.rbegin();
6600  it != delgeometries.rend();
6601  ++it) {
6602  delGeometry(*it, false);
6603  }
6604  }
6605 
6606  int ndeleted = delgeometries.size();
6607 
6608  delgeometries.clear();
6609 
6610  return ndeleted;// number of deleted elements
6611  }
6612  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
6613  // if the focus-to-vertex line is constrained, then never delete the focus
6614  // if the line is unconstrained, then the line may be deleted,
6615  // in this case the focus may be deleted if unconstrained.
6616  int majorelementindex = -1;
6617  int focus1elementindex = -1;
6618 
6619  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
6620 
6621  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6622  ++it) {
6623  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
6624  switch ((*it)->AlignmentType) {
6625  case Sketcher::ParabolaFocus:
6626  focus1elementindex = (*it)->First;
6627  break;
6628  case Sketcher::ParabolaFocalAxis:
6629  majorelementindex = (*it)->First;
6630  break;
6631  default:
6632  return -1;
6633  }
6634  }
6635  }
6636 
6637  // Hide unused geometry here
6638  // number of constraints associated to the geoid of the major axis other than the coincident
6639  // ones
6640  int majorconstraints = 0;
6641  int focus1constraints = 0;
6642 
6643  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
6644  ++it) {
6645  if ((*it)->Second == majorelementindex || (*it)->First == majorelementindex
6646  || (*it)->Third == majorelementindex)
6647  majorconstraints++;
6648  else if ((*it)->Second == focus1elementindex || (*it)->First == focus1elementindex
6649  || (*it)->Third == focus1elementindex)
6650  focus1constraints++;
6651  }
6652 
6653  std::vector<int> delgeometries;
6654 
6655  // major has minimum one constraint, the specific internal alignment constraint
6656  if (majorelementindex != -1 && majorconstraints < 2)
6657  delgeometries.push_back(majorelementindex);
6658 
6659  // focus has minimum one constraint now, the specific internal alignment constraint
6660  if (focus1elementindex != -1 && focus1constraints < 2)
6661  delgeometries.push_back(focus1elementindex);
6662 
6663  if (delgeoid)
6664  delgeometries.push_back(GeoId);
6665 
6666  // indices over an erased element get automatically updated!!
6667  std::sort(delgeometries.begin(), delgeometries.end());
6668 
6669  if (!delgeometries.empty()) {
6670  for (std::vector<int>::reverse_iterator it = delgeometries.rbegin();
6671  it != delgeometries.rend();
6672  ++it) {
6673  delGeometry(*it, false);
6674  }
6675  }
6676 
6677  int ndeleted = delgeometries.size();
6678 
6679  delgeometries.clear();
6680 
6681  return ndeleted;// number of deleted elements
6682  }
6683  else if (geo->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
6684 
6685  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
6686 
6687  // First we search existing IA
6688  std::vector<int> controlpointgeoids(bsp->countPoles());
6689  std::vector<int> cpassociatedconstraints(bsp->countPoles());
6690 
6691  std::vector<int> knotgeoids(bsp->countKnots());
6692  std::vector<int> kassociatedconstraints(bsp->countKnots());
6693 
6694  std::vector<int>::iterator it;
6695  std::vector<int>::iterator ita;
6696 
6697  for (it = controlpointgeoids.begin(), ita = cpassociatedconstraints.begin();
6698  it != controlpointgeoids.end() && ita != cpassociatedconstraints.end();
6699  ++it, ++ita) {
6700  (*it) = -1;
6701  (*ita) = 0;
6702  }
6703 
6704  for (it = knotgeoids.begin(), ita = kassociatedconstraints.begin();
6705  it != knotgeoids.end() && ita != kassociatedconstraints.end();
6706  ++it, ++ita) {
6707  (*it) = -1;
6708  (*ita) = 0;
6709  }
6710 
6711  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
6712 
6713  // search for existing poles
6714  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator jt = vals.begin(); jt != vals.end();
6715  ++jt) {
6716  if ((*jt)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*jt)->Second == GeoId) {
6717  switch ((*jt)->AlignmentType) {
6718  case Sketcher::BSplineControlPoint:
6719  controlpointgeoids[(*jt)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = (*jt)->First;
6720  break;
6721  case Sketcher::BSplineKnotPoint:
6722  knotgeoids[(*jt)->InternalAlignmentIndex] = (*jt)->First;
6723  break;
6724  default:
6725  return -1;
6726  }
6727  }
6728  }
6729 
6730  std::vector<int> delgeometries;
6731 
6732  for (it = controlpointgeoids.begin(), ita = cpassociatedconstraints.begin();
6733  it != controlpointgeoids.end() && ita != cpassociatedconstraints.end();
6734  ++it, ++ita) {
6735  if ((*it) != -1) {
6736  // look for a circle at geoid index
6737  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator itc = vals.begin();
6738  itc != vals.end();
6739  ++itc) {
6740 
6741  if ((*itc)->Type == Sketcher::Equal) {
6742  bool f = false, s = false;
6743  for (std::vector<int>::iterator its = controlpointgeoids.begin();
6744  its != controlpointgeoids.end();
6745  ++its) {
6746  if ((*itc)->First == *its) {
6747  f = true;
6748  }
6749  else if ((*itc)->Second == *its) {
6750  s = true;
6751  }
6752 
6753  if (f && s) {// the equality constraint is not interpole
6754  break;
6755  }
6756  }
6757 
6758  // the equality constraint constraints a pole but it is not interpole
6759  if (f != s) {
6760  (*ita)++;
6761  }
6762  }
6763  // We do not ignore weight constraints as we did with radius constraints,
6764  // because the radius magnitude no longer makes sense without the B-Spline.
6765  }
6766 
6767  if ((*ita) < 2) {// IA
6768  delgeometries.push_back((*it));
6769  }
6770  }
6771  }
6772 
6773  for (it = knotgeoids.begin(), ita = kassociatedconstraints.begin();
6774  it != knotgeoids.end() && ita != kassociatedconstraints.end();
6775  ++it, ++ita) {
6776  if ((*it) != -1) {
6777  // look for a point at geoid index
6778  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator itc = vals.begin();
6779  itc != vals.end();
6780  ++itc) {
6781  if ((*itc)->Second == (*it) || (*itc)->First == (*it)
6782  || (*itc)->Third == (*it)) {
6783  (*ita)++;
6784  }
6785  }
6786 
6787  if ((*ita) < 2) {// IA
6788  delgeometries.push_back((*it));
6789  }
6790  }
6791  }
6792 
6793 
6794  if (delgeoid)
6795  delgeometries.push_back(GeoId);
6796 
6797  int ndeleted = delGeometriesExclusiveList(delgeometries);
6798 
6799  return ndeleted;// number of deleted elements
6800  }
6801  else {
6802  return -1;// not supported type
6803  }
6804 }

6806 int SketchObject::deleteUnusedInternalGeometryAndUpdateGeoId(int& GeoId, bool delgeoid)
6807 {
6808  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
6809 
6810  if (!hasInternalGeometry(geo)) {
6811  return -1;
6812  }
6813  // We need to remove the internal geometry of the BSpline, as BSplines change in number
6814  // of poles and knots We save the tags of the relevant geometry to retrieve the new
6815  // GeoIds later on.
6816  boost::uuids::uuid GeoIdTag;
6817 
6818  GeoIdTag = geo->getTag();
6819 
6820  int returnValue = deleteUnusedInternalGeometry(GeoId, delgeoid);
6821 
6822  if (delgeoid) {
6823  GeoId = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
6824  return returnValue;
6825  }
6826 
6827  auto vals = getCompleteGeometry();
6828 
6829  for (size_t i = 0; i < vals.size(); i++) {
6830  if (vals[i]->getTag() == GeoIdTag) {
6831  GeoId = getGeoIdFromCompleteGeometryIndex(i);
6832  break;
6833  }
6834  }
6835 
6836  return returnValue;
6837 }
