6839 bool SketchObject::convertToNURBS(int GeoId)
6840 {
6841  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
6842  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
6843 
6844  if (GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex()
6845  || (GeoId < 0 && -GeoId > static_cast<int>(ExternalGeo.getSize())) || GeoId == -1
6846  || GeoId == -2)
6847  return false;
6848 
6849  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
6850 
6851  if (geo->is<Part::GeomPoint>())
6852  return false;
6853 
6854  const Part::GeomCurve* geo1 = static_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(geo);
6855 
6856  Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bspline;
6857 
6858  try {
6859  bspline = geo1->toNurbs(geo1->getFirstParameter(), geo1->getLastParameter());
6860 
6861  if (geo1->isDerivedFrom(Part::GeomArcOfConic::getClassTypeId())) {
6862  const Part::GeomArcOfConic* geoaoc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfConic*>(geo1);
6863 
6864  if (geoaoc->isReversed())
6865  bspline->reverse();
6866  }
6867  }
6868  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
6869  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
6870  // revert to original values
6871  return false;
6872  }
6873 
6874  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
6875 
6876  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
6877 
6878  // Block checks and updates in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
6879  {
6880  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
6881 
6882  if (GeoId < 0) {// external geometry
6883  newVals.push_back(bspline);
6884  generateId(bspline);
6885  }
6886  else {// normal geometry
6887 
6888  newVals[GeoId] = bspline;
6889  GeometryFacade::copyId(geo, bspline);
6890 
6891  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& cvals = Constraints.getValues();
6892 
6893  std::vector<Constraint*> newcVals(cvals);
6894 
6895  int index = cvals.size() - 1;
6896  // delete constraints on this elements other than coincident constraints (bspline does
6897  // not support them currently), except for coincidents on mid point of the
6898  // to-be-converted curve.
6899  for (; index >= 0; index--) {
6900  auto otherthancoincident = cvals[index]->Type != Sketcher::Coincident
6901  && (cvals[index]->First == GeoId || cvals[index]->Second == GeoId
6902  || cvals[index]->Third == GeoId);
6903 
6904  auto coincidentonmidpoint = cvals[index]->Type == Sketcher::Coincident
6905  && ((cvals[index]->First == GeoId
6906  && cvals[index]->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::mid)
6907  || (cvals[index]->Second == GeoId
6908  && cvals[index]->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::mid));
6909 
6910  if (otherthancoincident || coincidentonmidpoint)
6911  newcVals.erase(newcVals.begin() + index);
6912  }
6913 
6914  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newcVals));
6915  }
6916 
6917  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
6918  }
6919 
6920  // trigger update now
6921  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
6922  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
6923  Geometry.touch();
6924 
6925  return true;
6926 }

6928 bool SketchObject::increaseBSplineDegree(int GeoId, int degreeincrement /*= 1*/)
6929 {
6930  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
6931  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
6932 
6933  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
6934  return false;
6935 
6936  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
6937 
6938  if (geo->getTypeId() != Part::GeomBSplineCurve::getClassTypeId())
6939  return false;
6940 
6941  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
6942 
6943  const Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) curve = Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(bsp->handle());
6944 
6945  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve> bspline(new Part::GeomBSplineCurve(curve));
6946 
6947  try {
6948  int cdegree = bspline->getDegree();
6949 
6950  bspline->increaseDegree(cdegree + degreeincrement);
6951  }
6952  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
6953  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
6954  return false;
6955  }
6956 
6957  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
6958 
6959  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
6960 
6961  GeometryFacade::copyId(geo, bspline.get());
6962  newVals[GeoId] = bspline.release();
6963 
6964  // AcceptGeometry called from onChanged
6965  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
6966 
6967  return true;
6968 }

6970 bool SketchObject::decreaseBSplineDegree(int GeoId, int degreedecrement /*= 1*/)
6971 {
6972  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
6973  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
6974 
6975  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
6976  return false;
6977 
6978  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
6979 
6980  if (geo->getTypeId() != Part::GeomBSplineCurve::getClassTypeId())
6981  return false;

6983  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
6984 
6985  const Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve) curve = Handle(Geom_BSplineCurve)::DownCast(bsp->handle());

6988 
6989  try {
6990  int cdegree = bspline->getDegree();
6991

6995  return false;

6997  }
6998  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
6999  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7000  return false;

7013  Geometry.setValues(newVals);
7014 #else
7015  delGeometry(GeoId);
7016  int newId = addGeometry(bspline.release());
7017  exposeInternalGeometry(newId);
7018 #endif
7019 
7020  return true;
7021 }

7023 bool SketchObject::modifyBSplineKnotMultiplicity(int GeoId, int knotIndex, int multiplicityincr)
7024 {
7025  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7026  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7027 
7028  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex()) {
7029  THROWMT(
7030  Base::ValueError,
7031  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions", "B-spline Geometry Index (GeoID) is out of bounds."))
7032  }
7033 
7034  if (multiplicityincr == 0)// no change in multiplicity
7035  THROWMT(
7036  Base::ValueError,
7037  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions", "You are requesting no change in knot multiplicity."))
7038 
7039  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
7040 
7041  if (geo->getTypeId() != Part::GeomBSplineCurve::getClassTypeId())
7042  THROWMT(Base::TypeError,
7043  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions",
7044  "The Geometry Index (GeoId) provided is not a B-spline."))
7045 
7046  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
7047 
7048  int degree = bsp->getDegree();
7049 
7050  if (knotIndex > bsp->countKnots() || knotIndex < 1)// knotindex in OCC 1 -> countKnots
7051  THROWMT(Base::ValueError,
7052  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions",
7053  "The knot index is out of bounds. Note that in accordance with "
7054  "OCC notation, the first knot has index 1 and not zero."))
7055 
7056  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve> bspline;
7057 
7058  int curmult = bsp->getMultiplicity(knotIndex);
7059 
7060  // zero is removing the knot, degree is just positional continuity
7061  if ((curmult + multiplicityincr) > degree)
7062  THROWMT(Base::ValueError,
7063  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP(
7064  "Exceptions",
7065  "The multiplicity cannot be increased beyond the degree of the B-spline."))
7066 
7067  // zero is removing the knot, degree is just positional continuity
7068  if ((curmult + multiplicityincr) < 0)
7069  THROWMT(
7070  Base::ValueError,
7071  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions", "The multiplicity cannot be decreased beyond zero."))
7072 
7073  try {
7074  bspline.reset(static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(bsp->clone()));
7075 
7076  if (multiplicityincr > 0) {// increase multiplicity
7077  bspline->increaseMultiplicity(knotIndex, curmult + multiplicityincr);
7078  }
7079  else {// decrease multiplicity
7080  bool result = bspline->removeKnot(knotIndex, curmult + multiplicityincr, 1E6);
7081 
7082  if (!result)
7083  THROWMT(
7084  Base::CADKernelError,
7085  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP(
7086  "Exceptions",
7087  "OCC is unable to decrease the multiplicity within the maximum tolerance."))
7088  }
7089  }
7090  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
7091  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7092  return false;
7093  }
7094 
7095  // we succeeded with the multiplicity modification, so alignment geometry may be
7096  // invalid/inconsistent for the new bspline
7097 
7098  std::vector<int> delGeoId;
7099 
7100  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = bsp->getPoles();
7101  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> newpoles = bspline->getPoles();
7102  std::vector<int> prevpole(bsp->countPoles());
7103 
7104  for (int i = 0; i < int(poles.size()); i++)
7105  prevpole[i] = -1;
7106 
7107  int taken = 0;
7108  for (int j = 0; j < int(poles.size()); j++) {
7109  for (int i = taken; i < int(newpoles.size()); i++) {
7110  if (newpoles[i] == poles[j]) {
7111  prevpole[j] = i;
7112  taken++;
7113  break;
7114  }
7115  }
7116  }
7117 
7118  // on fully removing a knot the knot geometry changes
7119  std::vector<double> knots = bsp->getKnots();
7120  std::vector<double> newknots = bspline->getKnots();
7121  std::vector<int> prevknot(bsp->countKnots());
7122 
7123  for (int i = 0; i < int(knots.size()); i++)
7124  prevknot[i] = -1;
7125 
7126  taken = 0;
7127  for (int j = 0; j < int(knots.size()); j++) {
7128  for (int i = taken; i < int(newknots.size()); i++) {
7129  if (newknots[i] == knots[j]) {
7130  prevknot[j] = i;
7131  taken++;
7132  break;
7133  }
7134  }
7135  }
7136 
7137  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& cvals = Constraints.getValues();
7138 
7139  std::vector<Constraint*> newcVals(0);
7140 
7141  // modify pole constraints
7142  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = cvals.begin(); it != cvals.end();
7143  ++it) {
7144  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
7145  if ((*it)->AlignmentType == Sketcher::BSplineControlPoint) {
7146  if (prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] != -1) {
7147  assert(prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] < bspline->countPoles());
7148  Constraint* newConstr = (*it)->clone();
7149  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex];
7150  newcVals.push_back(newConstr);
7151  }
7152  else {
7153  // it is an internal alignment geometry that is no longer valid => delete it and
7154  // the pole circle
7155  delGeoId.push_back((*it)->First);
7156  }
7157  }
7158  else if ((*it)->AlignmentType == Sketcher::BSplineKnotPoint) {
7159  if (prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] != -1) {
7160  assert(prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] < bspline->countKnots());
7161  Constraint* newConstr = (*it)->clone();
7162  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex];
7163  newcVals.push_back(newConstr);
7164  }
7165  else {
7166  // it is an internal alignment geometry that is no longer valid => delete it and
7167  // the knot point
7168  delGeoId.push_back((*it)->First);
7169  }
7170  }
7171  else {// it is a bspline geometry, but not a controlpoint or knot
7172  newcVals.push_back(*it);
7173  }
7174  }
7175  else {
7176  newcVals.push_back(*it);
7177  }
7178  }
7179 
7180  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
7181 
7182  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
7183 
7184  GeometryFacade::copyId(geo, bspline.get());
7185  newVals[GeoId] = bspline.release();
7186 
7187  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
7188  {
7189  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
7190  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
7191 
7192  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newcVals));
7193  }
7194 
7195  // Trigger update now
7196  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
7197  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
7198  if (!delGeoId.empty()) {
7199  delGeometriesExclusiveList(delGeoId);
7200  }
7201  else {
7202  Geometry.touch();
7203  }
7204  return true;
7205 }
7206 
7207 bool SketchObject::insertBSplineKnot(int GeoId, double param, int multiplicity)
7208 {
7209  // TODO: Check if this is still valid: no need to check input data validity as this is an
7210  // sketchobject managed operation.
7211  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7212 
7213  // handling unacceptable cases
7214  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId > getHighestCurveIndex())
7215  THROWMT(
7216  Base::ValueError,
7217  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions", "B-spline Geometry Index (GeoID) is out of bounds."));
7218 
7219  if (multiplicity == 0)
7220  THROWMT(Base::ValueError,
7221  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions", "Knot cannot have zero multiplicity."));
7222 
7223  const Part::Geometry* geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
7224 
7225  if (geo->getTypeId() != Part::GeomBSplineCurve::getClassTypeId())
7226  THROWMT(Base::TypeError,
7227  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions",
7228  "The Geometry Index (GeoId) provided is not a B-spline."));
7229 
7230  const Part::GeomBSplineCurve* bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(geo);
7231 
7232  int degree = bsp->getDegree();
7233  double firstParam = bsp->getFirstParameter();
7234  double lastParam = bsp->getLastParameter();
7235 
7236  if (multiplicity > degree)
7237  THROWMT(Base::ValueError,
7238  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP(
7239  "Exceptions",
7240  "Knot multiplicity cannot be higher than the degree of the B-spline."));
7241 
7242  if (param > lastParam || param < firstParam)
7243  THROWMT(Base::ValueError,
7244  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Exceptions",
7245  "Knot cannot be inserted outside the B-spline parameter range."));
7246 
7247  std::unique_ptr<Part::GeomBSplineCurve> bspline;
7248 
7249  // run the command
7250  try {
7251  bspline.reset(static_cast<Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(bsp->clone()));
7252 
7253  bspline->insertKnot(param, multiplicity);
7254  }
7255  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
7256  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7257  return false;
7258  }
7259 
7260  // once command is run update the internal geometries
7261  std::vector<int> delGeoId;
7262 
7263  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> poles = bsp->getPoles();
7264  std::vector<Base::Vector3d> newpoles = bspline->getPoles();
7265  std::vector<int> prevpole(bsp->countPoles());
7266 
7267  for (int i = 0; i < int(poles.size()); i++)
7268  prevpole[i] = -1;
7269 
7270  int taken = 0;
7271  for (int j = 0; j < int(poles.size()); j++) {
7272  for (int i = taken; i < int(newpoles.size()); i++) {
7273  if (newpoles[i] == poles[j]) {
7274  prevpole[j] = i;
7275  taken++;
7276  break;
7277  }
7278  }
7279  }
7280 
7281  // on fully removing a knot the knot geometry changes
7282  std::vector<double> knots = bsp->getKnots();
7283  std::vector<double> newknots = bspline->getKnots();
7284  std::vector<int> prevknot(bsp->countKnots());
7285 
7286  for (int i = 0; i < int(knots.size()); i++)
7287  prevknot[i] = -1;
7288 
7289  taken = 0;
7290  for (int j = 0; j < int(knots.size()); j++) {
7291  for (int i = taken; i < int(newknots.size()); i++) {
7292  if (newknots[i] == knots[j]) {
7293  prevknot[j] = i;
7294  taken++;
7295  break;
7296  }
7297  }
7298  }
7299 
7300  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& cvals = Constraints.getValues();
7301 
7302  std::vector<Constraint*> newcVals(0);
7303 
7304  // modify pole constraints
7305  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = cvals.begin(); it != cvals.end();
7306  ++it) {
7307  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::InternalAlignment && (*it)->Second == GeoId) {
7308  if ((*it)->AlignmentType == Sketcher::BSplineControlPoint) {
7309  if (prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] != -1) {
7310  assert(prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] < bspline->countPoles());
7311  Constraint* newConstr = (*it)->clone();
7312  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = prevpole[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex];
7313  newcVals.push_back(newConstr);
7314  }
7315  else {
7316  // it is an internal alignment geometry that is no longer valid => delete it and
7317  // the pole circle
7318  delGeoId.push_back((*it)->First);
7319  }
7320  }
7321  else if ((*it)->AlignmentType == Sketcher::BSplineKnotPoint) {
7322  if (prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] != -1) {
7323  assert(prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex] < bspline->countKnots());
7324  Constraint* newConstr = (*it)->clone();
7325  newConstr->InternalAlignmentIndex = prevknot[(*it)->InternalAlignmentIndex];
7326  newcVals.push_back(newConstr);
7327  }
7328  else {
7329  // it is an internal alignment geometry that is no longer valid => delete it and
7330  // the knot point
7331  delGeoId.push_back((*it)->First);
7332  }
7333  }
7334  else {
7335  // it is a bspline geometry, but not a controlpoint or knot
7336  newcVals.push_back(*it);
7337  }
7338  }
7339  else {
7340  newcVals.push_back(*it);
7341  }
7342  }
7343 
7344  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
7345 
7346  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
7347 
7348  newVals[GeoId] = bspline.release();
7349 
7350  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
7351  {
7352  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
7353  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
7354 
7355  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newcVals));
7356  }
7357 
7358  // Trigger update now
7359  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
7360  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
7361  if (!delGeoId.empty()) {
7362  // NOTE: There have been a couple of instances when knot insertion has
7363  // led to a segmentation fault: see
7364  // https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=19&t=64962&sid=10272db50a635c633260517b14ecad37.
7365  // If a segfault happens again and a `Geometry.touch()` here fixes it,
7366  // it is possible that `delGeometriesExclusiveList` is causing an update
7367  // in constraint GUI features during an intermediate step.
7368  // See 247a9f0876a00e08c25b07d1f8802479d8623e87 for suggestions.
7369  // Geometry.touch();
7370  delGeometriesExclusiveList(delGeoId);
7371  }
7372  else {
7373  Geometry.touch();
7374  }
7375 
7376  // handle this last return
7377  return true;
7378 }
7379 
7380 int SketchObject::carbonCopy(App::DocumentObject* pObj, bool construction)
7381 {
7382  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7383  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7384 
7385  // so far only externals to the support of the sketch and datum features
7386  bool xinv = false, yinv = false;
7387 
7388  if (!isCarbonCopyAllowed(pObj->getDocument(), pObj, xinv, yinv))
7389  return -1;
7390 
7391  SketchObject* psObj = static_cast<SketchObject*>(pObj);
7392 
7393  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
7394 
7395  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& cvals = Constraints.getValues();
7396 
7397  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
7398 
7399  std::vector<Constraint*> newcVals(cvals);
7400 
7401  int nextgeoid = vals.size();
7402 
7403  int nextextgeoid = getExternalGeometryCount();
7404 
7405  int nextcid = cvals.size();
7406 
7407  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& svals = psObj->getInternalGeometry();
7408 
7409  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& scvals = psObj->Constraints.getValues();
7410 
7411  newVals.reserve(vals.size() + svals.size());
7412  newcVals.reserve(cvals.size() + scvals.size());
7413 
7414  std::map<int, int> extMap;
7415  if (psObj->ExternalGeo.getSize() > 1) {
7416  int i = -1;
7417  auto geos = this->ExternalGeo.getValues();
7418  std::string myName(this->getNameInDocument());
7419  myName += ".";
7420  for (const auto &geo : psObj->ExternalGeo.getValues()) {
7421  if (++i < 2) // skip h/v axes
7422  continue;
7423  else {
7424  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
7425  const auto &ref = egf->getRef();
7426  if (boost::starts_with(ref, myName)) {
7427  int geoId;
7428  PointPos posId;
7429  if (this->geoIdFromShapeType(ref.c_str()+myName.size(), geoId, posId)) {
7430  extMap[-i-1] = geoId;
7431  continue;
7432  }
7433  }
7434  }
7435  auto copy = geo->copy();
7436  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(copy);
7437  egf->setId(++geoLastId);
7438  if (!egf->getRef().empty()) {
7439  auto &refs = this->externalGeoRefMap[egf->getRef()];
7440  refs.push_back(geoLastId);
7441  }
7442  this->externalGeoMap[geoLastId] = (int)geos.size();
7443  geos.push_back(copy);
7444  extMap[-i-1] = -(int)geos.size();
7445  }
7446  Base::ObjectStatusLocker<App::Property::Status,App::Property>
7447  guard(App::Property::User3, &this->ExternalGeo);
7448  this->ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
7449  }
7450 
7451  if (psObj->ExternalGeometry.getSize() > 0) {
7452  std::vector<DocumentObject*> Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7453  std::vector<std::string> SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7454 
7455  const std::vector<DocumentObject*> originalObjects = Objects;
7456  const std::vector<std::string> originalSubElements = SubElements;
7457 
7458  std::vector<DocumentObject*> sObjects = psObj->ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7459  std::vector<std::string> sSubElements = psObj->ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7460 
7461  if (Objects.size() != SubElements.size() || sObjects.size() != sSubElements.size()) {
7462  assert(0 /*counts of objects and subelements in external geometry links do not match*/);
7463  Base::Console().Error("Internal error: counts of objects and subelements in external "
7464  "geometry links do not match\n");
7465  return -1;
7466  }
7467 
7468  int si = 0;
7469  for (auto& sobj : sObjects) {
7470  int i = 0;
7471  for (auto& obj : Objects) {
7472  if (obj == sobj && SubElements[i] == sSubElements[si]) {
7473  Base::Console().Error(
7474  "Link to %s already exists in this sketch. Delete the link and try again\n",
7475  sSubElements[si].c_str());
7476  return -1;
7477  }
7478 
7479  i++;
7480  }
7481 
7482  Objects.push_back(sobj);
7483  SubElements.push_back(sSubElements[si]);
7484 
7485  si++;
7486  }
7487 
7488  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects, SubElements);
7489 
7490  try {
7491  rebuildExternalGeometry();
7492  }
7493  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
7494  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7495  // revert to original values
7496  ExternalGeometry.setValues(originalObjects, originalSubElements);
7497  return -1;
7498  }
7499 
7500  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
7501  }
7502 
7503  for (std::vector<Part::Geometry*>::const_iterator it = svals.begin(); it != svals.end(); ++it) {
7504  Part::Geometry* geoNew = (*it)->copy();
7505  generateId(geoNew);
7506  if (construction && geoNew->getTypeId() != Part::GeomPoint::getClassTypeId()) {
7507  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(geoNew, true);
7508  }
7509  newVals.push_back(geoNew);
7510  }
7511 
7512  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = scvals.begin(); it != scvals.end();
7513  ++it) {
7514  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = (*it)->copy();
7515  if ((*it)->First >= 0)
7516  newConstr->First += nextgeoid;
7517  if ((*it)->Second >= 0)
7518  newConstr->Second += nextgeoid;
7519  if ((*it)->Third >= 0)
7520  newConstr->Third += nextgeoid;
7521 
7522  if ((*it)->First < -2 && (*it)->First != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
7523  newConstr->First -= (nextextgeoid - 2);
7524  if ((*it)->Second < -2 && (*it)->Second != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
7525  newConstr->Second -= (nextextgeoid - 2);
7526  if ((*it)->Third < -2 && (*it)->Third != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
7527  newConstr->Third -= (nextextgeoid - 2);
7528 
7529  newcVals.push_back(newConstr);
7530  }
7531 
7532  // Block acceptGeometry in OnChanged to avoid unnecessary checks and updates
7533  {
7534  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
7535  Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
7536  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newcVals));
7537  }
7538  // we trigger now the update (before dealing with expressions)
7539  // Update geometry indices and rebuild vertexindex now via onChanged, so that
7540  // ViewProvider::UpdateData is triggered.
7541  Geometry.touch();
7542 
7543  int sourceid = 0;
7544  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = scvals.begin(); it != scvals.end();
7545  ++it, nextcid++, sourceid++) {
7546 
7547  if ((*it)->isDimensional()) {
7548  // then we link its value to the parent
7549  if ((*it)->isDriving) {
7550  App::ObjectIdentifier spath;
7551  std::shared_ptr<App::Expression> expr;
7552  std::string scname = (*it)->Name;
7553  if (App::ExpressionParser::isTokenAnIndentifier(scname)) {
7554  spath = App::ObjectIdentifier(psObj->Constraints)
7555  << App::ObjectIdentifier::SimpleComponent(scname);
7556  expr = std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>(App::Expression::parse(
7557  this, spath.getDocumentObjectName().getString() + spath.toString()));
7558  }
7559  else {
7560  spath = psObj->Constraints.createPath(sourceid);
7561  expr = std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>(
7562  App::Expression::parse(this,
7563  spath.getDocumentObjectName().getString()
7564  + std::string(1, '.') + spath.toString()));
7565  }
7566  // (there is a plausible alternative for a slightly different use case to copy the
7567  // expression of the parent if one is existing)
7568  /*
7569  * App::PropertyExpressionEngine::ExpressionInfo expr_info =
7570  * psObj->getExpression(path);
7571  *
7572  * if (expr_info.expression)*/
7573  // App::Expression * expr = parse(this, const std::string& buffer);
7574  setExpression(Constraints.createPath(nextcid), expr);
7575  }
7576  }
7577  }
7578 
7579  // We shall solve in all cases, because recompute may fail, and leave the
7580  // sketch in an inconsistent state. A concrete example. If the copied sketch
7581  // has broken external geometry, its recomputation will fail. And because we
7582  // use expression for copied constraint to add dependency to the copied
7583  // sketch, this sketch will not be recomputed (because its dependency fails
7584  // to recompute).
7585 #if 0
7586  if (noRecomputes) // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
7587 #endif
7588  solve();
7589 
7590 
7591  return svals.size();
7592 }
7593 
7594 int SketchObject::addExternal(App::DocumentObject *Obj, const char* SubName, bool defining, bool intersection)
7595 {
7596  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7597  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7598 
7599  // so far only externals to the support of the sketch and datum features
7600  if (!isExternalAllowed(Obj->getDocument(), Obj))
7601  return -1;
7602 
7603  auto wholeShape = Part::Feature::getTopoShape(Obj);
7604  auto shape = wholeShape.getSubTopoShape(SubName, /*silent*/true);
7605  TopAbs_ShapeEnum shapeType = TopAbs_SHAPE;
7606  if (shape.shapeType(/*silent*/true) != TopAbs_FACE) {
7607  if (shape.hasSubShape(TopAbs_FACE))
7608  shapeType = TopAbs_FACE;
7609  else if (shape.shapeType(/*silent*/true) != TopAbs_EDGE
7610  && shape.hasSubShape(TopAbs_EDGE))
7611  shapeType = TopAbs_EDGE;
7612  }
7613 
7614  if (shapeType != TopAbs_SHAPE) {
7615  std::string element = Part::TopoShape::shapeName(shapeType);
7616  std::size_t elementNameSize = element.size();
7617  int geometryCount = ExternalGeometry.getSize();
7618 
7619  gp_Pln sketchPlane;
7620  if (intersection) {
7621  Base::Placement Plm = Placement.getValue();
7622  Base::Vector3d Pos = Plm.getPosition();
7623  Base::Rotation Rot = Plm.getRotation();
7624  Base::Vector3d dN(0,0,1);
7625  Rot.multVec(dN,dN);
7626  Base::Vector3d dX(1,0,0);
7627  Rot.multVec(dX,dX);
7628  gp_Ax3 sketchAx3(gp_Pnt(Pos.x,Pos.y,Pos.z),
7629  gp_Dir(dN.x,dN.y,dN.z),
7630  gp_Dir(dX.x,dX.y,dX.z));
7631  sketchPlane.SetPosition(sketchAx3);
7632  }
7633  for (const auto &subShape : shape.getSubShapes(shapeType)) {
7634  int idx = wholeShape.findShape(subShape);
7635  if (idx == 0)
7636  continue;
7637  if (intersection) {
7638  try {
7639  FCBRepAlgoAPI_Section maker(subShape, sketchPlane);
7640  if (!maker.IsDone() || maker.Shape().IsNull())
7641  continue;
7642  } catch (Standard_Failure &) {
7643  continue;
7644  }
7645  }
7646  element += std::to_string(idx);
7647  addExternal(Obj, element.c_str(), defining, intersection);
7648  element.resize(elementNameSize);
7649  }
7650  if (ExternalGeometry.getSize() == geometryCount)
7651  return -1;
7652  return geometryCount;
7653  }
7654 
7655  // get the actual lists of the externals
7656  std::vector<long> Types = ExternalTypes.getValues();
7657  std::vector<DocumentObject*> Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7658  std::vector<std::string> SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7659  if (Types.size() != Objects.size()) {
7660  Types.resize(Objects.size(), 0);
7661  }
7662 
7663  const std::vector<DocumentObject*> originalObjects = Objects;
7664  const std::vector<std::string> originalSubElements = SubElements;
7665 
7666  if (Objects.size() != SubElements.size()) {
7667  assert(0 /*counts of objects and subelements in external geometry links do not match*/);
7668  Base::Console().Error("Internal error: counts of objects and subelements in external "
7669  "geometry links do not match\n");
7670  return -1;
7671  }
7672 
7673  bool add = true;
7674  for (size_t i = 0; i < Objects.size(); ++i) {
7675  if (Objects[i] == Obj && std::string(SubName) == SubElements[i]) {
7676  if (Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Both
7677  || (Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Projection && !intersection)
7678  || (Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Intersection && intersection)) {
7679  Base::Console().Error("Link to %s already exists in this sketch.\n", SubName);
7680  return -1;
7681  }
7682  // Case where projections are already there when adding intersections.
7683  add = false;
7684  Types[i] = (int)ExtType::Both;
7685  }
7686  }
7687  if (add) {
7688  // add the new ones
7689  Objects.push_back(Obj);
7690  SubElements.emplace_back(SubName);
7691  Types.push_back((int)(intersection ? ExtType::Intersection : ExtType::Projection));
7692  if (intersection) {}
7693 
7694  // set the Link list.
7695  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects, SubElements);
7696  }
7697  ExternalTypes.setValues(Types);
7698 
7699  try {
7700  ExternalToAdd ext{ Obj, std::string(SubName), defining, intersection };
7701  rebuildExternalGeometry(ext);
7702  }
7703  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
7704  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7705  // revert to original values
7706  ExternalGeometry.setValues(originalObjects, originalSubElements);
7707  return -1;
7708  }
7709 
7710  acceptGeometry();// This may need to be refactored into onChanged for ExternalGeometry
7711 
7712  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
7713  return ExternalGeometry.getValues().size() - 1;
7714 }
7715 
7716 int SketchObject::delExternal(int ExtGeoId)
7717 {
7718  return delExternal(std::vector<int>{ExtGeoId});
7719 }
7720 
7721 int SketchObject::delExternal(const std::vector<int>& ExtGeoIds)
7722 {
7723  std::set<long> geoIds;
7724  for (int ExtGeoId : ExtGeoIds) {
7725  int GeoId = ExtGeoId >= 0 ? GeoEnum::RefExt - ExtGeoId : ExtGeoId;
7726  if (GeoId > GeoEnum::RefExt || -GeoId - 1 >= ExternalGeo.getSize())
7727  return -1;
7728 
7729  auto geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
7730  if (!geo)
7731  return -1;
7732 
7733  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
7734  geoIds.insert(egf->getId());
7735  if (egf->getRef().size()) {
7736  auto& refs = externalGeoRefMap[egf->getRef()];
7737  geoIds.insert(refs.begin(), refs.end());
7738  }
7739  }
7740 
7741  delExternalPrivate(geoIds, true);
7742  return 0;
7743 }
7744 
7745 void SketchObject::delExternalPrivate(const std::set<long> &ids, bool removeRef) {
7746 
7747  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true); // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7748 
7749  std::set<std::string> refs;
7750  // Must sort in reverse order so as to delete geo from back to front to
7751  // avoid index change
7752  std::set<int, std::greater<int>> geoIds;
7753 
7754  for(auto id : ids) {
7755  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
7756  if(it == externalGeoMap.end())
7757  continue;
7758 
7759  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(ExternalGeo[it->second]);
7760  if(removeRef && egf->getRef().size())
7761  refs.insert(egf->getRef());
7762  geoIds.insert(-it->second-1);
7763  }
7764 
7765  if(geoIds.empty())
7766  return;
7767 
7768  std::vector< Constraint * > newConstraints;
7769  for(auto cstr : Constraints.getValues()) {
7770  if(!geoIds.count(cstr->First) &&
7771  (cstr->Second==GeoEnum::GeoUndef || !geoIds.count(cstr->Second)) &&
7772  (cstr->Third==GeoEnum::GeoUndef || !geoIds.count(cstr->Third)))
7773  {
7774  bool cloned = false;
7775  int offset = 0;
7776  for(auto GeoId : geoIds) {
7777  GeoId += offset++;
7778  bool done = true;
7779  if (cstr->First < GeoId && cstr->First != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
7780  if (!cloned) {
7781  cloned = true;
7782  cstr = cstr->clone();
7783  }
7784  cstr->First += 1;
7785  done = false;
7786  }
7787  if (cstr->Second < GeoId && cstr->Second != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
7788  if (!cloned) {
7789  cloned = true;
7790  cstr = cstr->clone();
7791  }
7792  cstr->Second += 1;
7793  done = false;
7794  }
7795  if (cstr->Third < GeoId && cstr->Third != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
7796  if (!cloned) {
7797  cloned = true;
7798  cstr = cstr->clone();
7799  }
7800  cstr->Third += 1;
7801  done = false;
7802  }
7803  if(done) break;
7804  }
7805  newConstraints.push_back(cstr);
7806  }
7807  }
7808 
7809  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
7810  int offset = 0;
7811  for(auto geoId : geoIds) {
7812  int idx = -geoId-1;
7813  geos.erase(geos.begin()+idx-offset);
7814  ++offset;
7815  }
7816 
7817  if(refs.size()) {
7818  std::vector<std::string> newSubs;
7819  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> newObjs;
7820  const auto &subs = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7821  auto itSub = subs.begin();
7822  const auto &objs = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7823  auto itObj = objs.begin();
7824  bool touched = false;
7825  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == objs.size());
7826  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == subs.size());
7827  for(auto it=externalGeoRef.begin();it!=externalGeoRef.end();++it,++itObj,++itSub) {
7828  if(refs.count(*it)) {
7829  if(!touched) {
7830  touched = true;
7831  if(newObjs.empty()) {
7832  newObjs.insert(newObjs.end(),objs.begin(),itObj);
7833  newSubs.insert(newSubs.end(),subs.begin(),itSub);
7834  }
7835  }
7836  }else if(touched) {
7837  newObjs.push_back(*itObj);
7838  newSubs.push_back(*itSub);
7839  }
7840  }
7841  if(touched)
7842  ExternalGeometry.setValues(newObjs,newSubs);
7843  }
7844 
7845  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
7846 
7847  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
7848  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
7849  acceptGeometry(); // This may need to be refactored into OnChanged for ExternalGeometry.
7850 }
7851 
7852 int SketchObject::delAllExternal()
7853 {
7854  int count = 0; // the remaining count of the detached external geometry
7855  std::map<int,int> indexMap; // the index map of the remain external geometry
7856  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geos; // the remaining external geometry
7857  for(int i=0;i<ExternalGeo.getSize();++i) {
7858  auto geo = ExternalGeo[i];
7859  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
7860  if(egf->getRef().empty())
7861  indexMap[i] = count++;
7862  geos.push_back(geo);
7863  }
7864  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7865  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7866 
7867  // get the actual lists of the externals
7868  std::vector<DocumentObject*> Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7869  std::vector<std::string> SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7870 
7871  const std::vector<DocumentObject*> originalObjects = Objects;
7872  const std::vector<std::string> originalSubElements = SubElements;
7873 
7874  Objects.clear();
7875 
7876  SubElements.clear();
7877 
7878  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = Constraints.getValues();
7879  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints(0);
7880 
7881  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constraints.begin(); it != constraints.end();
7882  ++it) {
7883  if ((*it)->First > GeoEnum::RefExt
7884  && ((*it)->Second > GeoEnum::RefExt || (*it)->Second == GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
7885  && ((*it)->Third > GeoEnum::RefExt || (*it)->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef)) {
7886  Constraint* copiedConstr = (*it)->clone();
7887 
7888  newConstraints.push_back(copiedConstr);
7889  }
7890  }
7891 
7892  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects, SubElements);
7893  try {
7894  rebuildExternalGeometry();
7895  }
7896  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
7897  Base::Console().Error("%s\n", e.what());
7898  // revert to original values
7899  ExternalGeometry.setValues(originalObjects, originalSubElements);
7900  for (Constraint* it : newConstraints)
7901  delete it;
7902  return -1;
7903  }
7904 
7905  ExternalGeometry.setValue(0);
7906  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
7907  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
7908  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
7909  acceptGeometry();// This may need to be refactored into OnChanged for ExternalGeometry
7910  return 0;
7911 }
7912 
7913 int SketchObject::delConstraintsToExternal()
7914 {
7915  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
7916  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
7917 
7918  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = Constraints.getValuesForce();
7919  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints(0);
7920  int GeoId = GeoEnum::RefExt, NullId = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
7921  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constraints.begin(); it != constraints.end();
7922  ++it) {
7923  if ((*it)->First > GeoId && ((*it)->Second > GeoId || (*it)->Second == NullId)
7924  && ((*it)->Third > GeoId || (*it)->Third == NullId)) {
7925  newConstraints.push_back(*it);
7926  }
7927  }
7928 
7929  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
7930  Constraints.acceptGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
7931 
7932  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver
7933  if (noRecomputes)
7934  solve();
7935 
7936  return 0;
7937 }
7938 
7939 int SketchObject::attachExternal(
7940  const std::vector<int> &geoIds, App::DocumentObject *Obj, const char* SubName)
7941 {
7942  if (!isExternalAllowed(Obj->getDocument(), Obj))
7943  return -1;
7944 
7945  std::set<std::string> detached;
7946  std::set<int> idSet;
7947  for (int geoId : geoIds) {
7948  if (geoId > GeoEnum::RefExt || -geoId - 1 >= ExternalGeo.getSize())
7949  continue;
7950  auto geo = getGeometry(geoId);
7951  if(!geo)
7952  continue;
7953  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
7954  if(egf->getRef().size())
7955  detached.insert(egf->getRef());
7956  for(int id : getRelatedGeometry(geoId))
7957  idSet.insert(id);
7958  }
7959 
7960  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
7961 
7962  std::vector<DocumentObject*> Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
7963  auto itObj = Objects.begin();
7964  std::vector<std::string> SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
7965  auto itSub = SubElements.begin();
7966 
7967  assert(Objects.size()==SubElements.size());
7968  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == Objects.size());
7969 
7970  for(auto &key : externalGeoRef) {
7971  if (*itObj == Obj && *itSub == SubName){
7972  FC_ERR("Duplicate external element reference in " << getFullName() << ": " << key);
7973  return -1;
7974  }
7975  // detach old reference
7976  if(detached.count(key)) {
7977  itObj = Objects.erase(itObj);
7978  itSub = SubElements.erase(itSub);
7979  }else{
7980  ++itObj;
7981  ++itSub;
7982  }
7983  }
7984 
7985  // add the new ones
7986  Objects.push_back(Obj);
7987  SubElements.push_back(std::string(SubName));
7988 
7989  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects,SubElements);
7990  if(externalGeoRef.size()!=Objects.size())
7991  return -1;
7992 
7993  std::string ref = externalGeoRef.back();
7994  for(auto geoId : idSet) {
7995  auto &geo = geos[-geoId-1];
7996  geo = geo->clone();
7997  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->setRef(ref);
7998  }
7999 
8000  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
8001  rebuildExternalGeometry();
8002  return ExternalGeometry.getSize()-1;
8003 }
8004 
8005 std::vector<int> SketchObject::getRelatedGeometry(int GeoId) const {
8006  std::vector<int> res;
8007  if(GeoId>GeoEnum::RefExt || -GeoId-1>=ExternalGeo.getSize())
8008  return res;
8009  auto geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
8010  if(!geo)
8011  return res;
8012  const std::string &ref = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->getRef();
8013  if(!ref.size())
8014  return {GeoId};
8015  auto iter = externalGeoRefMap.find(ref);
8016  if(iter == externalGeoRefMap.end())
8017  return {GeoId};
8018  for(auto id : iter->second) {
8019  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
8020  if(it!=externalGeoMap.end())
8021  res.push_back(-it->second-1);
8022  }
8023  return res;
8024 }
8025 
8026 int SketchObject::syncGeometry(const std::vector<int> &geoIds) {
8027  bool touched = false;
8028  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
8029  std::set<int> idSet;
8030  for(int geoId : geoIds) {
8031  auto geo = getGeometry(geoId);
8032  if(!geo || !ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Frozen))
8033  continue;
8034  for(int gid : getRelatedGeometry(geoId))
8035  idSet.insert(gid);
8036  }
8037  for(int geoId : idSet) {
8038  if(geoId <= GeoEnum::RefExt && -geoId-1 < ExternalGeo.getSize()) {
8039  auto &geo = geos[-geoId-1];
8040  geo = geo->clone();
8041  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Sync);
8042  touched = true;
8043  }
8044  }
8045  if(touched)
8046  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
8047  return 0;
8048 }

8050 const Part::Geometry* SketchObject::_getGeometry(int GeoId) const
8051 {

8053  const std::vector<Part::Geometry *> &geomlist = getInternalGeometry();
8054  if (GeoId < int(geomlist.size()))
8055  return geomlist[GeoId];
8056  }
8057  else if (GeoId < 0 && -GeoId-1 < ExternalGeo.getSize())
8058  return ExternalGeo[-GeoId-1];
8059 
8060  return nullptr;
8061 }

8067  return GeoId;

8070  return -GeoId - 1;
8071 
8072  return GeoEnum::GeoUndef;

8075 int SketchObject::getGeoIdFromCompleteGeometryIndex(int completeGeometryIndex) const
8076 {
8077  int completeGeometryCount = int(Geometry.getSize() + ExternalGeo.getSize());
8078 
8079  if (completeGeometryIndex < 0 || completeGeometryIndex >= completeGeometryCount)
8080  return GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
8081 
8082  if (completeGeometryIndex < Geometry.getSize())
8083  return completeGeometryIndex;
8084  else
8085  return (completeGeometryIndex - completeGeometryCount);
8086 }

8106 // Auxiliary Method: returns vector projection in UV space of plane
8107 static gp_Vec2d ProjVecOnPlane_UV(const gp_Vec& V, const gp_Pln& Pl)
8108 {
8109  return gp_Vec2d(V.Dot(Pl.Position().XDirection()), V.Dot(Pl.Position().YDirection()));
8110 }
8111 
8112 // Auxiliary Method: returns vector projection in UVN space of plane
8113 static gp_Vec ProjVecOnPlane_UVN(const gp_Vec& V, const gp_Pln& Pl)
8114 {
8115  gp_Vec2d vector = ProjVecOnPlane_UV(V, Pl);
8116  return gp_Vec(vector.X(), vector.Y(), 0.0);
8117 }
8118 
8119 // Auxiliary Method: returns vector projection in XYZ space
8120 #if 0

8122 {
8123  return V.Dot(Pl.Position().XDirection()) * Pl.Position().XDirection() +
8124  V.Dot(Pl.Position().YDirection()) * Pl.Position().YDirection();
8125 }
8126 #endif

8128 // Auxiliary Method: returns point projection in UV space of plane
8129 static gp_Vec2d ProjPointOnPlane_UV(const gp_Pnt& P, const gp_Pln& Pl)
8130 {
8131  gp_Vec OP = gp_Vec(Pl.Location(), P);
8132  return ProjVecOnPlane_UV(OP, Pl);
8133 }
8134 
8135 // Auxiliary Method: returns point projection in UVN space of plane
8136 static gp_Vec ProjPointOnPlane_UVN(const gp_Pnt& P, const gp_Pln& Pl)
8137 {
8138  gp_Vec2d vec2 = ProjPointOnPlane_UV(P, Pl);
8139  return gp_Vec(vec2.X(), vec2.Y(), 0.0);
8140 }

8142 // Auxiliary Method: returns point projection in XYZ space
8143 static gp_Pnt ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(const gp_Pnt& P, const gp_Pln& Pl)
8144 {
8145  gp_Vec positionUVN = ProjPointOnPlane_UVN(P, Pl);
8146  return gp_Pnt((positionUVN.X() * Pl.Position().XDirection()
8147  + positionUVN.Y() * Pl.Position().YDirection() + gp_Vec(Pl.Location().XYZ()))
8148  .XYZ());
8149 }

8151 // Auxiliary method
8152 Part::Geometry* projectLine(const BRepAdaptor_Curve& curve, const Handle(Geom_Plane) & gPlane,
8153  const Base::Placement& invPlm)
8154 {
8155  double first = curve.FirstParameter();
8156 
8157  if (fabs(first) > 1E99) {
8158  // TODO: What is OCE's definition of Infinite?
8159  // TODO: The clean way to do this is to handle a new sketch geometry Geom::Line
8160  // but its a lot of work to implement...
8161  first = -10000;
8162  }
8163 
8164  double last = curve.LastParameter();
8165  if (fabs(last) > 1E99) {
8166  last = +10000;
8167  }
8168 
8169  gp_Pnt P1 = curve.Value(first);
8170  gp_Pnt P2 = curve.Value(last);
8171 
8172  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj1(P1, gPlane);
8173  P1 = proj1.NearestPoint();
8174  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj2(P2, gPlane);
8175  P2 = proj2.NearestPoint();
8176 
8177  Base::Vector3d p1(P1.X(), P1.Y(), P1.Z());
8178  Base::Vector3d p2(P2.X(), P2.Y(), P2.Z());
8179  invPlm.multVec(p1, p1);
8180  invPlm.multVec(p2, p2);
8181 
8182  if (Base::Distance(p1, p2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8183  Base::Vector3d p = (p1 + p2) / 2;
8184  Part::GeomPoint* point = new Part::GeomPoint(p);
8185  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(point, true);
8186  return point;
8187  }
8188  else {
8189  Part::GeomLineSegment* line = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
8190  line->setPoints(p1, p2);
8191  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(line, true);
8192  return line;
8193  }
8194 }
