8198 bool SketchObject::evaluateSupport()
8199 {
8200  // returns false if the shape is broken, null or non-planar
8201  App::DocumentObject* link = AttachmentSupport.getValue();
8202  if (!link || !link->isDerivedFrom<Part::Feature>())
8203  return false;
8204  return true;
8205 }
8206 
8207 static Part::Geometry *fitArcs(std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry> > &arcs,
8208  const gp_Pnt &P1,
8209  const gp_Pnt &P2,
8210  double tol)
8211 {
8212  double radius = 0.0;
8213  double m = 0.0;
8214  Base::Vector3d center;
8215  for (auto &geo : arcs) {
8216  if (auto arc = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>(geo.get())) {
8217  if (radius == 0.0) {
8218  radius = arc->getRadius();
8219  center = arc->getCenter();
8220  double f = arc->getFirstParameter();
8221  double l = arc->getLastParameter();
8222  m = (l-f)*0.5 + f; // middle parameter
8223  } else if (std::abs(radius - arc->getRadius()) > tol)
8224  return nullptr;
8225  } else
8226  return nullptr;
8227  }
8228  if (radius == 0.0) {
8229  return nullptr;
8230  }
8231  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8232  Part::GeomCircle* circle = new Part::GeomCircle();
8233  circle->setCenter(center);
8234  circle->setRadius(radius);
8235  return circle;
8236  }
8237  if (arcs.size() == 1) {
8238  auto res = arcs.front().release();
8239  arcs.clear();
8240  return res;
8241  }
8242 
8243  GeomLProp_CLProps prop(Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(arcs.front()->handle()),m,0,Precision::Confusion());
8244  gp_Pnt midPoint = prop.Value();
8245  GC_MakeArcOfCircle arc(P1, midPoint, P2);
8246  auto geo = new Part::GeomArcOfCircle();
8247  geo->setHandle(arc.Value());
8248  return geo;
8249 }
8250 
8251 void SketchObject::validateExternalLinks()
8252 {
8253  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
8254  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
8255 
8256  std::vector<DocumentObject*> Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
8257  std::vector<std::string> SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
8258 
8259  bool rebuild = false;
8260 
8261  for (int i = 0; i < int(Objects.size()); i++) {
8262  const App::DocumentObject* Obj = Objects[i];
8263  const std::string SubElement = SubElements[i];
8264 
8265  TopoDS_Shape refSubShape;
8266  bool removeBadLink = false;
8267  try {
8268  if (Obj->isDerivedFrom<Part::Datum>()) {
8269  const Part::Datum* datum = static_cast<const Part::Datum*>(Obj);
8270  refSubShape = datum->getShape();
8271  }
8272  else {
8273  const Part::Feature* refObj = static_cast<const Part::Feature*>(Obj);
8274  const Part::TopoShape& refShape = refObj->Shape.getShape();
8275  refSubShape = refShape.getSubShape(SubElement.c_str());
8276  }
8277  }
8278  catch ( Base::IndexError& indexError) {
8279  removeBadLink = true;
8280  Base::Console().Warning(
8281  this->getFullLabel(), (indexError.getMessage() + "\n").c_str());
8282  }
8283  catch ( Base::ValueError& valueError ) {
8284  removeBadLink = true;
8285  Base::Console().Warning(
8286  this->getFullLabel(), (valueError.getMessage() + "\n").c_str());
8287  }
8288  catch (Standard_Failure&) {
8289  removeBadLink = true;
8290  }
8291  if ( removeBadLink ) {
8292  rebuild = true;
8293  Objects.erase(Objects.begin() + i);
8294  SubElements.erase(SubElements.begin() + i);
8295 
8296  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = Constraints.getValues();
8297  std::vector<Constraint*> newConstraints(0);
8298  int GeoId = GeoEnum::RefExt - i;
8299  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constraints.begin();
8300  it != constraints.end();
8301  ++it) {
8302  if ((*it)->First != GeoId && (*it)->Second != GeoId && (*it)->Third != GeoId) {
8303  Constraint* copiedConstr = (*it)->clone();
8304  if (copiedConstr->First < GeoId && copiedConstr->First != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
8305  copiedConstr->First += 1;
8306  if (copiedConstr->Second < GeoId && copiedConstr->Second != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
8307  copiedConstr->Second += 1;
8308  if (copiedConstr->Third < GeoId && copiedConstr->Third != GeoEnum::GeoUndef)
8309  copiedConstr->Third += 1;
8310 
8311  newConstraints.push_back(copiedConstr);
8312  }
8313  }
8314 
8315  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
8316  i--;// we deleted an item, so the next one took its place
8317  }
8318  }
8319 
8320  if (rebuild) {
8321  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects, SubElements);
8322  rebuildExternalGeometry();
8323  acceptGeometry();// This may need to be refactor to OnChanged for ExternalGeo
8324  solve(true); // we have to update this sketch and everything depending on it.
8325  }
8326 }
8327 
8328 namespace {
8329 void processEdge2(TopoDS_Edge& projEdge, std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry>>& geos)
8330 {
8331  BRepAdaptor_Curve projCurve(projEdge);
8332  if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Line) {
8333  gp_Pnt P1 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.FirstParameter());
8334  gp_Pnt P2 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.LastParameter());
8335  Base::Vector3d p1(P1.X(), P1.Y(), P1.Z());
8336  Base::Vector3d p2(P2.X(), P2.Y(), P2.Z());
8337 
8338  if (Base::Distance(p1, p2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8339  Base::Vector3d p = (p1 + p2) / 2;
8340  auto* point = new Part::GeomPoint(p);
8341  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(point, true);
8342  geos.emplace_back(point);
8343  }
8344  else {
8345  auto* line = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
8346  line->setPoints(p1, p2);
8347  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(line, true);
8348  geos.emplace_back(line);
8349  }
8350  }
8351  else if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Circle) {
8352  gp_Circ c = projCurve.Circle();
8353  gp_Pnt p = c.Location();
8354  gp_Pnt P1 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.FirstParameter());
8355  gp_Pnt P2 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.LastParameter());
8356 
8357  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8358  auto* circle = new Part::GeomCircle();
8359  circle->setRadius(c.Radius());
8360  circle->setCenter(Base::Vector3d(p.X(), p.Y(), p.Z()));
8361 
8362  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(circle, true);
8363  geos.emplace_back(circle);
8364  }
8365  else {
8366  auto* arc = new Part::GeomArcOfCircle();
8367  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = new Geom_Circle(c);
8368  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve,
8369  projCurve.FirstParameter(),
8370  projCurve.LastParameter());
8371  arc->setHandle(tCurve);
8372  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(arc, true);
8373  geos.emplace_back(arc);
8374  }
8375  }
8376  else if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_BSplineCurve) {
8377  // Unfortunately, a normal projection of a circle can also give
8378  // a Bspline Split the spline into arcs
8379  GeomConvert_BSplineCurveKnotSplitting bSplineSplitter(projCurve.BSpline(), 2);
8380  auto* bspline = new Part::GeomBSplineCurve(projCurve.BSpline());
8381  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(bspline, true);
8382  geos.emplace_back(bspline);
8383  }
8384  else if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Hyperbola) {
8385  gp_Hypr e = projCurve.Hyperbola();
8386  gp_Pnt p = e.Location();
8387  gp_Pnt P1 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.FirstParameter());
8388  gp_Pnt P2 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.LastParameter());
8389 
8390  gp_Dir normal = e.Axis().Direction();
8391  gp_Dir xdir = e.XAxis().Direction();
8392  gp_Ax2 xdirref(p, normal);
8393 
8394  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8395  auto* hyperbola = new Part::GeomHyperbola();
8396  hyperbola->setMajorRadius(e.MajorRadius());
8397  hyperbola->setMinorRadius(e.MinorRadius());
8398  hyperbola->setCenter(Base::Vector3d(p.X(), p.Y(), p.Z()));
8399  hyperbola->setAngleXU(-xdir.AngleWithRef(xdirref.XDirection(), normal));
8400  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(hyperbola, true);
8401  geos.emplace_back(hyperbola);
8402  }
8403  else {
8404  auto* aoh = new Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola();
8405  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = new Geom_Hyperbola(e);
8406  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve,
8407  projCurve.FirstParameter(),
8408  projCurve.LastParameter());
8409  aoh->setHandle(tCurve);
8410  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(aoh, true);
8411  geos.emplace_back(aoh);
8412  }
8413  }
8414  else if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Parabola) {
8415  gp_Parab e = projCurve.Parabola();
8416  gp_Pnt p = e.Location();
8417  gp_Pnt P1 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.FirstParameter());
8418  gp_Pnt P2 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.LastParameter());
8419 
8420  gp_Dir normal = e.Axis().Direction();
8421  gp_Dir xdir = e.XAxis().Direction();
8422  gp_Ax2 xdirref(p, normal);
8423 
8424  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8425  auto* parabola = new Part::GeomParabola();
8426  parabola->setFocal(e.Focal());
8427  parabola->setCenter(Base::Vector3d(p.X(), p.Y(), p.Z()));
8428  parabola->setAngleXU(-xdir.AngleWithRef(xdirref.XDirection(), normal));
8429  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(parabola, true);
8430  geos.emplace_back(parabola);
8431  }
8432  else {
8433  auto* aop = new Part::GeomArcOfParabola();
8434  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = new Geom_Parabola(e);
8435  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve,
8436  projCurve.FirstParameter(),
8437  projCurve.LastParameter());
8438  aop->setHandle(tCurve);
8439  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(aop, true);
8440  geos.emplace_back(aop);
8441  }
8442  }
8443  else if (projCurve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Ellipse) {
8444  gp_Elips e = projCurve.Ellipse();
8445  gp_Pnt p = e.Location();
8446  gp_Pnt P1 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.FirstParameter());
8447  gp_Pnt P2 = projCurve.Value(projCurve.LastParameter());
8448 
8449  // gp_Dir normal = e.Axis().Direction();
8450  gp_Dir normal = gp_Dir(0, 0, 1);
8451  gp_Ax2 xdirref(p, normal);
8452 
8453  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8454  auto* ellipse = new Part::GeomEllipse();
8455  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) curve = new Geom_Ellipse(e);
8456  ellipse->setHandle(curve);
8457  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(ellipse, true);
8458  geos.emplace_back(ellipse);
8459  }
8460  else {
8461  auto* aoe = new Part::GeomArcOfEllipse();
8462  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve = new Geom_Ellipse(e);
8463  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve,
8464  projCurve.FirstParameter(),
8465  projCurve.LastParameter());
8466  aoe->setHandle(tCurve);
8467  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(aoe, true);
8468  geos.emplace_back(aoe);
8469  }
8470  }
8471  else {
8472  throw Base::NotImplementedError("Not yet supported geometry for external geometry");
8473  }
8474 }
8475 
8476 void processEdge(const TopoDS_Edge& edge,
8477  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry>>& geos,
8478  const Handle(Geom_Plane)& gPlane,
8479  const Base::Placement& invPlm,
8480  const gp_Trsf& mov,
8481  const gp_Pln& sketchPlane,
8482  const Base::Rotation& invRot,
8483  gp_Ax3& sketchAx3,
8484  TopoDS_Shape& aProjFace)
8485 {
8486  BRepAdaptor_Curve curve(edge);
8487  if (curve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Line) {
8488  geos.emplace_back(projectLine(curve, gPlane, invPlm));
8489  }
8490  else if (curve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Circle) {
8491  gp_Dir vec1 = sketchPlane.Axis().Direction();
8492  gp_Dir vec2 = curve.Circle().Axis().Direction();
8493  if (vec1.IsParallel(vec2, Precision::Confusion())) {
8494  gp_Circ circle = curve.Circle();
8495  gp_Pnt cnt = circle.Location();
8496  gp_Pnt beg = curve.Value(curve.FirstParameter());
8497  gp_Pnt end = curve.Value(curve.LastParameter());
8498 
8499  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj(cnt, gPlane);
8500  cnt = proj.NearestPoint();
8501  circle.SetLocation(cnt);
8502  cnt.Transform(mov);
8503  circle.Transform(mov);
8504 
8505  if (beg.SquareDistance(end) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8506  auto* gCircle = new Part::GeomCircle();
8507  gCircle->setRadius(circle.Radius());
8508  gCircle->setCenter(Base::Vector3d(cnt.X(), cnt.Y(), cnt.Z()));
8509 
8510  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(gCircle, true);
8511  geos.emplace_back(gCircle);
8512  }
8513  else {
8514  auto* gArc = new Part::GeomArcOfCircle();
8515  Handle(Geom_Curve) hCircle = new Geom_Circle(circle);
8516  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(
8517  hCircle, curve.FirstParameter(), curve.LastParameter());
8518  gArc->setHandle(tCurve);
8519  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(gArc, true);
8520  geos.emplace_back(gArc);
8521  }
8522  }
8523  else {
8524  // creates an ellipse or a segment
8525 
8526  gp_Dir vec1 = sketchPlane.Axis().Direction();
8527  gp_Dir vec2 = curve.Circle().Axis().Direction();
8528  gp_Circ origCircle = curve.Circle();
8529 
8530  if (vec1.IsNormal(
8531  vec2, Precision::Angular())) {// circle's normal vector in plane:
8532  // projection is a line
8533  // define center by projection
8534  gp_Pnt cnt = origCircle.Location();
8535  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj(cnt, gPlane);
8536  cnt = proj.NearestPoint();
8537 
8538  gp_Dir dirOrientation = gp_Dir(vec1 ^ vec2);
8539  gp_Dir dirLine(dirOrientation);
8540 
8541  auto* projectedSegment = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
8542  Geom_Line ligne(cnt, dirLine);// helper object to compute end points
8543  gp_Pnt P1, P2; // end points of the segment, OCC style
8544 
8545  ligne.D0(-origCircle.Radius(), P1);
8546  ligne.D0(origCircle.Radius(), P2);
8547 
8548  if (!curve.IsClosed()) {// arc of circle
8549 
8550  // start point of arc of circle
8551  gp_Pnt pntF = curve.Value(curve.FirstParameter());
8552  // end point of arc of circle
8553  gp_Pnt pntL = curve.Value(curve.LastParameter());
8554 
8555  double alpha =
8556  dirOrientation.AngleWithRef(curve.Circle().XAxis().Direction(),
8557  curve.Circle().Axis().Direction());
8558 
8559  double baseAngle = curve.FirstParameter();
8560 
8561  int tours = 0;
8562  double startAngle = baseAngle + alpha;
8563  // bring startAngle back in [-pi/2 , 3pi/2[
8564  while (startAngle < -M_PI / 2.0 && tours < 10) {
8565  startAngle = baseAngle + ++tours * 2.0 * M_PI + alpha;
8566  }
8567  while (startAngle >= 3.0 * M_PI / 2.0 && tours > -10) {
8568  startAngle = baseAngle + --tours * 2.0 * M_PI + alpha;
8569  }
8570 
8571  // apply same offset to end angle
8572  double endAngle = curve.LastParameter() + startAngle - baseAngle;
8573 
8574  if (startAngle <= 0.0) {
8575  if (endAngle <= 0.0) {
8576  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8577  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8578  }
8579  else {
8580  if (endAngle <= fabs(startAngle)) {
8581  // P2 = P2 already defined
8582  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8583  }
8584  else if (endAngle < M_PI) {
8585  // P2 = P2, already defined
8586  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8587  }
8588  else {
8589  // P1 = P1, already defined
8590  // P2 = P2, already defined
8591  }
8592  }
8593  }
8594  else if (startAngle < M_PI) {
8595  if (endAngle < M_PI) {
8596  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8597  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8598  }
8599  else if (endAngle < 2.0 * M_PI - startAngle) {
8600  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8601  // P1 = P1, already defined
8602  }
8603  else if (endAngle < 2.0 * M_PI) {
8604  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8605  // P1 = P1, already defined
8606  }
8607  else {
8608  // P1 = P1, already defined
8609  // P2 = P2, already defined
8610  }
8611  }
8612  else {
8613  if (endAngle < 2 * M_PI) {
8614  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8615  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8616  }
8617  else if (endAngle < 4 * M_PI - startAngle) {
8618  P1 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntF, sketchPlane);
8619  // P2 = P2, already defined
8620  }
8621  else if (endAngle < 3 * M_PI) {
8622  // P1 = P1, already defined
8623  P2 = ProjPointOnPlane_XYZ(pntL, sketchPlane);
8624  }
8625  else {
8626  // P1 = P1, already defined
8627  // P2 = P2, already defined
8628  }
8629  }
8630  }
8631 
8632  Base::Vector3d p1(P1.X(), P1.Y(), P1.Z());// ends of segment FCAD style
8633  Base::Vector3d p2(P2.X(), P2.Y(), P2.Z());
8634  invPlm.multVec(p1, p1);
8635  invPlm.multVec(p2, p2);
8636 
8637  projectedSegment->setPoints(p1, p2);
8638  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(projectedSegment, true);
8639  geos.emplace_back(projectedSegment);
8640  }
8641  else {// general case, full circle
8642  gp_Pnt cnt = origCircle.Location();
8643  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj(cnt, gPlane);
8644  // projection of circle center on sketch plane, 3D space
8645  cnt = proj.NearestPoint();
8646  // converting to FCAD style vector
8647  Base::Vector3d p(cnt.X(), cnt.Y(), cnt.Z());
8648  // transforming towards sketch's (x,y) coordinates
8649  invPlm.multVec(p, p);
8650 
8651 
8652  gp_Vec vecMajorAxis = vec1 ^ vec2;// major axis in 3D space
8653 
8654  double minorRadius;// TODO use data type of vectors around...
8655  double cosTheta;
8656  // cos of angle between the two planes, assuming vectirs are normalized
8657  // to 1
8658  cosTheta = fabs(vec1.Dot(vec2));
8659  minorRadius = origCircle.Radius() * cosTheta;
8660 
8661  // maj axis into FCAD style vector
8662  Base::Vector3d vectorMajorAxis(
8663  vecMajorAxis.X(), vecMajorAxis.Y(), vecMajorAxis.Z());
8664  // transforming to sketch's (x,y) coordinates
8665  invRot.multVec(vectorMajorAxis, vectorMajorAxis);
8666  // back to OCC
8667  vecMajorAxis.SetXYZ(
8668  gp_XYZ(vectorMajorAxis[0], vectorMajorAxis[1], vectorMajorAxis[2]));
8669 
8670  // NB: force normal of ellipse to be normal of sketch's plane.
8671  gp_Ax2 refFrameEllipse(
8672  gp_Pnt(gp_XYZ(p[0], p[1], p[2])), gp_Vec(0, 0, 1), vecMajorAxis);
8673  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) curve =
8674  new Geom_Ellipse(refFrameEllipse, origCircle.Radius(), minorRadius);
8675  Part::GeomEllipse* ellipse = new Part::GeomEllipse();
8676  ellipse->setHandle(curve);
8677  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(ellipse, true);
8678  geos.emplace_back(ellipse);
8679  }
8680  }
8681  }
8682  else if (curve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Ellipse) {
8683 
8684  gp_Pnt P1 = curve.Value(curve.FirstParameter());
8685  gp_Pnt P2 = curve.Value(curve.LastParameter());
8686  gp_Elips elipsOrig = curve.Ellipse();
8687  gp_Elips elipsDest;
8688  gp_Pnt origCenter = elipsOrig.Location();
8689  gp_Pnt destCenter = ProjPointOnPlane_UVN(origCenter, sketchPlane).XYZ();
8690 
8691  gp_Dir origAxisMajorDir = elipsOrig.XAxis().Direction();
8692  gp_Vec origAxisMajor = elipsOrig.MajorRadius() * gp_Vec(origAxisMajorDir);
8693  gp_Dir origAxisMinorDir = elipsOrig.YAxis().Direction();
8694  gp_Vec origAxisMinor = elipsOrig.MinorRadius() * gp_Vec(origAxisMinorDir);
8695 
8696  // Here, it used to be a test for parallel direction between the sketchplane and
8697  // the elipsOrig, in which the original ellipse would be copied and translated
8698  // to the new position. The problem with that approach is that for the sketcher
8699  // the normal vector is always (0,0,1). If the original ellipse was not on the
8700  // XY plane, the copy will not be either. Then, the dimensions would be wrong
8701  // because of the different major axis direction (which is not projected on the
8702  // XY plane). So here, we default to the more general ellipse construction
8703  // algorithm.
8704  //
8705  // Doing that solves:
8706  // https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&t=55284#p477522
8707 
8708  // GENERAL ELLIPSE CONSTRUCTION ALGORITHM
8709  //
8710  // look for major axis of projected ellipse
8711  //
8712  // t is the parameter along the origin ellipse
8713  // OM(t) = origCenter
8714  // + majorRadius * cos(t) * origAxisMajorDir
8715  // + minorRadius * sin(t) * origAxisMinorDir
8716  gp_Vec2d PA = ProjVecOnPlane_UV(origAxisMajor, sketchPlane);
8717  gp_Vec2d PB = ProjVecOnPlane_UV(origAxisMinor, sketchPlane);
8718  double t_max = 2.0 * PA.Dot(PB) / (PA.SquareMagnitude() - PB.SquareMagnitude());
8719  t_max = 0.5 * atan(t_max);// gives new major axis is most cases, but not all
8720  double t_min = t_max + 0.5 * M_PI;
8721 
8722  // ON_max = OM(t_max) gives the point, which projected on the sketch plane,
8723  // becomes the apoapse of the projected ellipse.
8724  gp_Vec ON_max = origAxisMajor * cos(t_max) + origAxisMinor * sin(t_max);
8725  gp_Vec ON_min = origAxisMajor * cos(t_min) + origAxisMinor * sin(t_min);
8726  gp_Vec destAxisMajor = ProjVecOnPlane_UVN(ON_max, sketchPlane);
8727  gp_Vec destAxisMinor = ProjVecOnPlane_UVN(ON_min, sketchPlane);
8728 
8729  double RDest = destAxisMajor.Magnitude();
8730  double rDest = destAxisMinor.Magnitude();
8731 
8732  if (RDest < rDest) {
8733  double rTmp = rDest;
8734  rDest = RDest;
8735  RDest = rTmp;
8736  gp_Vec axisTmp = destAxisMajor;
8737  destAxisMajor = destAxisMinor;
8738  destAxisMinor = axisTmp;
8739  }
8740 
8741  double sens = sketchAx3.Direction().Dot(elipsOrig.Position().Direction());
8742  int flip = sens > 0.0 ? 1.0 : -1.0;
8743  gp_Ax2 destCurveAx2(destCenter, gp_Dir(0, 0, flip), gp_Dir(destAxisMajor));
8744 
8745  // projection is a circle
8746  if ((RDest - rDest) < (double)Precision::Confusion()) {
8747  Handle(Geom_Circle) curve2 = new Geom_Circle(destCurveAx2, 0.5 * (rDest + RDest));
8748  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8749  auto* circle = new Part::GeomCircle();
8750  circle->setHandle(curve2);
8751  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(circle, true);
8752  geos.emplace_back(circle);
8753  }
8754  else {
8755  auto* arc = new Part::GeomArcOfCircle();
8756  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve2,
8757  curve.FirstParameter(),
8758  curve.LastParameter());
8759  arc->setHandle(tCurve);
8760  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(arc, true);
8761  geos.emplace_back(arc);
8762  }
8763  }
8764  else {
8765  if (sketchPlane.Position().Direction().IsNormal(
8766  elipsOrig.Position().Direction(), Precision::Angular())) {
8767  gp_Vec start = gp_Vec(destCenter.XYZ()) + destAxisMajor;
8768  gp_Vec end = gp_Vec(destCenter.XYZ()) - destAxisMajor;
8769 
8770  auto* projectedSegment = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
8771  projectedSegment->setPoints(
8772  Base::Vector3d(start.X(), start.Y(), start.Z()),
8773  Base::Vector3d(end.X(), end.Y(), end.Z()));
8774  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(projectedSegment, true);
8775  geos.emplace_back(projectedSegment);
8776  }
8777  else {
8778 
8779  elipsDest.SetPosition(destCurveAx2);
8780  elipsDest.SetMajorRadius(destAxisMajor.Magnitude());
8781  elipsDest.SetMinorRadius(destAxisMinor.Magnitude());
8782 
8783 
8784  if (P1.SquareDistance(P2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
8785  Handle(Geom_Ellipse) curve = new Geom_Ellipse(elipsDest);
8786  auto* ellipse = new Part::GeomEllipse();
8787  ellipse->setHandle(curve);
8788  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(ellipse, true);
8789  geos.emplace_back(ellipse);
8790  }
8791  else {
8792  auto* aoe = new Part::GeomArcOfEllipse();
8793  Handle(Geom_Curve) curve2 = new Geom_Ellipse(elipsDest);
8794  Handle(Geom_TrimmedCurve) tCurve = new Geom_TrimmedCurve(curve2,
8795  curve.FirstParameter(),
8796  curve.LastParameter());
8797  aoe->setHandle(tCurve);
8798  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(aoe, true);
8799  geos.emplace_back(aoe);
8800  }
8801  }
8802  }
8803  }
8804  else {
8805  try {
8806  BRepOffsetAPI_NormalProjection mkProj(aProjFace);
8807  mkProj.Add(edge);
8808  mkProj.Build();
8809  const TopoDS_Shape& projShape = mkProj.Projection();
8810  if (!projShape.IsNull()) {
8811  TopExp_Explorer xp;
8812  for (xp.Init(projShape, TopAbs_EDGE); xp.More(); xp.Next()) {
8813  TopoDS_Edge projEdge = TopoDS::Edge(xp.Current());
8814  TopLoc_Location loc(mov);
8815  projEdge.Location(loc);
8816  processEdge2(projEdge, geos);
8817  }
8818  }
8819  }
8820  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
8821  throw Base::CADKernelError(e.GetMessageString());
8822  }
8823  }
8824 }
8825 
8826 std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> projectShape(const TopoDS_Shape& inShape, const gp_Ax3& viewAxis)
8827 {
8828  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> res;
8829  Handle(HLRBRep_Algo) brep_hlr;
8830  try {
8831  brep_hlr = new HLRBRep_Algo();
8832  brep_hlr->Add(inShape);
8833 
8834  gp_Trsf aTrsf;
8835  aTrsf.SetTransformation(viewAxis);
8836  HLRAlgo_Projector projector(aTrsf, false, 1);
8837 
8838  brep_hlr->Projector(projector);
8839  brep_hlr->Update();
8840  brep_hlr->Hide();
8841  }
8842  catch (const Standard_Failure& e) {
8843  Base::Console().Error("GO::projectShape - OCC error - %s - while projecting shape\n",
8844  e.GetMessageString());
8845  throw Base::RuntimeError("SketchObject::projectShape - OCC error");
8846  }
8847  catch (...) {
8848  throw Base::RuntimeError("SketchObject::projectShape - unknown error");
8849  }
8850 
8851  try {
8852  HLRBRep_HLRToShape hlrToShape(brep_hlr);
8853  if (!hlrToShape.VCompound().IsNull()) {
8854  //TopAbs_COMPOUND to TopAbs_EDGE
8855  res.push_back(hlrToShape.VCompound());
8856  }
8857 
8858  if (!hlrToShape.Rg1LineVCompound().IsNull()) {
8859  res.push_back(hlrToShape.Rg1LineVCompound());
8860  }
8861 
8862  /*if (!hlrToShape.RgNLineVCompound().IsNull()) {
8863  res.push_back(hlrToShape.RgNLineVCompound());
8864  }*/ // we don't need the seams.
8865 
8866  if (!hlrToShape.OutLineVCompound().IsNull()) {
8867  res.push_back(hlrToShape.OutLineVCompound());
8868  }
8869 
8870  if (!hlrToShape.IsoLineVCompound().IsNull()) {
8871  res.push_back(hlrToShape.IsoLineVCompound());
8872  }
8873 
8874  if (!hlrToShape.HCompound().IsNull()) {
8875  res.push_back(hlrToShape.HCompound());
8876  }
8877 
8878  if (!hlrToShape.Rg1LineHCompound().IsNull()) {
8879  res.push_back(hlrToShape.Rg1LineHCompound());
8880  }
8881 
8882  /*if (!hlrToShape.RgNLineHCompound().IsNull()) {
8883  res.push_back(hlrToShape.RgNLineHCompound());
8884  }*/
8885 
8886  if (!hlrToShape.OutLineHCompound().IsNull()) {
8887  res.push_back(hlrToShape.OutLineHCompound());
8888  }
8889 
8890  if (!hlrToShape.IsoLineHCompound().IsNull()) {
8891  res.push_back(hlrToShape.IsoLineHCompound());
8892  }
8893  }
8894  catch (const Standard_Failure&) {
8895  throw Base::RuntimeError(
8896  "SketchObject::projectShape - OCC error occurred while extracting edges");
8897  }
8898  catch (...) {
8899  throw Base::RuntimeError(
8900  "SketchObject::projectShape - unknown error occurred while extracting edges");
8901  }
8902 
8903  return res;
8904 }
8905 }
8906 
8907 void SketchObject::rebuildExternalGeometry(std::optional<ExternalToAdd> extToAdd)
8908 {
8909  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true); // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
8910 
8911  // get the actual lists of the externals
8912  auto Types = ExternalTypes.getValues();
8913  auto Objects = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
8914  auto SubElements = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
8915  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == Objects.size());
8916  auto keys = externalGeoRef;
8917  if (Types.size() != Objects.size()) {
8918  Types.resize(Objects.size(), 0);
8919  }
8920 
8921  // re-check for any missing geometry element. The code here has a side
8922  // effect that the linked external geometry will continue to work even if
8923  // ExternalGeometry is wiped out.
8924  for(auto &geo : ExternalGeo.getValues()) {
8925  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
8926  if(egf->getRef().size() && egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing)) {
8927  const std::string &ref = egf->getRef();
8928  auto pos = ref.find('.');
8929  if(pos == std::string::npos)
8930  continue;
8931  std::string objName = ref.substr(0,pos);
8932  auto obj = getDocument()->getObject(objName.c_str());
8933  if(!obj)
8934  continue;
8935  App::ElementNamePair elementName;
8936  App::GeoFeature::resolveElement(obj,ref.c_str()+pos+1,elementName);
8937  if(elementName.oldName.size()
8938  && !App::GeoFeature::hasMissingElement(elementName.oldName.c_str()))
8939  {
8940  Objects.push_back(obj);
8941  SubElements.push_back(elementName.oldName);
8942  keys.push_back(ref);
8943  }
8944  }
8945  }
8946 
8947  Base::Placement Plm = Placement.getValue();
8948  Base::Vector3d Pos = Plm.getPosition();
8949  Base::Rotation Rot = Plm.getRotation();
8950  Base::Rotation invRot = Rot.inverse();
8951  Base::Vector3d dN(0, 0, 1);
8952  Rot.multVec(dN, dN);
8953  Base::Vector3d dX(1, 0, 0);
8954  Rot.multVec(dX, dX);
8955 
8956  Base::Placement invPlm = Plm.inverse();
8957  Base::Matrix4D invMat = invPlm.toMatrix();
8958  gp_Trsf mov;
8959  mov.SetValues(invMat[0][0],
8960  invMat[0][1],
8961  invMat[0][2],
8962  invMat[0][3],
8963  invMat[1][0],
8964  invMat[1][1],
8965  invMat[1][2],
8966  invMat[1][3],
8967  invMat[2][0],
8968  invMat[2][1],
8969  invMat[2][2],
8970  invMat[2][3]);
8971 
8972  gp_Ax3 sketchAx3(
8973  gp_Pnt(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.z), gp_Dir(dN.x, dN.y, dN.z), gp_Dir(dX.x, dX.y, dX.z));
8974  gp_Pln sketchPlane(sketchAx3);
8975 
8976  Handle(Geom_Plane) gPlane = new Geom_Plane(sketchPlane);
8977  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeFace mkFace(sketchPlane);
8978  TopoDS_Shape aProjFace = mkFace.Shape();
8979 
8980  std::set<std::string> refSet;
8981  // We use a vector here to keep the order (roughly) the same as ExternalGeometry
8982  std::vector<std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry> > > newGeos;
8983  newGeos.reserve(Objects.size());
8984  for (int i=0; i < int(Objects.size()); i++) {
8985  const App::DocumentObject *Obj=Objects[i];
8986  const std::string &SubElement=SubElements[i];
8987  const std::string &key = keys[i];
8988 
8989  bool beingCreated = false;
8990  if (extToAdd) {
8991  beingCreated = extToAdd->obj == Obj && extToAdd->subname == SubElement;
8992  }
8993 
8994  bool projection = Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Projection || Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Both;
8995  bool intersection = Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Intersection || Types[i] == (int)ExtType::Both;
8996 
8997  // Skip frozen geometries
8998  bool frozen = false;
8999  bool sync = false;
9000  for(auto id : externalGeoRefMap[key]) {
9001  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
9002  if(it != externalGeoMap.end()) {
9003  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(ExternalGeo[it->second]);
9004  if(egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Frozen)) {
9005  frozen = true;
9006  }
9007  if (egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Sync)) {
9008  sync = true;
9009  }
9010  }
9011  }
9012  if(frozen && !sync) {
9013  refSet.insert(std::move(key));
9014  continue;
9015  }
9016  if (!Obj || !Obj->getNameInDocument()) {
9017  continue;
9018  }
9019 
9020  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Part::Geometry> > geos;
9021 
9022  auto importVertex = [&](const TopoDS_Shape& refSubShape) {
9023  gp_Pnt P = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(refSubShape));
9024  GeomAPI_ProjectPointOnSurf proj(P, gPlane);
9025  P = proj.NearestPoint();
9026  Base::Vector3d p(P.X(), P.Y(), P.Z());
9027  invPlm.multVec(p, p);
9028 
9029  Part::GeomPoint* point = new Part::GeomPoint(p);
9030  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(point, true);
9031  geos.emplace_back(point);
9032  };
9033 
9034  try {
9035  TopoDS_Shape refSubShape;
9036 
9037  if (Obj->isDerivedFrom<Part::Datum>()) {
9038  auto* datum = static_cast<const Part::Datum*>(Obj);
9039  refSubShape = datum->getShape();
9040  }
9041  else if (Obj->isDerivedFrom<Part::Feature>()) {
9042  auto* refObj = static_cast<const Part::Feature*>(Obj);
9043  const Part::TopoShape& refShape = refObj->Shape.getShape();
9044  refSubShape = refShape.getSubShape(SubElement.c_str());
9045  }
9046  else if (Obj->isDerivedFrom<App::Plane>()) {
9047  auto* pl = static_cast<const App::Plane*>(Obj);
9048  Base::Placement plm = pl->Placement.getValue();
9049  Base::Vector3d base = plm.getPosition();
9050  Base::Rotation rot = plm.getRotation();
9051  Base::Vector3d normal(0, 0, 1);
9052  rot.multVec(normal, normal);
9053  gp_Pln plane(gp_Pnt(base.x, base.y, base.z), gp_Dir(normal.x, normal.y, normal.z));
9054  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeFace fBuilder(plane);
9055  if (!fBuilder.IsDone())
9056  throw Base::RuntimeError(
9057  "Sketcher: addExternal(): Failed to build face from App::Plane");
9058 
9059  TopoDS_Face f = TopoDS::Face(fBuilder.Shape());
9060  refSubShape = f;
9061  }
9062  else {
9063  throw Base::TypeError(
9064  "Datum feature type is not yet supported as external geometry for a sketch");
9065  }
9066 
9067  if (projection) {
9068  switch (refSubShape.ShapeType()) {
9069  case TopAbs_FACE: {
9070  const TopoDS_Face& face = TopoDS::Face(refSubShape);
9071  BRepAdaptor_Surface surface(face);
9072  if (surface.GetType() == GeomAbs_Plane) {
9073  // Check that the plane is perpendicular to the sketch plane
9074  Geom_Plane plane = surface.Plane();
9075  gp_Dir dnormal = plane.Axis().Direction();
9076  gp_Dir snormal = sketchPlane.Axis().Direction();
9077 
9078  // Extract all edges from the face
9079  TopExp_Explorer edgeExp;
9080  for (edgeExp.Init(face, TopAbs_EDGE); edgeExp.More(); edgeExp.Next()) {
9081  TopoDS_Edge edge = TopoDS::Edge(edgeExp.Current());
9082  // Process each edge
9083  processEdge(edge, geos, gPlane, invPlm, mov, sketchPlane, invRot, sketchAx3, aProjFace);
9084  }
9085 
9086  if (fabs(dnormal.Angle(snormal) - M_PI_2) < Precision::Confusion()) {
9087  // The face is normal to the sketch plane
9088  // We don't want to keep the projection of all the edges of the face.
9089  // We need a single line that goes from min to max of all the projections.
9090  bool initialized = false;
9091  Base::Vector3d start, end;
9092  // Lambda to determine if a point should replace start or end
9093  auto updateExtremes = [&](const Base::Vector3d& point) {
9094  if ((point - start).Length() < (point - end).Length()) {
9095  // `point` is closer to `start` than `end`, check if it's further out than `start`
9096  if ((point - end).Length() > (end - start).Length()) {
9097  start = point;
9098  }
9099  }
9100  else {
9101  // `point` is closer to `end`, check if it's further out than `end`
9102  if ((point - start).Length() > (end - start).Length()) {
9103  end = point;
9104  }
9105  }
9106  };
9107  for (auto& geo : geos) {
9108  auto* line = dynamic_cast<Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo.get());
9109  if (!line) {
9110  // The face being normal to the sketch, we should have
9111  // only lines. This is just a fail-safe in case there's a
9112  // straight bspline or something like this.
9113  continue;
9114  }
9115  if (!initialized) {
9116  start = line->getStartPoint();
9117  end = line->getEndPoint();
9118  initialized = true;
9119  continue;
9120  }
9121 
9122  updateExtremes(line->getStartPoint());
9123  updateExtremes(line->getEndPoint());
9124  }
9125  if (initialized) {
9126  auto* unifiedLine = new Part::GeomLineSegment();
9127  unifiedLine->setPoints(start, end);
9128  geos.clear(); // Clear other segments
9129  geos.emplace_back(unifiedLine);
9130  }
9131  else {
9132  // In case we have not initialized, perhaps the projections were
9133  // only straight bsplines.
9134  // Then we use the old method that will give a line with 20000 length:
9135  // Get vector that is normal to both sketch plane normal and plane normal.
9136  // This is the line's direction
9137  gp_Dir lnormal = dnormal.Crossed(snormal);
9138  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeEdge builder(gp_Lin(plane.Location(), lnormal));
9139  builder.Build();
9140  if (builder.IsDone()) {
9141  const TopoDS_Edge& edge = TopoDS::Edge(builder.Shape());
9142  BRepAdaptor_Curve curve(edge);
9143  if (curve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Line) {
9144  geos.emplace_back(projectLine(curve, gPlane, invPlm));
9145  }
9146  }
9147  }
9148  }
9149  }
9150  else {
9151  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> res = projectShape(face, sketchAx3);
9152  for (auto& resShape : res) {
9153  TopExp_Explorer explorer(resShape, TopAbs_EDGE);
9154  while (explorer.More()) {
9155  TopoDS_Edge projEdge = TopoDS::Edge(explorer.Current());
9156  processEdge2(projEdge, geos);
9157  explorer.Next();
9158  }
9159  }
9160  }
9161  } break;
9162  case TopAbs_EDGE: {
9163  const TopoDS_Edge& edge = TopoDS::Edge(refSubShape);
9164  processEdge(edge, geos, gPlane, invPlm, mov, sketchPlane, invRot, sketchAx3, aProjFace);
9165  } break;
9166  case TopAbs_VERTEX: {
9167  importVertex(refSubShape);
9168  } break;
9169  default:
9170  throw Base::TypeError("Unknown type of geometry");
9171  break;
9172  }
9173  if (beingCreated && !extToAdd->intersection) {
9174  // We are adding the projections, so we need to initialize those
9175  for (auto& geo : geos) {
9176  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo.get());
9177  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining, extToAdd->defining);
9178  }
9179  }
9180  }
9181  int projSize = geos.size();
9182 
9183  if (intersection) {
9184  FCBRepAlgoAPI_Section maker(refSubShape, sketchPlane);
9185  maker.Approximation(Standard_True);
9186  if (!maker.IsDone())
9187  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Failed to get intersection");
9188  Part::TopoShape intersectionShape(maker.Shape());
9189  auto edges = intersectionShape.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE);
9190  for (const auto& s : edges) {
9191  TopoDS_Edge edge = TopoDS::Edge(s.getShape());
9192  processEdge(edge, geos, gPlane, invPlm, mov, sketchPlane, invRot, sketchAx3, aProjFace);
9193  }
9194  // Section of some face (e.g. sphere) produce more than one arcs
9195  // from the same circle. So we try to fit the arcs with a single
9196  // circle/arc.
9197  if (refSubShape.ShapeType() == TopAbs_FACE && geos.size() > 1) {
9198  auto wires = Part::TopoShape().makeElementWires(edges);
9199  if (wires.countSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE) == 1) {
9200  TopoDS_Vertex firstVertex, lastVertex;
9201  BRepTools_WireExplorer exp(TopoDS::Wire(wires.getSubShape(TopAbs_WIRE, 1)));
9202  firstVertex = exp.CurrentVertex();
9203  while (!exp.More())
9204  exp.Next();
9205  lastVertex = exp.CurrentVertex();
9206  gp_Pnt P1 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(firstVertex);
9207  gp_Pnt P2 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(lastVertex);
9208  if (auto geo = fitArcs(geos, P1, P2, ArcFitTolerance.getValue())) {
9209  geos.clear();
9210  geos.emplace_back(geo);
9211  }
9212  }
9213  }
9214  for (const auto& s : intersectionShape.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE)) {
9215  importVertex(s);
9216  }
9217 
9218  if (beingCreated && extToAdd->intersection) {
9219  // We are adding the projections, so we need to initialize those
9220  for (size_t i = projSize; i < geos.size(); ++i) {
9221  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geos[i].get());
9222  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Defining, extToAdd->defining);
9223  }
9224  }
9225  }
9226 
9227  } catch (Base::Exception &e) {
9228  FC_ERR("Failed to project external geometry in "
9229  << getFullName() << ": " << key << std::endl << e.what());
9230  continue;
9231  } catch (Standard_Failure &e) {
9232  FC_ERR("Failed to project external geometry in "
9233  << getFullName() << ": " << key << std::endl << e.GetMessageString());
9234  continue;
9235  } catch (std::exception &e) {
9236  FC_ERR("Failed to project external geometry in "
9237  << getFullName() << ": " << key << std::endl << e.what());
9238  continue;
9239  } catch (...) {
9240  FC_ERR("Failed to project external geometry in "
9241  << getFullName() << ": " << key << std::endl << "Unknown exception");
9242  continue;
9243  }
9244  if (geos.empty()) {
9245  continue;
9246  }
9247 
9248  if(!refSet.emplace(key).second) {
9249  FC_WARN("Duplicated external reference in " << getFullName() << ": " << key);
9250  continue;
9251  }
9252 
9253  for (auto& geo : geos) {
9254  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo.get())->setRef(key);
9255  }
9256  newGeos.push_back(std::move(geos));
9257  }
9258 
9259  // allocate unique geometry id
9260  for(auto &geos : newGeos) {
9261  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geos.front().get());
9262  auto &refs = externalGeoRefMap[egf->getRef()];
9263  while(refs.size() < geos.size())
9264  refs.push_back(++geoLastId);
9265 
9266  // In case a projection reduces output geometries, delete them
9267  std::set<long> geoIds;
9268  geoIds.insert(refs.begin()+geos.size(),refs.end());
9269 
9270  // Sync id and ref of the new geometries
9271  int i = 0;
9272  for(auto &geo : geos)
9273  GeometryFacade::setId(geo.get(), refs[i++]);
9274 
9275  delExternalPrivate(geoIds,false);
9276  }
9277 
9278  auto geoms = ExternalGeo.getValues();
9279 
9280  // now update the geometries
9281  for(auto &geos : newGeos) {
9282  for(auto &geo : geos) {
9283  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(GeometryFacade::getId(geo.get()));
9284  if(it == externalGeoMap.end()) {
9285  // This is a new geometries.
9286  geoms.push_back(geo.release());
9287  continue;
9288  }
9289  // This is an existing geometry. Update it while keeping the old flags
9290  ExternalGeometryFacade::copyFlags(geoms[it->second], geo.get());
9291  geoms[it->second] = geo.release();
9292  }
9293  }
9294 
9295  // Check for any missing references
9296  bool hasError = false;
9297  for(auto geo : geoms) {
9298  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
9299  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Sync,false);
9300  if(egf->getRef().empty())
9301  continue;
9302  if(!refSet.count(egf->getRef())) {
9303  FC_ERR( "External geometry " << getFullName() << ".e" << egf->getId()
9304  << " missing reference: " << egf->getRef());
9305  hasError = true;
9306  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing,true);
9307  } else {
9308  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing,false);
9309  }
9310  }
9311 
9312  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geoms));
9313  rebuildVertexIndex();
9314 
9315  // clean up geometry reference
9316  if(refSet.size() != (size_t)ExternalGeometry.getSize()) {
9317  if(refSet.size() < keys.size()) {
9318  auto itObj = Objects.begin();
9319  auto itSub = SubElements.begin();
9320  for(auto &ref : keys) {
9321  if(!refSet.count(ref)) {
9322  itObj = Objects.erase(itObj);
9323  itSub = SubElements.erase(itSub);
9324  }else {
9325  ++itObj;
9326  ++itSub;
9327  }
9328  }
9329  }
9330  ExternalGeometry.setValues(Objects,SubElements);
9331  }
9332 
9333  solverNeedsUpdate=true;
9334  Constraints.acceptGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
9335 
9336  if (hasError && this->isRecomputing()) {
9337  throw Base::RuntimeError("Missing external geometry reference");
9338  }
9339 }
9340 
9341 void SketchObject::fixExternalGeometry(const std::vector<int> &geoIds) {
9342  std::set<int> idSet(geoIds.begin(),geoIds.end());
9343  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
9344  auto objs = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
9345  auto subs = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
9346  bool touched = false;
9347  for(int i=2;i<(int)geos.size();++i) {
9348  auto &geo = geos[i];
9349  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
9350  int GeoId = -i-1;
9351  if(egf->getRef().empty()
9352  || !egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing)
9353  || (idSet.size() && !idSet.count(GeoId)))
9354  continue;
9355  std::string ref = egf->getRef();
9356  auto pos = ref.find('.');
9357  if(pos == std::string::npos) {
9358  FC_ERR("Invalid geometry reference " << ref);
9359  continue;
9360  }
9361  std::string objName = ref.substr(0,pos);
9362  auto obj = getDocument()->getObject(objName.c_str());
9363  if(!obj) {
9364  FC_ERR("Cannot find object in reference " << ref);
9365  continue;
9366  }
9367 
9368  auto elements = Part::Feature::getRelatedElements(obj,ref.c_str()+pos+1);
9369  if(!elements.size()) {
9370  FC_ERR("No related reference found for " << ref);
9371  continue;
9372  }
9373 
9374  geo = geo->clone();
9375  egf->setGeometry(geo);
9376  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing,false);
9377  ref = objName + "." + Data::ComplexGeoData::elementMapPrefix();
9378  elements.front().name.appendToBuffer(ref);
9379  egf->setRef(ref);
9380  objs.push_back(obj);
9381  subs.emplace_back();
9382  elements.front().index.appendToStringBuffer(subs.back());
9383  touched = true;
9384  }
9385 
9386  if(touched) {
9387  ExternalGeo.setValues(geos);
9388  ExternalGeometry.setValues(objs,subs);
9389  rebuildExternalGeometry();
9390  }
9391 }
9392 
9393 std::vector<Part::Geometry*> SketchObject::getCompleteGeometry() const
9394 {
9395  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> vals = getInternalGeometry();
9396  const auto &geos = getExternalGeometry();
9397  vals.insert(vals.end(), geos.rbegin(), geos.rend()); // in reverse order
9398  return vals;
9399 }
9400 
9401 GeoListFacade SketchObject::getGeoListFacade() const
9402 {
9403  std::vector<GeometryFacadeUniquePtr> facade;
9404  facade.reserve(Geometry.getSize() + ExternalGeo.getSize());
9405 
9406  for (auto geo : Geometry.getValues())
9407  facade.push_back(GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo));
9408 
9409  const auto &externalGeos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
9410  for(auto rit = externalGeos.rbegin(); rit != externalGeos.rend(); rit++)
9411  facade.push_back(GeometryFacade::getFacade(*rit));
9412 
9413  return GeoListFacade::getGeoListModel(std::move(facade), Geometry.getSize());
9414 }
9415 
9416 void SketchObject::rebuildVertexIndex()
9417 {
9418  VertexId2GeoId.resize(0);
9419  VertexId2PosId.resize(0);
9420  int imax = getHighestCurveIndex();
9421  int i = 0;
9422  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geometry = getCompleteGeometry();
9423  if (geometry.size() <= 2)
9424  return;
9425  for (std::vector<Part::Geometry*>::const_iterator it = geometry.begin();
9426  it != geometry.end() - 2;
9427  ++it, i++) {
9428  if (i > imax)
9429  i = -getExternalGeometryCount();
9430  if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomPoint>()) {
9431  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9432  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9433  }
9434  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomLineSegment>()) {
9435  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9436  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9437  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9438  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9439  }
9440  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomCircle>()) {
9441  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9442  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9443  }
9444  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomEllipse>()) {
9445  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9446  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9447  }
9448  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
9449  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9450  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9451  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9452  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9453  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9454  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9455  }
9456  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomArcOfEllipse>()) {
9457  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9458  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9459  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9460  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9461  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9462  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9463  }
9464  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola>()) {
9465  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9466  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9467  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9468  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9469  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9470  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9471  }
9472  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>()) {
9473  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9474  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9475  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9476  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9477  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9478  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::mid);
9479  }
9480  else if ((*it)->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
9481  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9482  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::start);
9483  VertexId2GeoId.push_back(i);
9484  VertexId2PosId.push_back(PointPos::end);
9485  }
9486  }
9487 }
9488 
9489 const std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>> SketchObject::getCoincidenceGroups()
9490 {
9491  // this function is different from that in getCoincidentPoints in that:
9492  // - getCoincidentPoints only considers direct coincidence (the points that are linked via a
9493  // single coincidence)
9494  // - this function provides an array of maps of points, each map containing the points that are
9495  // coincident by virtue
9496  // of any number of interrelated coincidence constraints (if coincidence 1-2 and coincidence
9497  // 2-3, {1,2,3} are in that set)
9498 
9499  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Constraints.getValues();
9500 
9501  std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>> coincidenttree;
9502  // push the constraints
9503  for (std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it = vals.begin(); it != vals.end();
9504  ++it) {
9505  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Coincident) {
9506  int firstpresentin = -1;
9507  int secondpresentin = -1;
9508 
9509  int i = 0;
9510 
9511  for (std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>>::const_iterator iti =
9512  coincidenttree.begin();
9513  iti != coincidenttree.end();
9514  ++iti, i++) {
9515  // First
9516  std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>::const_iterator filiterator;
9517  filiterator = (*iti).find((*it)->First);
9518  if (filiterator != (*iti).end()) {
9519  if ((*it)->FirstPos == (*filiterator).second)
9520  firstpresentin = i;
9521  }
9522  // Second
9523  filiterator = (*iti).find((*it)->Second);
9524  if (filiterator != (*iti).end()) {
9525  if ((*it)->SecondPos == (*filiterator).second)
9526  secondpresentin = i;
9527  }
9528  }
9529 
9530  if (firstpresentin != -1 && secondpresentin != -1) {
9531  // we have to merge those sets into one
9532  coincidenttree[firstpresentin].insert(coincidenttree[secondpresentin].begin(),
9533  coincidenttree[secondpresentin].end());
9534  coincidenttree.erase(coincidenttree.begin() + secondpresentin);
9535  }
9536  else if (firstpresentin == -1 && secondpresentin == -1) {
9537  // we do not have any of the values, so create a setCursor
9538  std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos> tmp;
9539  tmp.insert(std::pair<int, Sketcher::PointPos>((*it)->First, (*it)->FirstPos));
9540  tmp.insert(std::pair<int, Sketcher::PointPos>((*it)->Second, (*it)->SecondPos));
9541  coincidenttree.push_back(tmp);
9542  }
9543  else if (firstpresentin != -1) {
9544  // add to existing group
9545  coincidenttree[firstpresentin].insert(
9546  std::pair<int, Sketcher::PointPos>((*it)->Second, (*it)->SecondPos));
9547  }
9548  else {// secondpresentin != -1
9549  // add to existing group
9550  coincidenttree[secondpresentin].insert(
9551  std::pair<int, Sketcher::PointPos>((*it)->First, (*it)->FirstPos));
9552  }
9553  }
9554  }
9555 
9556  return coincidenttree;
9557 }
9558 
9559 void SketchObject::isCoincidentWithExternalGeometry(int GeoId, bool& start_external,
9560  bool& mid_external, bool& end_external)
9561 {
9562 
9563  start_external = false;
9564  mid_external = false;
9565  end_external = false;
9566 
9567  const std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>> coincidenttree = getCoincidenceGroups();
9568 
9569  for (const auto& cGroup : coincidenttree) {
9570  const auto& geoId1iterator = cGroup.find(GeoId);
9571  if (geoId1iterator == cGroup.end()) {
9572  continue;
9573  }
9574 
9575  if (cGroup.begin()->first >= 0) {
9576  continue;
9577  }
9578 
9579  // `GeoId` is in this set and the first key in this ordered element key is external
9580  if (geoId1iterator->second == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
9581  start_external = true;
9582  else if (geoId1iterator->second == Sketcher::PointPos::mid)
9583  mid_external = true;
9584  else if (geoId1iterator->second == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
9585  end_external = true;
9586  }
9587 }

9589 const std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos> SketchObject::getAllCoincidentPoints(int GeoId,
9590  PointPos PosId)
9591 {
9592  const std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>> coincidenttree = getCoincidenceGroups();
9593 
9594  for (const auto& cGroup : coincidenttree) {
9595  std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>::const_iterator geoId1iterator;
9596 
9597  geoId1iterator = cGroup.find(GeoId);
9598 
9599  if (geoId1iterator != cGroup.end()) {
9600  // If GeoId is in this set
9601 
9602  if (geoId1iterator->second == PosId)// and posId matches
9603  return cGroup;
9604  }
9605  }
9606 
9607  std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos> empty;
9608 
9609  return empty;
9610 }

9613 void SketchObject::getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(int GeoId, PointPos PosId,
9614  std::vector<int>& GeoIdList,
9615  std::vector<PointPos>& PosIdList)
9616 {
9617  const std::vector<Constraint*>& constraints = this->Constraints.getValues();
9618 
9619  GeoIdList.clear();
9620  PosIdList.clear();
9621  GeoIdList.push_back(GeoId);
9622  PosIdList.push_back(PosId);
9623  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = constraints.begin(); it != constraints.end();
9624  ++it) {
9625  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Coincident) {
9626  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId) {
9627  GeoIdList.push_back((*it)->Second);
9628  PosIdList.push_back((*it)->SecondPos);
9629  }
9630  else if ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId) {
9631  GeoIdList.push_back((*it)->First);
9632  PosIdList.push_back((*it)->FirstPos);
9633  }
9634  }
9635  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Tangent) {
9636  if ((*it)->First == GeoId && (*it)->FirstPos == PosId &&
9637  ((*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start ||
9638  (*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
9639  GeoIdList.push_back((*it)->Second);
9640  PosIdList.push_back((*it)->SecondPos);
9641  }
9642  if ((*it)->Second == GeoId && (*it)->SecondPos == PosId &&
9643  ((*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start ||
9644  (*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
9645  GeoIdList.push_back((*it)->First);
9646  PosIdList.push_back((*it)->FirstPos);
9647  }
9648  }
9649  }
9650  if (GeoIdList.size() == 1) {
9651  GeoIdList.clear();
9652  PosIdList.clear();
9653  }
9654 }
9655 
9656 void SketchObject::getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(int VertexId, std::vector<int>& GeoIdList,
9657  std::vector<PointPos>& PosIdList)
9658 {
9659  int GeoId;
9660  PointPos PosId;
9661  getGeoVertexIndex(VertexId, GeoId, PosId);
9662  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(GeoId, PosId, GeoIdList, PosIdList);
9663 }

9665 bool SketchObject::arePointsCoincident(int GeoId1, PointPos PosId1, int GeoId2, PointPos PosId2)
9666 {
9667  if (GeoId1 == GeoId2 && PosId1 == PosId2)
9668  return true;
9669 
9670  const std::vector<std::map<int, Sketcher::PointPos>> coincidenttree = getCoincidenceGroups();
9671 
9672  for (const auto& cGroup : coincidenttree) {
9673  const auto& geoId1iterator = cGroup.find(GeoId1);
9674 
9675  if (geoId1iterator != cGroup.end()) {
9676  // If First is in this set
9677  const auto& geoId2iterator = cGroup.find(GeoId2);
9678 
9679  if (geoId2iterator != cGroup.end()) {
9680  // If Second is in this set
9681  if (geoId1iterator->second == PosId1 && geoId2iterator->second == PosId2)
9682  return true;
9683  }
9684  }
9685  }
9686 
9687  return false;
9688 }

9697  constraintList.push_back(i);
9698  }
9699  ++i;
9700  }
9701 }

9748 
9749 void SketchObject::getGeometryWithDependentParameters(
9750  std::vector<std::pair<int, PointPos>>& geometrymap)
9751 {
9752  auto geos = getInternalGeometry();
9753 
9754  int geoid = 0;
9755 
9756  for (auto geo : geos) {
9757  if (geo) {
9758  if (geo->hasExtension(Sketcher::SolverGeometryExtension::getClassTypeId())) {
9759 
9760  auto solvext = std::static_pointer_cast<const Sketcher::SolverGeometryExtension>(
9761  geo->getExtension(Sketcher::SolverGeometryExtension::getClassTypeId()).lock());
9762 
9763  if (solvext->getGeometry()
9764  == Sketcher::SolverGeometryExtension::NotFullyConstraint) {
9765  // The solver differentiates whether the parameters that are dependent are not
9766  // those of start, end, mid, and assigns them to the edge (edge params = curve
9767  // params - parms of start, end, mid). The user looking at the UI expects that
9768  // the edge of a NotFullyConstraint geometry will always move, even if the edge
9769  // parameters are independent, for example if mid is the only dependent
9770  // parameter. In other words, the user could reasonably restrict the edge to
9771  // reach a fully constrained element. Under this understanding, the edge
9772  // parameter would always be dependent, unless the element is fully constrained.
9773  //
9774  // While this is ok from a user visual expectation point of view, it leads to a
9775  // loss of information of whether restricting the point start, end, mid that is
9776  // dependent may suffice, or even if such points are restricted, the edge would
9777  // still need to be restricted.
9778  //
9779  // Because Python gets the information in this function, it would lead to Python
9780  // users having access to a lower amount of detail.
9781  //
9782  // For this reason, this function returns edge as dependent parameter if and
9783  // only if constraining the parameters of the points would not suffice to
9784  // constraint the element.
9785  if (solvext->getEdge() == SolverGeometryExtension::Dependent)
9786  geometrymap.emplace_back(geoid, Sketcher::PointPos::none);
9787  if (solvext->getStart() == SolverGeometryExtension::Dependent)
9788  geometrymap.emplace_back(geoid, Sketcher::PointPos::start);
9789  if (solvext->getEnd() == SolverGeometryExtension::Dependent)
9790  geometrymap.emplace_back(geoid, Sketcher::PointPos::start);
9791  if (solvext->getMid() == SolverGeometryExtension::Dependent)
9792  geometrymap.emplace_back(geoid, Sketcher::PointPos::start);
9793  }
9794  }
9795  }
9796 
9797  geoid++;
9798  }
9799 }
9800 
9801 bool SketchObject::evaluateConstraint(const Constraint* constraint) const
9802 {
9803  // if requireXXX, GeoUndef is treated as an error. If not requireXXX,
9804  // GeoUndef is accepted. Index range checking is done on everything regardless.
9805 
9806  // constraints always require a First!!
9807  bool requireSecond = false;
9808  bool requireThird = false;
9809 
9810  switch (constraint->Type) {
9811  case Radius:
9812  case Diameter:
9813  case Weight:
9814  case Horizontal:
9815  case Vertical:
9816  case Distance:
9817  case DistanceX:
9818  case DistanceY:
9819  case Coincident:
9820  case Perpendicular:
9821  case Parallel:
9822  case Equal:
9823  case PointOnObject:
9824  case Angle:
9825  break;
9826  case Tangent:
9827  requireSecond = true;
9828  break;
9829  case Symmetric:
9830  case SnellsLaw:
9831  requireSecond = true;
9832  requireThird = true;
9833  break;
9834  default:
9835  break;
9836  }
9837 
9838  int intGeoCount = getHighestCurveIndex() + 1;
9839  int extGeoCount = getExternalGeometryCount();
9840 
9841  // the actual checks
9842  bool ret = true;
9843  int geoId;
9844 
9845  // First is always required and GeoId must be within range
9846  geoId = constraint->First;
9847  ret = ret && (geoId >= -extGeoCount && geoId < intGeoCount);
9848 
9849  geoId = constraint->Second;
9850  ret = ret
9851  && ((geoId == GeoEnum::GeoUndef && !requireSecond)
9852  || (geoId >= -extGeoCount && geoId < intGeoCount));
9853 
9854  geoId = constraint->Third;
9855  ret = ret
9856  && ((geoId == GeoEnum::GeoUndef && !requireThird)
9857  || (geoId >= -extGeoCount && geoId < intGeoCount));
9858 
9859  return ret;
9860 }
9861 
9862 bool SketchObject::evaluateConstraints() const
9863 {
9864  int intGeoCount = getHighestCurveIndex() + 1;
9865  int extGeoCount = getExternalGeometryCount();
9866 
9867  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geometry = getCompleteGeometry();
9868  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& constraints = Constraints.getValuesForce();
9869  if (static_cast<int>(geometry.size()) != extGeoCount + intGeoCount) {
9870  return false;
9871  }
9872  if (geometry.size() < 2) {
9873  return false;
9874  }
9875 
9876  for (auto it : constraints) {
9877  if (!evaluateConstraint(it)) {
9878  return false;
9879  }
9880  }
9881 
9882  if (!constraints.empty()) {
9883  if (!Constraints.scanGeometry(geometry)) {
9884  return false;
9885  }
9886  }
9887 
9888  return true;
9889 }
9890 
9891 void SketchObject::validateConstraints()
9892 {
9893  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
9894  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
9895 
9896  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> geometry = getCompleteGeometry();
9897  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& constraints = Constraints.getValuesForce();
9898 
9899  std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*> newConstraints;
9900  newConstraints.reserve(constraints.size());
9901  std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>::const_iterator it;
9902  for (it = constraints.begin(); it != constraints.end(); ++it) {
9903  bool valid = evaluateConstraint(*it);
9904  if (valid) {
9905  newConstraints.push_back(*it);
9906  }
9907  }
9908 
9909  if (newConstraints.size() != constraints.size()) {
9910  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newConstraints));
9911  acceptGeometry();
9912  }
9913  else if (!Constraints.scanGeometry(geometry)) {
9914  Constraints.acceptGeometry(geometry);
9915  }
9916 }
9917 
9918 std::string SketchObject::validateExpression(const App::ObjectIdentifier& path,
9919  std::shared_ptr<const App::Expression> expr)
9920 {
9921  const App::Property* prop = path.getProperty();
9922 
9923  assert(expr);
9924 
9925  if (!prop)
9926  return "Property not found";
9927 
9928  if (prop == &Constraints) {
9929  const Constraint* constraint = Constraints.getConstraint(path);
9930 
9931  if (!constraint->isDriving)
9932  return "Reference constraints cannot be set!";
9933  }
9934 
9935  auto deps = expr->getDeps();
9936  auto it = deps.find(this);
9937  if (it != deps.end()) {
9938  auto it2 = it->second.find("Constraints");
9939  if (it2 != it->second.end()) {
9940  for (auto& oid : it2->second) {
9941  const Constraint* constraint = Constraints.getConstraint(oid);
9942 
9943  if (!constraint->isDriving)
9944  return "Reference constraint from this sketch cannot be used in this "
9945  "expression.";
9946  }
9947  }
9948  geoMap.clear();
9949  const auto &vals = getInternalGeometry();
9950  for(long i=0;i<(long)vals.size();++i) {
9951  auto geo = vals[i];
9952  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
9953  if(!gf->getId())
9954  gf->setId(++geoLastId);
9955  else if(gf->getId() > geoLastId)
9956  geoLastId = gf->getId();
9957  while(!geoMap.insert(std::make_pair(gf->getId(),i)).second) {
9958  FC_WARN("duplicate geometry id " << gf->getId() << " -> " << geoLastId+1);
9959  gf->setId(++geoLastId);
9960  }
9961  }
9962  updateGeoHistory();
9963  }
9964  return "";
9965 }
9966 
9967 // This function is necessary for precalculation of an angle when adding
9968 // an angle constraint. It is also used here, in SketchObject, to
9969 // lock down the type of tangency/perpendicularity.
9970 double SketchObject::calculateAngleViaPoint(int GeoId1, int GeoId2, double px, double py)
9971 {
9972  // Temporary sketch based calculation. Slow, but guaranteed consistency with constraints.
9973  Sketcher::Sketch sk;
9974 
9975  const Part::GeomCurve* p1 = dynamic_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(this->getGeometry(GeoId1));
9976  const Part::GeomCurve* p2 = dynamic_cast<const Part::GeomCurve*>(this->getGeometry(GeoId2));
9977 
9978  if (p1 && p2) {
9979  // TODO: Check if any of these are B-splines
9980  int i1 = sk.addGeometry(this->getGeometry(GeoId1));
9981  int i2 = sk.addGeometry(this->getGeometry(GeoId2));
9982 
9983  if (p1->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>() ||
9984  p2->is<Part::GeomBSplineCurve>()) {
9985  double p1ClosestParam, p2ClosestParam;
9986  Base::Vector3d pt(px, py, 0);
9987  p1->closestParameter(pt, p1ClosestParam);
9988  p2->closestParameter(pt, p2ClosestParam);
9989 
9990  return sk.calculateAngleViaParams(i1, i2, p1ClosestParam, p2ClosestParam);
9991  }
9992 
9993  return sk.calculateAngleViaPoint(i1, i2, px, py);
9994  }
9995  else
9996  throw Base::ValueError("Null geometry in calculateAngleViaPoint");
9997 }

10006 }

10008 void SketchObject::constraintsRemoved(const std::set<App::ObjectIdentifier>& removed)
10009 {
10010  std::set<App::ObjectIdentifier>::const_iterator i = removed.begin();
10011 
10012  while (i != removed.end()) {
10013  ExpressionEngine.setValue(*i, std::shared_ptr<App::Expression>());
10014  ++i;
10015  }
10016 }
10017 
10018 // Tests if the provided point lies exactly in a curve (satisfies
10019 // point-on-object constraint). It is used to decide whether it is nesessary to
10020 // constrain a point onto curves when 3-element selection tangent-via-point-like
10021 // constraints are applied.
10022 bool SketchObject::isPointOnCurve(int geoIdCurve, double px, double py)
10023 {
10024  // DeepSOIC: this may be slow, but I wanted to reuse the existing code
10025  Sketcher::Sketch sk;
10026  int icrv = sk.addGeometry(this->getGeometry(geoIdCurve));
10027  Base::Vector3d pp;
10028  pp.x = px;
10029  pp.y = py;
10030  Part::GeomPoint p(pp);
10031  int ipnt = sk.addPoint(p);
10032  int icstr = sk.addPointOnObjectConstraint(ipnt, Sketcher::PointPos::start, icrv);
10033  double err = sk.calculateConstraintError(icstr);
10034  return err * err < 10.0 * sk.getSolverPrecision();
10035 }
10036 
10037 // This one was done just for fun to see to what precision the constraints are solved.
10038 double SketchObject::calculateConstraintError(int ConstrId)
10039 {
10040  Sketcher::Sketch sk;
10041  const std::vector<Constraint*>& clist = this->Constraints.getValues();
10042  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(clist.size()))
10043  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
10044 
10045  Constraint* cstr = clist[ConstrId]->clone();
10046  double result = 0.0;
10047  try {
10048  std::vector<int> GeoIdList;
10049  int g;
10050  GeoIdList.push_back(cstr->First);
10051  GeoIdList.push_back(cstr->Second);
10052  GeoIdList.push_back(cstr->Third);
10053 
10054  // add only necessary geometry to the sketch
10055  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < GeoIdList.size(); i++) {
10056  g = GeoIdList[i];
10057  if (g != GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
10058  GeoIdList[i] = sk.addGeometry(this->getGeometry(g));
10059  }
10060  }
10061 
10062  cstr->First = GeoIdList[0];
10063  cstr->Second = GeoIdList[1];
10064  cstr->Third = GeoIdList[2];
10065  int icstr = sk.addConstraint(cstr);
10066  result = sk.calculateConstraintError(icstr);
10067  }
10068  catch (...) {// cleanup
10069  delete cstr;
10070  throw;
10071  }
10072  delete cstr;
10073  return result;
10074 }
