10089 
10090 void SketchObject::Save(Writer& writer) const
10091 {
10092  int index = -1;
10093  auto &geos = const_cast<Part::PropertyGeometryList&>(ExternalGeo).getValues();
10094  for(auto geo : geos)
10095  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->setRefIndex(-1);
10096 
10097  if(isExporting()) {
10098  // We cannot export shape with the new topological naming, because it
10099  // uses hasher indices that are unique only within its owner document.
10100  // Therefore, we cannot rely on Geometry::Ref as key to map geometry to
10101  // external object reference. So, before exporting, we pre-calculate
10102  // the mapping and store them in Geometry::RefIndex. When importing,
10103  // inside updateGeometryRefs() (called by onDocumentRestore()), we shall
10104  // regenerate Geometry::Ref based on RefIndex.
10105  //
10106  // Note that the regenerated Ref will not be using the new topological
10107  // naming either, because we didn't export them. This is exactly the
10108  // same as if we are opening a legacy file without new names.
10109  // updateGeometryRefs() will know how to handle the name change thanks
10110  // to a flag setup in onUpdateElementReference().
10111  for(auto &key : externalGeoRef) {
10112  ++index;
10113  auto iter = externalGeoRefMap.find(key);
10114  if(iter == externalGeoRefMap.end())
10115  continue;
10116  for(auto id : iter->second) {
10117  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
10118  if(it != externalGeoMap.end())
10119  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geos[it->second])->setRefIndex(index);
10120  }
10121  }
10122  }
10123 
10124  // save the father classes
10125  Part::Part2DObject::Save(writer);
10126 }
10127 
10128 void SketchObject::Restore(XMLReader& reader)
10129 {
10130  // read the father classes
10131  Part::Part2DObject::Restore(reader);
10132 }
10133 
10134 void SketchObject::handleChangedPropertyType(Base::XMLReader &reader,
10135  const char *TypeName, App::Property *prop)
10136 {
10137  if (prop == &Exports) {
10138  if(strcmp(TypeName, "App::PropertyLinkList") == 0)
10139  Exports.Restore(reader);
10140  }
10141 }
10142 
10143 static inline bool checkMigration(Part::PropertyGeometryList &prop)
10144 {
10145  for (auto g : prop.getValues()) {
10146  if(g->hasExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())
10147  || !g->hasExtension(SketchGeometryExtension::getClassTypeId()))
10148  return true;
10149  }
10150  return false;
10151 }
10152 
10153 void SketchObject::onChanged(const App::Property* prop)
10154 {
10155  if (prop == &Geometry) {
10156  if (isRestoring() && checkMigration(Geometry)) {
10157  // Construction migration to extension
10158  for (auto geometryValue : Geometry.getValues()) {
10159  if (geometryValue->hasExtension(
10160  Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())) {
10161  auto ext = std::static_pointer_cast<Part::GeometryMigrationExtension>(
10162  geometryValue
10163  ->getExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())
10164  .lock());
10165 
10166  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(
10167  geometryValue); // at this point IA geometry is already migrated
10168 
10169  if (ext->testMigrationType(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::Construction)) {
10170  bool oldconstr = ext->getConstruction();
10171  if (geometryValue->getTypeId() == Part::GeomPoint::getClassTypeId()
10172  && !gf->isInternalAligned()) {
10173  oldconstr = true;
10174  }
10175  gf->setConstruction(oldconstr);
10176  }
10177  if (ext->testMigrationType(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::GeometryId)) {
10178  gf->setId(ext->getId());
10179  }
10180  }
10181  }
10182  }
10183  geoMap.clear();
10184  const auto &vals = getInternalGeometry();
10185  for(long i=0;i<(long)vals.size();++i) {
10186  auto geo = vals[i];
10187  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
10188  if (gf->getId() == 0) {
10189  gf->setId(++geoLastId);
10190  }
10191  else if (gf->getId() > geoLastId) {
10192  geoLastId = gf->getId();
10193  }
10194  while (!geoMap.insert(std::make_pair(gf->getId(), i)).second) {
10195  FC_WARN("duplicate geometry id " << gf->getId() << " -> "
10196  << geoLastId + 1); // NOLINT
10197  gf->setId(++geoLastId);
10198  }
10199  }
10200  updateGeoHistory();
10201  }
10202 
10203  auto doc = getDocument();
10204 
10205  if (prop == &Geometry || prop == &Constraints) {
10206  if (doc && doc->isPerformingTransaction()) {// undo/redo
10207  setStatus(App::PendingTransactionUpdate, true);
10208  }
10209  else {
10210  if (!internaltransaction) {
10211  // internal sketchobject operations changing both geometry and constraints will
10212  // explicitly perform an update
10213  if (prop == &Geometry) {
10214  if (managedoperation || isRestoring()) {
10215  // if geometry changed, the constraint geometry indices must be updated
10216  acceptGeometry();
10217  }
10218  else {
10219  // this change was not effect via SketchObject, but using direct access to
10220  // properties, check input data
10221 
10222  // declares constraint invalid if indices go beyond the geometry and any
10223  // call to getValues with return an empty list until this is fixed.
10224  bool invalidinput = Constraints.checkConstraintIndices(
10225  getHighestCurveIndex(), -getExternalGeometryCount());
10226 
10227  if (!invalidinput) {
10228  acceptGeometry();
10229  }
10230  else {
10231  Base::Console().Error(
10232  this->getFullLabel() + " SketchObject::onChanged ",
10233  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications", "Unmanaged change of Geometry Property "
10234  "results in invalid constraint indices") "\n");
10235  }
10236  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
10237  setUpSketch();
10238  }
10239  }
10240  else {// Change is in Constraints
10241 
10242  if (managedoperation || isRestoring()) {
10243  Constraints.checkGeometry(getCompleteGeometry());
10244  }
10245  else {
10246  // this change was not effect via SketchObject, but using direct access to
10247  // properties, check input data
10248 
10249  // declares constraint invalid if indices go beyond the geometry and any
10250  // call to getValues with return an empty list until this is fixed.
10251  bool invalidinput = Constraints.checkConstraintIndices(
10252  getHighestCurveIndex(), -getExternalGeometryCount());
10253 
10254  if (!invalidinput) {
10255  if (Constraints.checkGeometry(getCompleteGeometry())) {
10256  // if there are invalid geometry indices in the constraints, we need
10257  // to update them
10258  acceptGeometry();
10259  }
10260  }
10261  else {
10262  Base::Console().Error(
10263  this->getFullLabel() + " SketchObject::onChanged ",
10264  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications", "Unmanaged change of Constraint "
10265  "Property results in invalid constraint indices") "\n");
10266  }
10267  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
10268  setUpSketch();
10269  }
10270  }
10271  }
10272  }
10273  }
10274  else if (prop == &ExternalGeo && !prop->testStatus(App::Property::User3)) {
10275  if (doc && doc->isPerformingTransaction()) {
10276  setStatus(App::PendingTransactionUpdate, true);
10277  }
10278 
10279  if (isRestoring() && checkMigration(ExternalGeo)) {
10280  for (auto geometryValue : ExternalGeo.getValues()) {
10281  if (geometryValue->hasExtension(
10282  Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())) {
10283  auto ext = std::static_pointer_cast<Part::GeometryMigrationExtension>(
10284  geometryValue
10285  ->getExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())
10286  .lock());
10287  std::unique_ptr<ExternalGeometryFacade> egf;
10288  if (ext->testMigrationType(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::GeometryId)) {
10289  egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geometryValue);
10290  egf->setId(ext->getId());
10291  }
10292 
10293  if (ext->testMigrationType(
10294  Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::ExternalReference)) {
10295  if (!egf) {
10296  egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geometryValue);
10297  }
10298  egf->setRef(ext->getRef());
10299  egf->setRefIndex(ext->getRefIndex());
10300  egf->setFlags(ext->getFlags());
10301  }
10302  }
10303  }
10304  }
10305  externalGeoRefMap.clear();
10306  externalGeoMap.clear();
10307  std::set<std::string> detached;
10308  for(int i=0;i<ExternalGeo.getSize();++i) {
10309  auto geo = ExternalGeo[i];
10310  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
10311  if (egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Detached)) {
10312  if (!egf->getRef().empty()) {
10313  detached.insert(egf->getRef());
10314  egf->setRef(std::string());
10315  }
10316  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Detached,false);
10317  egf->setFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing,false);
10318  }
10319  if (egf->getId() > geoLastId) {
10320  geoLastId = egf->getId();
10321  }
10322  if (!externalGeoMap.emplace(egf->getId(), i).second) {
10323  FC_WARN("duplicate geometry id " << egf->getId() << " -> "
10324  << geoLastId + 1); // NOLINT
10325  egf->setId(++geoLastId);
10326  externalGeoMap[egf->getId()] = i;
10327  }
10328  if (!egf->getRef().empty()) {
10329  externalGeoRefMap[egf->getRef()].push_back(egf->getId());
10330  }
10331  }
10332  if (!detached.empty()) {
10333  auto objs = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
10334  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == objs.size());
10335  auto itObj = objs.begin();
10336  auto subs = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
10337  auto itSub = subs.begin();
10338  for (const auto& i : externalGeoRef) {
10339  if (detached.count(i) != 0U) {
10340  itObj = objs.erase(itObj);
10341  itSub = subs.erase(itSub);
10342  auto& refs = externalGeoRefMap[i];
10343  for (long id : refs) {
10344  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
10345  if(it!=externalGeoMap.end()) {
10346  auto geo = ExternalGeo[it->second];
10347  ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->setRef(std::string());
10348  }
10349  }
10350  refs.clear();
10351  } else {
10352  ++itObj;
10353  ++itSub;
10354  }
10355  }
10356  ExternalGeometry.setValues(objs, subs);
10357  }
10358  else {
10359  signalElementsChanged();
10360  }
10361  }
10362  else if (prop == &ExternalGeometry) {
10363  if (doc && doc->isPerformingTransaction()) {
10364  setStatus(App::PendingTransactionUpdate, true);
10365  }
10366 
10367  if(!isRestoring()) {
10368  // must wait till onDocumentRestored() when shadow references are
10369  // fully restored
10370  updateGeometryRefs();
10371  signalElementsChanged();
10372  }
10373  }
10374  else if (prop == &Placement) {
10375  if (ExternalGeometry.getSize() > 0) {
10376  touch();
10377  }
10378  }
10379  else if (prop == &ExpressionEngine) {
10380  if (!isRestoring() && doc && !doc->isPerformingTransaction() && noRecomputes
10381  && !managedoperation) {
10382  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to
10383  // update the DoF of the solver, constraints and UI
10384  try {
10385  auto res = ExpressionEngine.execute();
10386  if (res) {
10387  FC_ERR("Failed to recompute " << ExpressionEngine.getFullName() << ": "
10388  << res->Why); // NOLINT
10389  delete res;
10390  }
10391  } catch (Base::Exception &e) {
10392  e.ReportException();
10393  FC_ERR("Failed to recompute " << ExpressionEngine.getFullName() << ": "
10394  << e.what()); // NOLINT
10395  }
10396  solve();
10397  }
10398  }
10399 #if 0
10400  // For now do not delete anything (#0001791). When changing the support
10401  // face it might be better to check which external geometries can be kept.
10402  else if (prop == &AttachmentSupport) {
10403  // make sure not to change anything while restoring this object
10404  if (!isRestoring()) {
10405  // if support face has changed then clear the external geometry
10406  delConstraintsToExternal();
10407  for (int i=0; i < getExternalGeometryCount(); i++) {
10408  delExternal(0);
10409  }
10410  rebuildExternalGeometry();
10411  }
10412  }
10413 #endif
10414  Part::Part2DObject::onChanged(prop);
10415 }
10416 
10417 void SketchObject::onUpdateElementReference(const App::Property *prop) {
10418  if(prop == &ExternalGeometry) {
10419  updateGeoRef = true;
10420  // Must call updateGeometryRefs() now to avoid the case of recursive
10421  // property change (e.g. temporary object removal in SubShapeBinder)
10422  // afterwards causing assertion failure, although this may mean extra
10423  // call of updateGeometryRefs() later in onChange().
10424  updateGeometryRefs();
10425  signalElementsChanged();
10426  }
10427 }
10428 
10429 void SketchObject::updateGeometryRefs() {
10430  const auto &objs = ExternalGeometry.getValues();
10431  const auto &subs = ExternalGeometry.getSubValues();
10432  const auto &shadows = ExternalGeometry.getShadowSubs();
10433  assert(subs.size() == shadows.size());
10434  std::vector<std::string> originalRefs;
10435  std::map<std::string,std::string> refMap;
10436  if(updateGeoRef) {
10437  assert(externalGeoRef.size() == objs.size());
10438  updateGeoRef = false;
10439  originalRefs = std::move(externalGeoRef);
10440  }
10441  externalGeoRef.clear();
10442  std::unordered_map<std::string, int> legacyMap;
10443  for(int i=0;i<(int)objs.size();++i) {
10444  auto obj = objs[i];
10445  const std::string& sub = shadows[i].newName.empty() ? subs[i] : shadows[i].newName;
10446  externalGeoRef.emplace_back(obj->getNameInDocument());
10447  auto &key = externalGeoRef.back();
10448  key += '.';
10449 
10450  legacyMap[key + Data::oldElementName(sub.c_str())] = i;
10451 
10452  if (!obj->getTypeId().isDerivedFrom(Part::Datum::getClassTypeId())) {
10453  key += Data::newElementName(sub.c_str());
10454  }
10455  if (!originalRefs.empty() && originalRefs[i] != key) {
10456  refMap[originalRefs[i]] = key;
10457  }
10458  }
10459  bool touched = false;
10460  auto geos = ExternalGeo.getValues();
10461  if(refMap.empty()) {
10462  for(auto geo : geos) {
10463  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
10464  if (egf->getRefIndex() < 0) {
10465  if (egf->getId() < 0 && !egf->getRef().empty()) {
10466  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
10467  FC_ERR("External geometry reference corrupted in " << getFullName()
10468  << " Please check.");
10469  // This could happen if someone saved the sketch containing
10470  // external geometries using some rouge releases during the
10471  // migration period. As a remedy, We re-initiate the
10472  // external geometry here to trigger rebuild later, with
10473  // call to rebuildExternalGeometry()
10474  initExternalGeo();
10475  return;
10476  }
10477  auto it = legacyMap.find(egf->getRef());
10478  if (it != legacyMap.end() && egf->getRef() != externalGeoRef[it->second]) {
10479  if(getDocument() && !getDocument()->isPerformingTransaction()) {
10480  // FIXME: this is a bug. Find out when and why does this happen
10481  //
10482  // Amendment: maybe the original bug is because of not
10483  // handling external geometry changes during undo/redo,
10484  // which should be considered as normal. So warning only
10485  // if not undo/redo.
10486  //
10487  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
10488  FC_WARN("Update legacy external reference "
10489  << egf->getRef() << " -> " << externalGeoRef[it->second] << " in "
10490  << getFullName());
10491  }
10492  else {
10493  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
10494  FC_LOG("Update undo/redo external reference "
10495  << egf->getRef() << " -> " << externalGeoRef[it->second] << " in "
10496  << getFullName());
10497  }
10498  touched = true;
10499  egf->setRef(externalGeoRef[it->second]);
10500  }
10501  continue;
10502  }
10503  if (egf->getRefIndex() < (int)externalGeoRef.size()
10504  && egf->getRef() != externalGeoRef[egf->getRefIndex()]) {
10505  touched = true;
10506  egf->setRef(externalGeoRef[egf->getRefIndex()]);
10507  }
10508  egf->setRefIndex(-1);
10509  }
10510  }else{
10511  for(auto &v : refMap) {
10512  auto it = externalGeoRefMap.find(v.first);
10513  if (it == externalGeoRefMap.end()) {
10514  continue;
10515  }
10516  for (long id : it->second) {
10517  auto iter = externalGeoMap.find(id);
10518  if(iter!=externalGeoMap.end()) {
10519  auto &geo = geos[iter->second];
10520  geo = geo->clone();
10521  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
10522  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
10523  FC_LOG(getFullName() << " ref change on ExternalEdge" << iter->second - 1 << ' '
10524  << egf->getRef() << " -> " << v.second);
10525  egf->setRef(v.second);
10526  touched = true;
10527  }
10528  }
10529  }
10530  }
10531  if (touched) {
10532  ExternalGeo.setValues(std::move(geos));
10533  }
10534 }
10535 
10536 void SketchObject::onUndoRedoFinished()
10537 {
10538  // upon undo/redo, PropertyConstraintList does not have updated valid geometry keys, which
10539  // results in empty constraint lists when using getValues
10540  //
10541  // The sketch will also have invalid vertex indices, requiring a call to rebuildVertexIndex
10542  //
10543  // Historically this was "solved" by issuing a recompute, which is absolutely unnecessary and
10544  // prevents solve() from working before such a recompute in case it is redoing an operation with
10545  // invalid data.
10546  Constraints.checkConstraintIndices(getHighestCurveIndex(), -getExternalGeometryCount());
10547  acceptGeometry();
10548  synchroniseGeometryState();
10549  solve();
10550 }
10551 
10552 void SketchObject::synchroniseGeometryState()
10553 {
10554  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
10555 
10556  for (size_t i = 0; i < vals.size(); i++) {
10557  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[i]);
10558 
10559  auto facadeInternalAlignment = gf->getInternalType();
10560  auto facadeBlockedState = gf->getBlocked();
10561 
10562  Sketcher::InternalType::InternalType constraintInternalAlignment = InternalType::None;
10563  bool constraintBlockedState = false;
10564 
10565  for (auto cstr : Constraints.getValues()) {
10566  if (cstr->First == int(i)) {
10567  getInternalTypeState(cstr, constraintInternalAlignment);
10568  getBlockedState(cstr, constraintBlockedState);
10569  }
10570  }
10571 
10572  if (constraintInternalAlignment != facadeInternalAlignment)
10573  gf->setInternalType(constraintInternalAlignment);
10574 
10575  if (constraintBlockedState != facadeBlockedState)
10576  gf->setBlocked(constraintBlockedState);
10577  }
10578 }
10579 
10580 bool SketchObject::getInternalTypeState(
10581  const Constraint* cstr, Sketcher::InternalType::InternalType& internaltypestate) const
10582 {
10583  if (cstr->Type == InternalAlignment) {
10584 
10585  switch (cstr->AlignmentType) {
10586  case Undef:
10587  case NumInternalAlignmentType:
10588  internaltypestate = InternalType::None;
10589  break;
10590  case EllipseMajorDiameter:
10591  internaltypestate = InternalType::EllipseMajorDiameter;
10592  break;
10593  case EllipseMinorDiameter:
10594  internaltypestate = InternalType::EllipseMinorDiameter;
10595  break;
10596  case EllipseFocus1:
10597  internaltypestate = InternalType::EllipseFocus1;
10598  break;
10599  case EllipseFocus2:
10600  internaltypestate = InternalType::EllipseFocus2;
10601  break;
10602  case HyperbolaMajor:
10603  internaltypestate = InternalType::HyperbolaMajor;
10604  break;
10605  case HyperbolaMinor:
10606  internaltypestate = InternalType::HyperbolaMinor;
10607  break;
10608  case HyperbolaFocus:
10609  internaltypestate = InternalType::HyperbolaFocus;
10610  break;
10611  case ParabolaFocus:
10612  internaltypestate = InternalType::ParabolaFocus;
10613  break;
10614  case BSplineControlPoint:
10615  internaltypestate = InternalType::BSplineControlPoint;
10616  break;
10617  case BSplineKnotPoint:
10618  internaltypestate = InternalType::BSplineKnotPoint;
10619  break;
10620  case ParabolaFocalAxis:
10621  internaltypestate = InternalType::ParabolaFocalAxis;
10622  break;
10623  }
10624 
10625  return true;
10626  }
10627 
10628  return false;
10629 }

10641 void SketchObject::onDocumentRestored()
10642 {
10643  try {
10644  restoreFinished();
10645  Part::Part2DObject::onDocumentRestored();
10646  }
10647  catch (...) {
10648  }
10649 }
10650 
10651 void SketchObject::restoreFinished()
10652 {
10653  try {
10654  migrateSketch();
10655 
10656  updateGeometryRefs();
10657  if(ExternalGeo.getSize()<=2) {
10658  if (ExternalGeo.getSize() < 2)
10659  initExternalGeo();
10660  for(auto &key : externalGeoRef) {
10661  long id = getDocument()->getStringHasher()->getID(key.c_str()).value();
10662  if(geoLastId < id)
10663  geoLastId = id;
10664  externalGeoRefMap[key].push_back(id);
10665  }
10666  rebuildExternalGeometry();
10667  if(ExternalGeometry.getSize()+2!=ExternalGeo.getSize())
10668  FC_WARN("Failed to restore some external geometry in " << getFullName());
10669  }else
10670  acceptGeometry();
10671 
10672  synchroniseGeometryState();
10673  // this may happen when saving a sketch directly in edit mode
10674  // but never performed a recompute before
10675  if (Shape.getValue().IsNull() && hasConflicts() == 0) {
10676  if (this->solve(true) == 0)
10677  Shape.setValue(solvedSketch.toShape());
10678  }
10679 
10680  // Sanity check on constraints with expression. It is added because the
10681  // way SketchObject syncs expression and constraints heavily relies on
10682  // proper setup of undo/redo transactions. The missing transaction in
10683  // EditDatumDialog may cause stray or worse wrongly bound expressions.
10684  for (auto &v : ExpressionEngine.getExpressions()) {
10685  if (v.first.getProperty() != &Constraints)
10686  continue;
10687  const Constraint * cstr = nullptr;
10688  try {
10689  cstr = Constraints.getConstraint(v.first);
10690  } catch (Base::Exception &) {
10691  }
10692  if (!cstr || !cstr->isDimensional()) {
10693  FC_WARN((cstr ? "Invalid" : "Orphan")
10694  << " constraint expression in "
10695  << getFullName() << "."
10696  << v.first.toString()
10697  << ": " << v.second->toString());
10698  ExpressionEngine.setValue(v.first, nullptr);
10699  }
10700  }
10701  } catch (Base::Exception &e) {
10702  e.ReportException();
10703  FC_ERR("Error while restoring " << getFullName());
10704  } catch (...) {
10705  }
10706 }
10707 
10708 void SketchObject::migrateSketch()
10709 {
10710  bool noextensions = false;
10711 
10712  for (const auto& g : getInternalGeometry())
10713  // no extension - legacy file
10714  if (!g->hasExtension(SketchGeometryExtension::getClassTypeId()))
10715  noextensions = true;
10716 
10717  if (noextensions) {
10718  for (auto c : Constraints.getValues()) {
10719 
10720  addGeometryState(c);
10721 
10722  // Convert B-Spline controlpoints radius/diameter constraints to Weight constraints
10723  if (c->Type == InternalAlignment && c->AlignmentType == BSplineControlPoint) {
10724  int circlegeoid = c->First;
10725  int bsplinegeoid = c->Second;
10726 
10727  auto bsp = static_cast<const Part::GeomBSplineCurve*>(getGeometry(bsplinegeoid));
10728 
10729  std::vector<double> weights = bsp->getWeights();
10730 
10731  for (auto ccp : Constraints.getValues()) {
10732 
10733  if ((ccp->Type == Radius || ccp->Type == Diameter)
10734  && ccp->First == circlegeoid) {
10735 
10736  if (c->InternalAlignmentIndex < int(weights.size())) {
10737  ccp->Type = Weight;
10738  ccp->setValue(weights[c->InternalAlignmentIndex]);
10739  }
10740  }
10741  }
10742  }
10743  }
10744 
10745  // Construction migration to extension
10746  for (auto g : Geometry.getValues()) {
10747 
10748  if (g->hasExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId())) {
10749  auto ext = std::static_pointer_cast<Part::GeometryMigrationExtension>(
10750  g->getExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId()).lock());
10751 
10752  if (ext->testMigrationType(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::Construction)) {
10753  // at this point IA geometry is already migrated
10754  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(g);
10755 
10756  bool oldconstr = ext->getConstruction();
10757 
10758  if (g->is<Part::GeomPoint>()
10759  && !gf->isInternalAligned())
10760  oldconstr = true;
10761 
10762  GeometryFacade::setConstruction(g, oldconstr);
10763  }
10764 
10765  g->deleteExtension(Part::GeometryMigrationExtension::getClassTypeId());
10766  }
10767  }
10768  }
10769 
10770  /* parabola axis as internal geometry */
10771  auto constraints = Constraints.getValues();
10772  auto geometries = getInternalGeometry();
10773 
10774  auto parabolafound = std::find_if(geometries.begin(), geometries.end(), [](Part::Geometry* g) {
10775  return g->is<Part::GeomArcOfParabola>();
10776  });
10777 
10778  if (parabolafound != geometries.end()) {
10779 
10780  auto focalaxisfound = std::find_if(constraints.begin(), constraints.end(), [](auto c) {
10781  return c->Type == InternalAlignment && c->AlignmentType == ParabolaFocalAxis;
10782  });
10783 
10784  // There are parabolas and there isn't an IA axis. (1) there are no axis or (2) there is a
10785  // legacy construction line
10786  if (focalaxisfound == constraints.end()) {
10787 
10788  // maps parabola geoid to focusgeoid
10789  std::map<int, int> parabolageoid2focusgeoid;
10790 
10791  // populate parabola and focus geoids
10792  for (const auto& c : constraints) {
10793  if (c->Type == InternalAlignment && c->AlignmentType == ParabolaFocus) {
10794  parabolageoid2focusgeoid[c->Second] = {c->First};
10795  }
10796  }
10797 
10798  // maps axis geoid to parabolageoid
10799  std::map<int, int> axisgeoid2parabolageoid;
10800 
10801  // populate axis geoid
10802  for (const auto& [parabolageoid, focusgeoid] : parabolageoid2focusgeoid) {
10803  // look for a line from focusgeoid:start to Geoid:mid_external
10804  std::vector<int> focusgeoidlistgeoidlist;
10805  std::vector<PointPos> focusposidlist;
10806  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(
10807  focusgeoid, Sketcher::PointPos::start, focusgeoidlistgeoidlist, focusposidlist);
10808 
10809  std::vector<int> parabgeoidlistgeoidlist;
10810  std::vector<PointPos> parabposidlist;
10811  getDirectlyCoincidentPoints(parabolageoid,
10812  Sketcher::PointPos::mid,
10813  parabgeoidlistgeoidlist,
10814  parabposidlist);
10815 
10816  if (!focusgeoidlistgeoidlist.empty() && !parabgeoidlistgeoidlist.empty()) {
10817  std::size_t i, j;
10818  for (i = 0; i < focusgeoidlistgeoidlist.size(); i++) {
10819  for (j = 0; j < parabgeoidlistgeoidlist.size(); j++) {
10820  if (focusgeoidlistgeoidlist[i] == parabgeoidlistgeoidlist[j]) {
10821  axisgeoid2parabolageoid[focusgeoidlistgeoidlist[i]] = parabolageoid;
10822  }
10823  }
10824  }
10825  }
10826  }
10827 
10828  std::vector<Constraint*> newconstraints;
10829  newconstraints.reserve(constraints.size());
10830 
10831  for (const auto& c : constraints) {
10832 
10833  if (c->Type != Coincident) {
10834  newconstraints.push_back(c);
10835  }
10836  else {
10837  auto axismajorcoincidentfound =
10838  std::find_if(axisgeoid2parabolageoid.begin(),
10839  axisgeoid2parabolageoid.end(),
10840  [&](const auto& pair) {
10841  auto parabolageoid = pair.second;
10842  auto axisgeoid = pair.first;
10843  return (c->First == axisgeoid && c->Second == parabolageoid
10844  && c->SecondPos == PointPos::mid)
10845  || (c->Second == axisgeoid && c->First == parabolageoid
10846  && c->FirstPos == PointPos::mid);
10847  });
10848 
10849  if (axismajorcoincidentfound != axisgeoid2parabolageoid.end()) {
10850  // we skip this coincident, the other coincident on axis will be substituted
10851  // by internal geometry constraint
10852  continue;
10853  }
10854 
10855  auto focuscoincidentfound =
10856  std::find_if(axisgeoid2parabolageoid.begin(),
10857  axisgeoid2parabolageoid.end(),
10858  [&](const auto& pair) {
10859  auto parabolageoid = pair.second;
10860  auto axisgeoid = pair.first;
10861  auto focusgeoid = parabolageoid2focusgeoid[parabolageoid];
10862  return (c->First == axisgeoid && c->Second == focusgeoid
10863  && c->SecondPos == PointPos::start)
10864  || (c->Second == axisgeoid && c->First == focusgeoid
10865  && c->FirstPos == PointPos::start);
10866  });
10867 
10868  if (focuscoincidentfound != axisgeoid2parabolageoid.end()) {
10869  Sketcher::Constraint* newConstr = new Sketcher::Constraint();
10870  newConstr->Type = Sketcher::InternalAlignment;
10871  newConstr->AlignmentType = Sketcher::ParabolaFocalAxis;
10872  newConstr->First = focuscoincidentfound->first;// axis geoid
10873  newConstr->FirstPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
10874  newConstr->Second = focuscoincidentfound->second;// parabola geoid
10875  newConstr->SecondPos = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
10876  newconstraints.push_back(newConstr);
10877 
10878  addGeometryState(newConstr);
10879 
10880  // we skip the coincident, as we have substituted it by internal geometry
10881  // constraint
10882  continue;
10883  }
10884 
10885  newconstraints.push_back(c);
10886  }
10887  }
10888 
10889  Constraints.setValues(std::move(newconstraints));
10890 
10891  Base::Console().Critical(
10892  this->getFullName(),
10893  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications",
10894  "Parabolas were migrated. Migrated files won't open in previous "
10895  "versions of FreeCAD!!\n"));
10896  }
10897  }
10898 }

10901 {
10902  if (VertexId < 0 || VertexId >= int(VertexId2GeoId.size())) {
10903  GeoId = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
10904  PosId = PointPos::none;
10905  return;
10906  }
10907  GeoId = VertexId2GeoId[VertexId];
10908  PosId = VertexId2PosId[VertexId];
10909 }

10911 int SketchObject::getVertexIndexGeoPos(int GeoId, PointPos PosId) const

10914  if (VertexId2GeoId[i] == GeoId && VertexId2PosId[i] == PosId)
10915  return i;
10916  }
10917 
10918  return -1;

10920 
10930 int SketchObject::changeConstraintsLocking(bool bLock)
10931 {
10932  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
10933  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
10934 
10935  int cntSuccess = 0;
10936  int cntToBeAffected = 0;//==cntSuccess+cntFail
10937  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
10938 
10939  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);// modifiable copy of pointers array
10940 
10941  for (size_t i = 0; i < newVals.size(); i++) {
10942  if (newVals[i]->Type == Tangent || newVals[i]->Type == Perpendicular) {
10943  // create a constraint copy, affect it, replace the pointer
10944  cntToBeAffected++;
10945  Constraint* constNew = newVals[i]->clone();
10946  bool ret = AutoLockTangencyAndPerpty(newVals[i], /*bForce=*/true, bLock);
10947 
10948  if (ret)
10949  cntSuccess++;
10950 
10951  newVals[i] = constNew;
10952  Base::Console().Log("Constraint%i will be affected\n", i + 1);
10953  }
10954  }
10955 
10956  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
10957 
10958  Base::Console().Log("ChangeConstraintsLocking: affected %i of %i tangent/perp constraints\n",
10959  cntSuccess,
10960  cntToBeAffected);
10961 
10962  return cntSuccess;
10963 }
10964 
10972 int SketchObject::port_reversedExternalArcs(bool justAnalyze)
10973 {
10974  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
10975  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
10976 
10977  int cntToBeAffected = 0;//==cntSuccess+cntFail
10978  const std::vector<Constraint*>& vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
10979 
10980  std::vector<Constraint*> newVals(vals);// modifiable copy of pointers array
10981 
10982  for (std::size_t ic = 0; ic < newVals.size(); ic++) {// ic = index of constraint
10983  bool affected = false;
10984  Constraint* constNew = nullptr;
10985  for (int ig = 1; ig <= 3; ig++) {// cycle through constraint.first, second, third
10986  int geoId = 0;
10987  Sketcher::PointPos posId = PointPos::none;
10988  switch (ig) {
10989  case 1:
10990  geoId = newVals[ic]->First;
10991  posId = newVals[ic]->FirstPos;
10992  break;
10993  case 2:
10994  geoId = newVals[ic]->Second;
10995  posId = newVals[ic]->SecondPos;
10996  break;
10997  case 3:
10998  geoId = newVals[ic]->Third;
10999  posId = newVals[ic]->ThirdPos;
11000  break;
11001  }
11002 
11003  if (geoId <= GeoEnum::RefExt
11004  && (posId == Sketcher::PointPos::start || posId == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
11005  // we are dealing with a link to an endpoint of external geom
11006 // Part::Geometry* g = this->ExternalGeo[-geoId - 1];
11007  Part::Geometry* g = this->ExternalGeo[-geoId - 1];
11008  if (g->is<Part::GeomArcOfCircle>()) {
11009  const Part::GeomArcOfCircle* segm =
11010  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(g);
11011  if (segm->isReversed()) {
11012  // Gotcha! a link to an endpoint of external arc that is reversed.
11013  // create a constraint copy, affect it, replace the pointer
11014  if (!affected)
11015  constNew = newVals[ic]->clone();
11016  affected = true;
11017  // Do the fix on temp vars
11018  if (posId == Sketcher::PointPos::start)
11019  posId = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
11020  else if (posId == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
11021  posId = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
11022  }
11023  }
11024  }
11025  if (!affected)
11026  continue;
11027  // Propagate the fix made on temp vars to the constraint
11028  switch (ig) {
11029  case 1:
11030  constNew->First = geoId;
11031  constNew->FirstPos = posId;
11032  break;
11033  case 2:
11034  constNew->Second = geoId;
11035  constNew->SecondPos = posId;
11036  break;
11037  case 3:
11038  constNew->Third = geoId;
11039  constNew->ThirdPos = posId;
11040  break;
11041  }
11042  }
11043  if (affected) {
11044  cntToBeAffected++;
11045  newVals[ic] = constNew;
11046  Base::Console().Log("Constraint%i will be affected\n", ic + 1);
11047  };
11048  }
11049 
11050  if (!justAnalyze) {
11051  this->Constraints.setValues(std::move(newVals));
11052  Base::Console().Log("Swapped start/end of reversed external arcs in %i constraints\n",
11053  cntToBeAffected);
11054  }
11055 
11056  return cntToBeAffected;
11057 }
11058 
11078 bool SketchObject::AutoLockTangencyAndPerpty(Constraint* cstr, bool bForce, bool bLock)
11079 {
11080  try {
11081  // assert ( cstr->Type == Tangent || cstr->Type == Perpendicular);
11082  /*tangency type already set. If not bForce - don't touch.*/
11083  if (cstr->getValue() != 0.0 && !bForce)
11084  return true;
11085  if (!bLock) {
11086  cstr->setValue(0.0);// reset
11087  }
11088  else {
11089  // decide on tangency type. Write the angle value into the datum field of the
11090  // constraint.
11091  int geoId1, geoId2, geoIdPt;
11092  PointPos posPt;
11093  geoId1 = cstr->First;
11094  geoId2 = cstr->Second;
11095  geoIdPt = cstr->Third;
11096  posPt = cstr->ThirdPos;
11097  if (geoIdPt == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {// not tangent-via-point, try endpoint-to-endpoint...
11098 
11099  // First check if it is a tangency at knot constraint, if not continue with checking
11100  // for endpoints. Endpoint constraints make use of the AngleViaPoint framework at
11101  // solver level, so they need locking angle calculation, tangency at knot constraint
11102  // does not.
11103  auto geof = getGeometryFacade(cstr->First);
11104  if (geof->isInternalType(InternalType::BSplineKnotPoint)) {
11105  // there is point that is a B-Spline knot in a two element constraint
11106  // this is not implement using AngleViaPoint (TangencyViaPoint)
11107  return false;
11108  }
11109 
11110  geoIdPt = cstr->First;
11111  posPt = cstr->FirstPos;
11112  }
11113  if (posPt == PointPos::none) {
11114  // not endpoint-to-curve and not endpoint-to-endpoint tangent (is simple tangency)
11115  // no tangency lockdown is implemented for simple tangency. Do nothing.
11116  return false;
11117  }
11118 
11119  Base::Vector3d p = getPoint(geoIdPt, posPt);
11120 
11121  // this piece of code is also present in Sketch.cpp, correct for offset
11122  // and to do the autodecision for old sketches.
11123  // the difference between the datum value and the actual angle to apply.
11124  // (datum=angle+offset)
11125  double angleOffset = 0.0;
11126  // the desired angle value (and we are to decide if 180* should be added to it)
11127  double angleDesire = 0.0;
11128  if (cstr->Type == Tangent) {
11129  angleOffset = -M_PI / 2;
11130  angleDesire = 0.0;
11131  }
11132  if (cstr->Type == Perpendicular) {
11133  angleOffset = 0;
11134  angleDesire = M_PI / 2;
11135  }
11136 
11137  double angleErr = calculateAngleViaPoint(geoId1, geoId2, p.x, p.y) - angleDesire;
11138 
11139  // bring angleErr to -pi..pi
11140  if (angleErr > M_PI)
11141  angleErr -= M_PI * 2;
11142  if (angleErr < -M_PI)
11143  angleErr += M_PI * 2;
11144 
11145  // the autodetector
11146  if (fabs(angleErr) > M_PI / 2)
11147  angleDesire += M_PI;
11148 
11149  // external tangency. The angle stored is offset by Pi/2 so that a value of 0.0 is
11150  // invalid and treated as "undecided".
11151  cstr->setValue(angleDesire + angleOffset);
11152  }
11153  }
11154  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
11155  // failure to determine tangency type is not a big deal, so a warning.
11156  Base::Console().Warning("Error in AutoLockTangency. %s \n", e.what());
11157  return false;
11158  }
11159  return true;
11160 }
11161 
11162 App::DocumentObject *SketchObject::getSubObject(
11163  const char *subname, PyObject **pyObj,
11164  Base::Matrix4D *pmat, bool transform, int depth) const
11165 {
11166  while(subname && *subname=='.') ++subname; // skip leading .
11167  std::string sub;
11168  const char *mapped = Data::isMappedElement(subname);
11169  if(!subname || !subname[0])
11170  return Part2DObject::getSubObject(subname,pyObj,pmat,transform,depth);
11171  const char *element = Data::findElementName(subname);
11172  if(element != subname) {
11173  const char *dot = strchr(subname,'.');
11174  if(!dot)
11175  return 0;
11176  std::string name(subname,dot-subname);
11177  auto child = Exports.find(name.c_str());
11178  if(!child)
11179  return 0;
11180  return child->getSubObject(dot+1,pyObj,pmat,true,depth+1);
11181  }
11182 
11183  Data::IndexedName indexedName = checkSubName(subname);
11184  int index = indexedName.getIndex();
11185  const char * shapetype = indexedName.getType();
11186  const Part::Geometry *geo = 0;
11187  Part::TopoShape subshape;
11188  Base::Vector3d point;
11189 
11190  if (auto realType = convertInternalName(indexedName.getType())) {
11191  if (realType[0] == '\0')
11192  subshape = InternalShape.getShape();
11193  else {
11194  auto shapeType = Part::TopoShape::shapeType(realType, true);
11195  if (shapeType != TopAbs_SHAPE)
11196  subshape = InternalShape.getShape().getSubTopoShape(shapeType, indexedName.getIndex(), true);
11197  }
11198  if (subshape.isNull())
11199  return nullptr;
11200  }
11201  else if (!pyObj || !mapped) {
11202  if (!pyObj
11203  || (index > 0
11204  && !boost::algorithm::contains(subname, "edge")
11205  && !boost::algorithm::contains(subname, "vertex")))
11206  return Part2DObject::getSubObject(subname,pyObj,pmat,transform,depth);
11207  } else {
11208  subshape = Shape.getShape().getSubTopoShape(subname, true);
11209  if (!subshape.isNull())
11210  return Part2DObject::getSubObject(subname,pyObj,pmat,transform,depth);
11211  }
11212 
11213  if (subshape.isNull()) {
11214  if (boost::equals(shapetype,"Edge") ||
11215  boost::equals(shapetype,"edge")) {
11216  geo = getGeometry(index - 1);
11217  if (!geo)
11218  return nullptr;
11219  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"ExternalEdge")) {
11220  int GeoId = index - 1;
11221  GeoId = -GeoId - 3;
11222  geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
11223  if(!geo)
11224  return nullptr;
11225  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"Vertex") ||
11226  boost::equals(shapetype,"vertex")) {
11227  int VtId = index- 1;
11228  int GeoId;
11229  PointPos PosId;
11230  getGeoVertexIndex(VtId,GeoId,PosId);
11231  if (PosId==PointPos::none)
11232  return nullptr;
11233  point = getPoint(GeoId,PosId);
11234  }
11235  else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"RootPoint"))
11236  point = getPoint(Sketcher::GeoEnum::RtPnt,PointPos::start);
11237  else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"H_Axis"))
11238  geo = getGeometry(Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis);
11239  else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"V_Axis"))
11240  geo = getGeometry(Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis);
11241  else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"Constraint")) {
11242  int ConstrId = PropertyConstraintList::getIndexFromConstraintName(shapetype);
11243  const std::vector< Constraint * > &vals = this->Constraints.getValues();
11244  if (ConstrId < 0 || ConstrId >= int(vals.size()))
11245  return nullptr;
11246  if(pyObj)
11247  *pyObj = vals[ConstrId]->getPyObject();
11248  return const_cast<SketchObject*>(this);
11249  } else
11250  return nullptr;
11251  }
11252 
11253  if (pmat && transform)
11254  *pmat *= Placement.getValue().toMatrix();
11255 
11256  if (pyObj) {
11257  Part::TopoShape shape;
11258  std::string name = convertSubName(indexedName,false);
11259  if (geo) {
11260  shape = getEdge(geo,name.c_str());
11261  if(pmat && !shape.isNull())
11262  shape.transformShape(*pmat,false,true);
11263  } else if (!subshape.isNull()) {
11264  shape = subshape;
11265  if (pmat)
11266  shape.transformShape(*pmat,false,true);
11267  } else {
11268  if(pmat)
11269  point = (*pmat)*point;
11270  shape = BRepBuilderAPI_MakeVertex(gp_Pnt(point.x,point.y,point.z)).Vertex();
11271  // Originally in ComplexGeoData::setElementName
11272  // LinkStable/src/App/ComplexGeoData.cpp#L1631
11273  // No longer possible after map separated in ElementMap.cpp
11274  if ( !shape.hasElementMap() ) {
11275  shape.resetElementMap(std::make_shared<Data::ElementMap>());
11276  }
11277  shape.setElementName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", 1),
11278  Data::MappedName::fromRawData(name.c_str()),0);
11279  }
11280  shape.Tag = getID();
11281  *pyObj = Py::new_reference_to(Part::shape2pyshape(shape));
11282  }
11283 
11284  return const_cast<SketchObject*>(this);
11285 }
11286 
11287 std::vector<Data::IndexedName>
11288 SketchObject::getHigherElements(const char *element, bool silent) const
11289 {
11290  std::vector<Data::IndexedName> res;
11291  if (boost::istarts_with(element, "vertex")) {
11292  int n = 0;
11293  int index = atoi(element+6);
11294  for (auto cstr : Constraints.getValues()) {
11295  ++n;
11296  if (cstr->Type != Sketcher::Coincident)
11297  continue;
11298  if(cstr->First >= 0 && index == getSolvedSketch().getPointId(cstr->First, cstr->FirstPos) + 1)
11299  res.push_back(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Constraint", n));
11300  if(cstr->Second >= 0 && index == getSolvedSketch().getPointId(cstr->Second, cstr->SecondPos) + 1)
11301  res.push_back(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Constraint", n));
11302  }
11303  }
11304  return res;
11305 
11306  auto getNames = [this, &silent, &res](const char *element) {
11307  bool internal = boost::starts_with(element, internalPrefix());
11308  const auto &shape = internal ? InternalShape.getShape() : Shape.getShape();
11309  for (const auto &indexedName : shape.getHigherElements(element+(internal?internalPrefix().size() : 0), silent)) {
11310  if (!internal) {
11311  res.push_back(indexedName);
11312  }
11313  else if (boost::equals(indexedName.getType(), "Face")
11314  || boost::equals(indexedName.getType(), "Edge")
11315  || boost::equals(indexedName.getType(), "Wire")) {
11316  res.emplace_back((internalPrefix() + indexedName.getType()).c_str(), indexedName.getIndex());
11317  }
11318  }
11319  };
11320  getNames(element);
11321  const auto &elementMap = getInternalElementMap();
11322  auto it = elementMap.find(element);
11323  if (it != elementMap.end()) {
11324  res.emplace_back(it->second.c_str());
11325  getNames(it->second.c_str());
11326  }
11327  return res;
11328 }
11329 
11330 std::vector<const char *> SketchObject::getElementTypes(bool all) const
11331 {
11332  if (!all)
11333  return Part::Part2DObject::getElementTypes();
11334  static std::vector<const char *> res { Part::TopoShape::shapeName(TopAbs_VERTEX).c_str(),
11335  Part::TopoShape::shapeName(TopAbs_EDGE).c_str(),
11336  "ExternalEdge",
11337  "Constraint",
11338  "InternalEdge",
11339  "InternalFace",
11340  "InternalVertex",
11341  };
11342  return res;
11343 }
11344 
11345 void SketchObject::setExpression(const App::ObjectIdentifier& path,
11346  std::shared_ptr<App::Expression> expr)
11347 {
11348  DocumentObject::setExpression(path, expr);
11349 
11350  if (noRecomputes) {
11351  // if we do not have a recompute, the sketch must be solved to update the DoF of the solver,
11352  // constraints and UI
11353  try {
11354  auto res = ExpressionEngine.execute();
11355  if (res) {
11356  FC_ERR("Failed to recompute " << ExpressionEngine.getFullName() << ": "
11357  << res->Why);
11358  delete res;
11359  }
11360  }
11361  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
11362  e.ReportException();
11363  FC_ERR("Failed to recompute " << ExpressionEngine.getFullName() << ": " << e.what());
11364  }
11365  solve();
11366  }
11367 }

11375 const char *SketchObject::convertInternalName(const char *name)

11379  return nullptr;
11380 }
11381 
11382 App::ElementNamePair SketchObject::getElementName(
11383  const char *name, ElementNameType type) const
11384 {
11385  App::ElementNamePair ret;
11386  if(!name) return ret;
11387 
11388  if(hasSketchMarker(name))
11389  return Part2DObject::getElementName(name,type);
11390 
11391  const char *mapped = Data::isMappedElement(name);
11392  Data::IndexedName index = checkSubName(name);
11393  index.appendToStringBuffer(ret.oldName);
11394  if (auto realName = convertInternalName(ret.oldName.c_str())) {
11395  Data::MappedElement mappedElement;
11396  if (mapped)
11397  mappedElement = InternalShape.getShape().getElementName(name);
11398  else if (type == ElementNameType::Export)
11399  ret.newName = getExportElementName(InternalShape.getShape(), realName).newName;
11400  else
11401  mappedElement = InternalShape.getShape().getElementName(realName);
11402 
11403  if (mapped || type != ElementNameType::Export) {
11404  if (mappedElement.index) {
11405  ret.oldName = internalPrefix();
11406  mappedElement.index.appendToStringBuffer(ret.oldName);
11407  }
11408  if (mappedElement.name) {
11409  ret.newName = Data::ComplexGeoData::elementMapPrefix();
11410  mappedElement.name.appendToBuffer(ret.newName);
11411  }
11412  else if (mapped)
11413  ret.newName = name;
11414  }
11415 
11416  if (ret.newName.size()) {
11417  if (auto dot = strrchr(ret.newName.c_str(), '.'))
11418  ret.newName.resize(dot+1-ret.newName.c_str());
11419  else
11420  ret.newName += ".";
11421  ret.newName += ret.oldName;
11422  }
11423  if (mapped && (!mappedElement.index || !mappedElement.name))
11424  ret.oldName.insert(0, Data::MISSING_PREFIX);
11425  return ret;
11426  }
11427 
11428  if(!mapped) {
11429  auto occindex = Part::TopoShape::shapeTypeAndIndex(name);
11430  if (occindex.second)
11431  return Part2DObject::getElementName(name,type);
11432  }
11433  if(index && type==ElementNameType::Export) {
11434  if(boost::starts_with(ret.oldName,"Vertex"))
11435  ret.oldName[0] = 'v';
11436  else if(boost::starts_with(ret.oldName,"Edge"))
11437  ret.oldName[0] = 'e';
11438  }
11439  ret.newName = convertSubName(index, true);
11440  if(!Data::isMappedElement(ret.newName.c_str()))
11441  ret.newName.clear();
11442  return ret;
11443 }
11444 
11445 Part::TopoShape SketchObject::getEdge(const Part::Geometry *geo, const char *name) const
11446 {
11447  Part::TopoShape shape(geo->toShape());
11448  // Originally in ComplexGeoData::setElementName
11449  // LinkStable/src/App/ComplexGeoData.cpp#L1631
11450  // No longer possible after map separated in ElementMap.cpp
11451  if ( !shape.hasElementMap() ) {
11452  shape.resetElementMap(std::make_shared<Data::ElementMap>());
11453  }
11454  shape.setElementName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Edge", 1),
11455  Data::MappedName::fromRawData(name),0L);
11456  TopTools_IndexedMapOfShape vmap;
11457  TopExp::MapShapes(shape.getShape(), TopAbs_VERTEX, vmap);
11458  std::ostringstream ss;
11459  for(int i=1;i<=vmap.Extent();++i) {
11460  auto gpt = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(vmap(i)));
11461  Base::Vector3d pt(gpt.X(),gpt.Y(),gpt.Z());
11462  PointPos pos[] = {PointPos::start,PointPos::end};
11463  for(size_t j=0;j<sizeof(pos)/sizeof(pos[0]);++j) {
11464  if(getPoint(geo,pos[j]) == pt) {
11465  ss.str("");
11466  ss << name << 'v' << static_cast<int>(pos[j]);
11467  shape.setElementName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", i),
11468  Data::MappedName::fromRawData(ss.str().c_str()),0L);
11469  break;
11470  }
11471  }
11472  }
11473  return shape;
11474 }
11475 
11476 Data::IndexedName SketchObject::checkSubName(const char *subname) const{
11477  static std::vector<const char *> types = {
11478  "Edge",
11479  "Vertex",
11480  "edge",
11481  "vertex",
11482  "ExternalEdge",
11483  "RootPoint",
11484  "H_Axis",
11485  "V_Axis",
11486  "Constraint",
11487 
11488  // other feature from LS3 not related to TNP
11489  "InternalEdge",
11490  "InternalFace",
11491  "InternalVertex",
11492  };
11493 
11494  if(!subname) return Data::IndexedName();
11495  const char *mappedSubname = Data::isMappedElement(subname);
11496 
11497  // if not a mapped name parse the indexed name directly, uppercasing "edge" and "vertex"
11498  if(!mappedSubname) {
11499  Data::IndexedName result(subname, types, true);
11500  if (boost::equals(result.getType(), "edge"))
11501  return Data::IndexedName("Edge", result.getIndex());
11502  if (boost::equals(result.getType(), "vertex"))
11503  return Data::IndexedName("Vertex", result.getIndex());
11504  return result;
11505  }
11506 
11507  bio::stream<bio::array_source> iss(mappedSubname+1, std::strlen(mappedSubname+1));
11508  int id = -1;
11509  bool valid = false;
11510  switch (mappedSubname[0]) {
11511  case '\0': // check length != 0
11512  break;
11513 
11514  case 'g': // = geometry
11515  case 'e': // = external geometry
11516  if (iss >> id) {
11517  valid = true;
11518  }
11519  break;
11520 
11521  // for RootPoint, H_Axis, V_Axis
11522  default: {
11523  const char* dot = strchr(mappedSubname, '.');
11524  if (dot) {
11525  mappedSubname = dot + 1;
11526  }
11527  return Data::IndexedName(mappedSubname, types, false);
11528  }
11529  }
11530 
11531  if (!valid) {
11532  FC_ERR("invalid subname " << subname);
11533  return Data::IndexedName();
11534  }
11535 
11536  int geoId;
11537  const Part::Geometry* geo = 0;
11538  switch (mappedSubname[0]) {
11539  case 'g': {
11540  auto it = geoMap.find(id);
11541  if (it != geoMap.end()) {
11542  geoId = it->second;
11543  geo = getGeometry(geoId);
11544  }
11545  break;
11546  }
11547  case 'e': {
11548  auto it = externalGeoMap.find(id);
11549  if (it != externalGeoMap.end()) {
11550  geoId = -it->second - 1;
11551  geo = getGeometry(geoId);
11552  }
11553  break;
11554  }
11555  }
11556  if (geo && GeometryFacade::getId(geo) == id) {
11557  char sep;
11558  int posId = static_cast<int>(PointPos::none);
11559  if ((iss >> sep >> posId) && sep == 'v') {
11560  int idx = getVertexIndexGeoPos(geoId, static_cast<PointPos>(posId));
11561  if (idx < 0) {
11562  FC_ERR("invalid subname " << subname);
11563  return Data::IndexedName();
11564  }
11565  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", idx + 1);
11566  }
11567  else if (geoId >= 0) {
11568  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Edge", geoId + 1);
11569  }
11570  else {
11571  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("ExternalEdge", -geoId - 2);
11572  }
11573  }
11574  FC_ERR("cannot find subname " << subname);
11575 
11576  return Data::IndexedName();
11577 }
11578 
11579 Data::IndexedName SketchObject::shapeTypeFromGeoId(int geoId, PointPos posId) const
11580 {
11581  if (geoId == GeoEnum::HAxis) {
11582  if (posId == PointPos::start) {
11583  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("RootPoint", 0);
11584  }
11585  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("H_Axis", 0);
11586  }
11587  if (geoId == GeoEnum::VAxis) {
11588  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("V_Axis", 0);
11589  }
11590 
11591  if (posId == PointPos::none) {
11592  auto geo = getGeometry(geoId);
11593  if (geo && geo->isDerivedFrom(Part::GeomPoint::getClassTypeId())) {
11594  posId = PointPos::start;
11595  }
11596  }
11597  if(posId != PointPos::none) {
11598  int idx = getVertexIndexGeoPos(geoId, posId);
11599  if (idx < 0) {
11600  return Data::IndexedName();
11601  }
11602  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", idx + 1);
11603  }
11604  if (geoId >= 0) {
11605  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Edge", geoId + 1);
11606  }
11607  return Data::IndexedName::fromConst("ExternalEdge", -geoId - 2);
11608 }
11609 
11610 bool SketchObject::geoIdFromShapeType(const Data::IndexedName & indexedName,
11611  int &geoId,
11612  PointPos &posId) const
11613 {
11614  posId = PointPos::none;
11615  geoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
11616  if (!indexedName)
11617  return false;
11618  const char *shapetype = indexedName.getType();
11619  if (boost::equals(shapetype,"Edge") ||
11620  boost::equals(shapetype,"edge")) {
11621  geoId = indexedName.getIndex() - 1;
11622  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"ExternalEdge")) {
11623  geoId = indexedName.getIndex() - 1;
11624  geoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt - geoId;
11625  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"Vertex") ||
11626  boost::equals(shapetype,"vertex")) {
11627  int VtId = indexedName.getIndex() - 1;
11628  getGeoVertexIndex(VtId,geoId,posId);
11629  if (posId==PointPos::none) return false;
11630  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"H_Axis")) {
11631  geoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis;
11632  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"V_Axis")) {
11633  geoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis;
11634  } else if (boost::equals(shapetype,"RootPoint")) {
11635  geoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::RtPnt;
11636  posId = PointPos::start;
11637  } else
11638  return false;
11639  return true;
11640 }
11641 
11642 std::string SketchObject::convertSubName(const char *subname, bool postfix) const {
11643  return convertSubName(checkSubName(subname), postfix);
11644 }
11645 
11646 std::string SketchObject::convertSubName(const Data::IndexedName &indexedName, bool postfix) const {
11647  std::ostringstream ss;
11648  if (auto realType = convertInternalName(indexedName.getType())) {
11649  auto mapped = InternalShape.getShape().getMappedName(
11650  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(realType, indexedName.getIndex()));
11651  if (!mapped) {
11652  if (postfix)
11653  ss << indexedName;
11654  } else if (postfix)
11655  ss << Data::ComplexGeoData::elementMapPrefix() << mapped << '.' << indexedName;
11656  else
11657  ss << mapped;
11658  return ss.str();
11659  }
11660  int geoId;
11661  PointPos posId;
11662  if (!geoIdFromShapeType(indexedName, geoId, posId)) {
11663  ss << indexedName;
11664  return ss.str();
11665  }
11666  if (geoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis ||
11667  geoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis ||
11668  geoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::RtPnt) {
11669  if (postfix)
11670  ss << Data::ELEMENT_MAP_PREFIX;
11671  ss << indexedName;
11672  if (postfix)
11673  ss << '.' << indexedName;
11674  return ss.str();
11675  }
11676 
11677  auto geo = getGeometry(geoId);
11678  if (!geo) {
11679  std::string res = indexedName.toString();
11680  return res;
11681  }
11682  if (postfix)
11683  ss << Data::ELEMENT_MAP_PREFIX;
11684  ss << (geoId >= 0 ? 'g' : 'e') << GeometryFacade::getFacade(geo)->getId();
11685  if (posId != PointPos::none)
11686  ss << 'v' << static_cast<int>(posId);
11687  if (postfix) {
11688  // rename Edge to edge, and Vertex to vertex to avoid ambiguous of
11689  // element mapping of the public shape and internal geometry.
11690  if (indexedName.getIndex() <= 0)
11691  ss << '.' << indexedName;
11692  else if (boost::starts_with(indexedName.getType(), "Edge"))
11693  ss << ".e" << (indexedName.getType() + 1) << indexedName.getIndex();
11694  else if (boost::starts_with(indexedName.getType(), "Vertex"))
11695  ss << ".v" << (indexedName.getType() + 1) << indexedName.getIndex();
11696  else
11697  ss << '.' << indexedName;
11698  }
11699  return ss.str();
11700 }
11701 
11702 std::string SketchObject::getGeometryReference(int GeoId) const {
11703  auto geo = getGeometry(GeoId);
11704  if (!geo) {
11705  return {};
11706  }
11707  auto egf = ExternalGeometryFacade::getFacade(geo);
11708  if (egf->getRef().empty()) {
11709  return {};
11710  }
11711 
11712  const std::string &ref = egf->getRef();
11713 
11714  if (egf->testFlag(ExternalGeometryExtension::Missing)) {
11715  return std::string("? ") + ref;
11716  }
11717 
11718  auto pos = ref.find('.');
11719  if (pos == std::string::npos) {
11720  return ref;
11721  }
11722  std::string objName = ref.substr(0, pos);
11723  auto obj = getDocument()->getObject(objName.c_str());
11724  if (!obj) {
11725  return ref;
11726  }
11727 
11728  App::ElementNamePair elementName;
11729  App::GeoFeature::resolveElement(obj, ref.c_str() + pos + 1, elementName);
11730  if (!elementName.oldName.empty()) {
11731  return objName + "." + elementName.oldName;
11732  }
11733  return ref;
11734 }

11839 int SketchObject::autoRemoveRedundants(bool updategeo)
11840 {
11841  auto redundants = getLastRedundant();
11842 
11843  if (redundants.empty())
11844  return 0;
11845 
11846  // getLastRedundant is base 1, while delConstraints is base 0
11847  for (size_t i = 0; i < redundants.size(); i++)
11848  redundants[i]--;
11849 
11850  delConstraints(redundants, updategeo);
11851 
11852  return redundants.size();
11853 }
11854 
11855 int SketchObject::renameConstraint(int GeoId, std::string name)
11856 {
11857  // only change the constraint item if the names are different
11858  const Constraint* item = Constraints[GeoId];
11859 
11860  if (item->Name != name) {
11861  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
11862  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
11863 
11864  Constraint* copy = item->clone();
11865  copy->Name = name;
11866 
11867  Constraints.set1Value(GeoId, copy);
11868  delete copy;
11869 
11870  // make sure any prospective solver access updates the constraint pointer that just got
11871  // invalidated
11872  solverNeedsUpdate = true;
11873 
11874  return 0;
11875  }
11876  return -1;
11877 }

11889 // SketchGeometryExtension interface
11890 
11891 int SketchObject::setGeometryId(int GeoId, long id)
11892 {
11893  // no need to check input data validity as this is an sketchobject managed operation.
11894  Base::StateLocker lock(managedoperation, true);
11895 
11896  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId >= int(Geometry.getValues().size()))
11897  return -1;
11898 
11899  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
11900 
11901 
11902  std::vector<Part::Geometry*> newVals(vals);
11903 
11904  // deep copy
11905  for (size_t i = 0; i < newVals.size(); i++) {
11906  newVals[i] = newVals[i]->clone();
11907 
11908  if ((int)i == GeoId) {
11909  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(newVals[i]);
11910 
11911  gf->setId(id);
11912  }
11913  }
11914 
11915  // There is not actual internal transaction going on here, however neither the geometry indices
11916  // nor the vertices need to be updated so this is a convenient way of preventing it.
11917  {
11918  Base::StateLocker lock(internaltransaction, true);
11919  this->Geometry.setValues(std::move(newVals));
11920  }
11921 
11922  return 0;
11923 }
11924 
11925 int SketchObject::getGeometryId(int GeoId, long& id) const
11926 {
11927  if (GeoId < 0 || GeoId >= int(Geometry.getValues().size()))
11928  return -1;
11929 
11930  const std::vector<Part::Geometry*>& vals = getInternalGeometry();
11931 
11932  auto gf = GeometryFacade::getFacade(vals[GeoId]);
11933 
11934  id = gf->getId();
11935 
11936  return 0;
11937 }

11954  // ref counter is set to 1
11955  PythonObject = Py::Object(new FeaturePythonPyT<SketchObjectPy>(this), true);
11956  }
11957  return Py::new_reference_to(PythonObject);
11958 }
